{"id": "9224", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9224", "title": "Goldander Blackenrock", "text": "Goldander Blackenrock is a &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Gnome\"&gt;svirfneblin&lt;/a&gt; who functions as the leader of the mining settlement \"village\" in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; near the &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; city of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nHe will greet the party in a friendly manner, although warily as well. Goldander will engage in dialogue, and answer questions about the gnome operation and its relationship with the nearby drow. \nHe'll also raise a serious subject regarding a potentially threatening situation facing the gnomes, and request assistance from the party. If the party agrees to help, then he'll promise a reward to assist the party in its search for Irenicus and Bodhi. This is further discussed on the quest page &lt;a href=\"Svirfneblin%20village%20concerns\"&gt;Svirfneblin village concerns&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that Goldander isn't immune to being pick pocketed. It's possible a rogue could purloin the &lt;a href=\"Light%20Gem\"&gt;Light Gem&lt;/a&gt; he carries, which is meant to be a reward for completing his requested task. There may be negative repercussions to the party if the gem is obtained through theft, rather than given as a reward.\nAttacking Goldander before deciding on the Seal the Monster quest will negate the chance to perform the quest. Attacking/murdering Goldander may result in other future consequences.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new \"Smarter Mage\" script to Goldanader, and may assign a Conjurer Kit (randomly determined at mod installation). If attacked, he'll attempt to fight back, potentially surviving long enough to launch a series of \"previously cast\" protective buffs. However, it is still likely that a determined party will put the gnome down quickly, if they are bent on murder."}
