{"id": "5054", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5054", "title": "Goodberry", "text": "Goodberry is a 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; that permanently creates 5 &lt;a href=\"Good%20Berry\"&gt;Good Berry&lt;/a&gt; items.\nIt counts as an Evocation spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell and is now a 1st level spell - also revising its effects, school, duration and description. See below:\nGoodberry\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Alteration\nSphere: Plant\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nCasting a Goodberry spell creates 5 magical berries that the caster can carry with him or give to others. These berries initially cure 1 point of physical damage for each one eaten. For every three levels of experience, the berries heal one additional point of damage (to a maximum of 7 points at level 18). The berries last for 8 hours, or until eaten.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, Goodberries should not play the *gulp* string when used as they are not potions. This is identified and corrected in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;. Ref: (gberry.itm)"}
