{"id": "44969", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44969", "title": "Gorf the Squisher", "text": "Gorf the Squisher is an &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt; who will insult &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt; if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; walks near him in the vicinity of the side door (left of the front door) outside of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt; district during the \"\" campaign.\nHe will hit a bystander and Mazzy will &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20has%20challenged%20Gorf%20the%20Squisher\"&gt;challenge him to a duel&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; fighting pits.\nEnter the Copper Coronet and talk to &lt;a href=\"Bunkin\"&gt;Bunkin&lt;/a&gt; to let Mazzy and Gorf fight in the pit. The party can persuade Bunkin to let Gorf drink &lt;a href=\"Festule%20the%20Alchemist%27s%20Potion\"&gt;Festule the Alchemist's Potion&lt;/a&gt; before the fight. The party may buy the potion from &lt;a href=\"Festule%20the%20Alchemist\"&gt;Festule the Alchemist&lt;/a&gt; before talking to Bunkin, which results in more experience points being awarded. However Mazzy might be able to defeat Gorf without any aid, whatsoever.\nEffects of the Potion.\nGorf, while drugged, has the following modifications to his statistics and abilities, resulting in his Experience Value being reduced from 2,500 to :\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Gorf slightly. The mod rectifies the error of the unmodded game weapon proficiency assignment of \"Spiked Weapons\" but giving Gorf a \"Blunt Weapon\", thus getting no proficiency (actually a -1 to hit penalty). SCS provides the normal and drugged Gorf with at least 3 Pips in Club weapon proficiency and 2 points in single weapon fighting style. This will of course boost THACO, armor class, APR and damage.\nAn SCS Fighter AI default script is also assigned for smarter tactical behavior in combat.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod has an optional component to ensure certain Giant Humanoids are affected by the \"Shorty\" THACO adjustment in the D&amp;D ruleset. Gorf has a penalty to hit dwarves, gnomes and halflings, reference &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 177 (RR#GRNT and RR#DWRT)."}
{"id": "9265", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9265", "title": "Gorgon Plate", "text": "Gorgon Plate +4 is plate mail +4 which offers an &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of -1. It also offers the wearer 15% fire and acid protection and weighs 30 lbs.\nBesides the aforementioned elemental resistances, this armor is noteworthy for its uniquely powerful AC modifier against slashing damage, providing the best protection against it with a single piece of armor, at a value of -6 (which is added over the general -1 AC resulting in the -7 shown in the description). For comparison, unenchanted plate mails and regular plate mails +1/+2/etc. have an AC modifier vs. slashing damage of -3 and full plate mails have, at best, a modifier of -4."}
