{"id": "38895", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38895", "title": "Gorje Hilldark", "text": "Gorje Hilldark is the non-canonical brother of &lt;a href=\"Unger%20Hilldark\"&gt;Unger Hilldark&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Duergar\"&gt;Duergar&lt;/a&gt; ore merchant who operates in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. He is part of the family business, specializing in acquiring &lt;a href=\"Illithium%20Ore\"&gt;Illithium Ore&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; for sale to merchants in the surface lands above.\nHe can be spawned at the player's location by using the console cheat (control + space bar to bring up the console): CLUAConsole:CreateCreature(\"GORJE\"), or in the EE edition it is C:CreateCreature(\"GORJE\"). \nQuests.\nIf added to the game, Gorje is an extra component called the \"Extended Illithium Quest\" that adds content to &lt;a href=\"Gain%20the%20services%20of%20Sir%20Sarles%20for%20the%20temple\"&gt;Gain the services of Sir Sarles for the temple&lt;/a&gt;; his brother &lt;a href=\"Unger%20Hilldark\"&gt;Unger Hilldark&lt;/a&gt; will not provide &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; with the location of the &lt;a href=\"Illithium%20Ore\"&gt;Illithium Ore&lt;/a&gt;, and instead tell them that they must rescue his missing brother instead.\nLocation.\nGorje has been captured by the &lt;a href=\"shadow\"&gt;shadow&lt;/a&gt;s occupying the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in the prison cell next to that of &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt;. In more recent revisions to the Mod (2018), if your party has already completed the Ruined Temple questline, then he will be in a corridor of the Ruined Temple. next to the impenetrable shadow wall and will claim that some \"beastie\" prevents his escape.\nOrigin Mod.\nGorje is added to the game by using the mod &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt;."}
