{"id": "49306", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49306", "title": "Gracien", "text": "Gracien is one of three mages who have been hired by &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Ployer\"&gt;Baron Ployer&lt;/a&gt; to curse &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt;, which begins one of her &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quests\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. The other two mages are &lt;a href=\"Terrece\"&gt;Terrece&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Malacazar\"&gt;Malacazar&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nIf the party should face this mage due to hostilities breaking out, then this wizard will engage in immediate spell casting attempts.\nMost probably he will be able to use &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; to turn improved invisible at the outset of battle. From there he'll further self-protect with &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;. As seen in his memorized spells in the InfoBox, his offensive damage and disabling spells are all scripted for use. Expect a &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Silence\"&gt;Power Word, Silence&lt;/a&gt; cast if he can detect either another mage or cleric party member. \nMost likely, unless disrupted - a &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Hold Person (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt; will be cast. As a conjurer, its also possible a &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning%20III\"&gt;Monster Summoning III&lt;/a&gt; spell may be attempted to bring forth some temporary help.\nThe sooner the mage is damaged and disrupted, the quicker he will be put out of action.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this wizard, and especially with the \"Smarter Mages\" component. He may be assigned an Enchanter specialty mage kit.\nWhen hostilities commence, Gracien is scripted to self-protect with an &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spell immediately, and a second later a group of protective buffs (previously cast) will initiate upon self. These spells include &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Armor (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith the more advanced AI scripts, the creature's actions will be determined by the party's protections and detected vulnerabilities. A whole slew of offensive and disabling spells are available to the wizard, many that aren't provided to the unmodified wizard. His spell choices are commensurate with his kit and experience level.\nGracien has a prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; loaded and can unleash it during the battle.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, this mage's spells will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "45615", "revid": "267218", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45615", "title": "Grae", "text": "Grae is a &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; shaman to whom &lt;a href=\"Roger%20the%20Fence\"&gt;Roger&lt;/a&gt; sold &lt;a href=\"Dennis%27s%20Mother%27s%20Gong\"&gt;Dennis's Mother's Gong&lt;/a&gt;. Grae can be encountered after receiving information from Roger. Find the shaman in the &lt;a href=\"Druid%20Grove\"&gt;Druid Grove&lt;/a&gt; area near the &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Mound\"&gt;Troll Mound&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen the party is close enough, Grae initiates dialogue. Regardless of initial conversation options, she becomes hostile. In the early battle stages the troll can't be killed (to prevent a plot foul up in the script).\nWhen sufficient damage is done to her, the troll pleads for mercy and provides information that an Ogre Mage named &lt;a href=\"Drush\"&gt;Drush&lt;/a&gt; is in possession of the gong. Drush is known to inhabit the &lt;a href=\"Ogre%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Ogre's Tower&lt;/a&gt; further on in the grove area.\nThe party can let the shaman flee or attempt to slay her. The special amulet she wears will be destroyed with a dialogue selection choice, rendering the creature killable."}
