{"id": "46521", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46521", "title": "Greater Earth Elemental", "text": "The Greater Earth Elemental is encountered in limited scenarios and areas in , the and the Enhanced Editions.\nThe title Greater Earth Elemental usually means that they have 16 to 24 Hit Dice. Ordinary Earth Elementals typically have 8 to 12 Hit Dice, and Lesser Earth Elementals will be 8 or less.\nThe game files are inconsistent in assigning names that differentiate between elementals - the default is typically just \"&lt;Air. Earth, Fire&gt;\" Elemental. However, there are some that are labelled correctly as Lesser or Greater. \nGameplay.\nOne of these elementals will appear as a guardian of the &lt;a href=\"Portals%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;Earth portal&lt;/a&gt; when the party participates in the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;A Mage's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; questline in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere's a 2% chance that (an aggressive) one of these might spawn when casting &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt;.\nThree of these creatures' spawn from the Globe Machine in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; the third time the green button is activated.\nTwo of them are found with the evil elemental prince of earth, &lt;a href=\"Ogremoch\"&gt;Ogremoch&lt;/a&gt; - in &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the unmodified game the creature is simply scripted using the basic WDASIGHT.bcs AI - which allows detected enemies to be pursued and attacked in melee combat.\nSee also.\n&lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Lesser Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Earth%20Elemental%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Conjure Earth Elemental (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Earth%20Elemental%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Conjure Earth Elemental (priest)&lt;/a&gt;\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes minor changes to the Greater Earth Elemental. All receive specific additional immunities to &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Webbed\"&gt;Webbed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; effects, as well as spells that inflict those status effects. They are also immune to &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Greater Earth Elemental encountered at the Earth Portal as part of &lt;a href=\"Vithal\"&gt;Vithal's&lt;/a&gt; quest is unique as it summons three other &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; allies instantaneously and can innately cast &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt; during the battle.\nIf using the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod enemy and party casters that use the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Conjure Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; spell and are level 15 and above will summon this creature, stats below:\nGreater Earth Elemental (16 Hit Dice):\nSTR 23, DEX 8, CON 21, INT 6, WIS 11, CHA 11; AL Neutral\nHP 152, AC 2, THAC0 0, Saving Throws 4/6/5/4/7\n2 Attacks Per Round, 2d10+14 Crushing Damage (Fist +3)\nSpecial Qualities (12 &amp; 16 Hit Dice):\nImmune to normal weapons\nImmune to hold, poison, polymorph, sleep, &amp; stun effects\nSlashing, Piercing, &amp; Missile Resistance 40%"}
{"id": "4771", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4771", "title": "Greater Elemental Summoning", "text": "Greater Elemental Summoning summons one of three Elemental Princes:\nKnowing the &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Summoning\"&gt;Elemental Summoning&lt;/a&gt; spell is a prerequisite of Greater Elemental Summoning. This &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; is available to Druid classes.\nGameplay.\nAlthough the Elemental Princes can dispel magic on-hit, the dispel effect only casts at level 10, meaning that the dispelling effect is only moderately effective, akin to that of a 10th level mage.\nEach Prince provides effective utility via their melee combat capabilities, immunities and, most notably, their special fast-casting innate abilities:\nFurthermore, they're all immune to weapons with enchantments of +2 and lower, have high magic resistance and can detect invisible creatures in visual range (and will attack them even if the player themselves can't see them).\nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a way that's different than most summoning spells, in that summoned elemental princes are treated as 'gated\" and do not add to the total towards the summoning cap (though you can't cast this spell again if you already have an elemental prince on the field). However, the spell still respects the summoning cap.\nWhat this means is that, if you summon an elemental prince before reaching the summoning cap of 5 creatures, you can then summon more regular creatures up to a total of 5 + 1 elemental prince.\nKeep in mind that a few other gated creatures behave similarly, in that they also do not count towards the summoning cap, such as &lt;a href=\"Deva\"&gt;Deva&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;, so technically it's possible to have even more if you conjure them in the correct order.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod replaces \"Greater Elemental Summoning\" with \"Elemental Prince Call\". See below for description:\nElemental Prince Call\nLevel: Quest\nSchool: Conjuration\nSphere: Elemental, Summoning\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 2 rounds\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nDruids, having a more powerful link to the elements, can cast a more specialized version of Elemental Swarm. This spell can summon one of the Elemental Princes themselves, randomly chosen from the Planes of Earth, Air, and Fire. The Elemental Prince will stay for 10 rounds and obey the caster as long as they remain summoned. The Elemental Princes rule over other elementals in their respective planes. The Elemental Prince of Air is Chan. The Elemental Prince of Earth is Sunnis. The Elemental Prince of Fire is Zaaman Rul.\nChan, Prince of Air (20 Hit Dice):\nSTR 19, DEX 24, CON 18, INT 17, WIS 16, CHA 18; AL Neutral\nHP 160, AC -8, THAC0 -3, Saving Throws 3/5/4/4/6\n4 Attacks Per Round, 1d12+11 Piercing Damage (Fist +4)\nSpecial Qualities:\nBlade Barrier (permanent)\nImmune to weapons lower than +2 enchantment\nImmune to hold, poison, polymorph, sleep, &amp; stun effects\nElectrical Resistance 100%; Magic Resistance 60%\nSlashing, Crushing, &amp; Piercing Resistance 20%; Missile Resistance 60%\nSunnis, Princess of Earth (20 Hit Dice):\nSTR 24, DEX 12, CON 21, INT 17, WIS 16, CHA 18; AL Neutral\nHP 190, AC -5, THAC0 -6, Saving Throws 3/5/4/4/6\n3 Attacks Per Round, 2d12+16 Crushing Damage (Fist +4)\nSpecial Qualities:\nStoneskin (1 skin each round)\nImmune to weapons lower than +2 enchantment\nImmune to hold, poison, polymorph, sleep, &amp; stun effects\nAcid Resistance 100%; Magic Resistance 60%\nSlashing, Piercing, &amp; Missile Resistance 40%\nZaaman Rul, Prince of Fire (20 Hit Dice):\nSTR 19, DEX 21, CON 19, INT 17, WIS 16, CHA 18; AL Neutral\nHP 170, AC -7, THAC0 -3, Saving Throws 3/5/4/4/6\n3 Attacks Per Round, 2d10+11 Slashing +2d10 Fire Damage (Fist +4)\nSpecial Qualities:\nFire Shield (permanent)\nImmune to weapons lower than +2 enchantment\nImmune to hold, poison, polymorph, sleep, &amp; stun effects\nFire Resistance 125%; Magic Resistance 60%\nSlashing, Crushing, Piercing, &amp; Missile Resistance 20%"}
{"id": "9374", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9374", "title": "Greater Evasion", "text": "Greater Evasion is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieve&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s.\nPrerequisite: &lt;a href=\"Evasion\"&gt;Evasion&lt;/a&gt;\nEffects.\nIt doesn't quite protect against \"normal missiles\", the exact list of affected projectiles can be read in the &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles%23Affected%20items\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt; article.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a change to the Rogue's HLA's:\nDanger Sense (replaces Greater Evasion)\nBy studying his surroundings intently, an experienced Thief can predict the actions of his opponents through cunning insight and extraordinary perception. Any potentially hostile actions are perceived in advance, giving the Thief enough time to react appropriately. This uncanny sense for impending danger almost borders on precognition and grants the Thief a +5 bonus to his armor class and all saving throws for 5 rounds after this ability is activated. Furthermore, as the Thief cannot be surprised nor caught off guard while using this ability, he is not susceptible to backstab attacks until the duration expires."}
{"id": "52607", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52607", "title": "Greater Feyr", "text": "Greater Feyr is a in \"\".\nEncounters.\nA Greater Feyr may appear during the &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt; quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Fear\"&gt;The Fear&lt;/a&gt;.\nCombat.\nGreater Feyrs attack 4 times at &lt;a href=\"Speed%20Factor\"&gt;speed&lt;/a&gt; 2 for 2d6 &lt;a href=\"crushing%20damage\"&gt;crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; and have an enchantment equivalent of +2. On hit, their attacks will &lt;a href=\"panic\"&gt;panic&lt;/a&gt; the target for 60 seconds, which is not subject to &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance\"&gt;Magic Resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe creature will begin by triggering an &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; effect and refresh if expired or dispelled. It can also use and &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey are immune to the spell Emotion: Hopelessness."}
{"id": "40603", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40603", "title": "Greater Fire Elemental", "text": ""}
{"id": "40544", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40544", "title": "Greater Fire Elemental (Watcher's Keep)", "text": "This page deals with the Greater Fire Elementals found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;. For other versions, refer to .\nGameplay.\nVersions.\nA Greater Fire Elemental is spawned from the lava pool in the Fire laboratory/chamber when a player character is inside the room. Only one elemental is spawned at a time. There are actually four different elementals spawned by the lava pool (GORFIR01-04). \nA Greater Fire Elemental is summoned by a the &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28TELTAN1%29\"&gt;Glabrezu (TELTAN1)&lt;/a&gt; creature in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Obelisk%20%28AR3010%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep - Obelisk (AR3010)&lt;/a&gt; area. Up to five of these elementals can be present on the map at one time.\nElemental Level version.\nThe elemental spawns nearby the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Giant%20%28Guardian%20of%20Fire%29\"&gt;Fire Giant (Guardian of Fire)&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe elemental will immediately move towards any detected enemy and attempt to engage in melee combat, fighting to the death. It will chase after a party member, until it loses sight of them, and then return to the Fire Laboratory.\nThe elemental is worth no experience if killed or banished. If the creature is killed, it will be reborn again and can respawn from the lava pool.\nThe only way to actually slay this elemental is to follow the procedures detailed on the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Library%20Note\"&gt;Ice Library Note&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the elemental is slain in the \"correct\" way, it awards to share with party members.\nFor further information, see the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Walkthrough on this page&lt;/a&gt;.\nTeleport Maze version.\nThe Greater Fire Elemental (TELELFIR) is summoned by the red colored Glabrezu in the Obelisk room in the Teleport Maze. The demon prioritizes summoning these elementals over all other actions, although it will retreat if threatened by melee attackers, and move away from that danger as far as it can go inside the confines of the room.\nUp to five Greater Elementals can be created and be on the map at the same time, and the demon will then cease summoning more and cast other spells at that time. Once a summoned Greater Fire elemental is destroyed, the demon will then attempt to summon another to replace it. This goes on as longs as the demon is functional. The demon can summon one demon per round, and damaging the demon doesn't disrupt this innate spell.\nThe Greater Fire elemental is a summoned creature and can be banished by a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;, but unlike some other summoned elementals, this one provides 10,000 experience points when slain.\nThe fiery foe will attack in melee combat, going for the nearest enemy it can detect."}
{"id": "51969", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51969", "title": "Greater Ghast", "text": "The Greater Ghast is another variety of the &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; brood of &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghast&lt;/a&gt; found in the game, although only in and . The creature is an ally of the summoner who brought forth the creature.\nGameplay.\nThis creature is slightly enhanced with some elemental and missile resistance. Like it's brethren, they can't take much punishment and will be destroyed rapidly by damage.\nAs with other ghast creatures, a successful attack will expose the target to a potential disabling &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt; status effect, although a saving throw negates. But, even if that effect is defended against, a second nauseating disease effect must be saved against as well. See the &lt;a href=\"GHAST1.ITM\"&gt;GHAST1.ITM&lt;/a&gt; page for details.\nLike most undead, they are immune to a number of status effects as summarized in the InfoBox.\nThis creature is a \"Summoned\" one and can be destroyed with a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt; or similar banishment magics."}
{"id": "16659", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16659", "title": "Greater Ghoul", "text": "Greater Ghouls are a stronger variant of the common &lt;a href=\"Ghoul\"&gt;Ghoul&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAside from all-around higher stats, Greater Ghouls are also permanently hasted which makes up for the slow speed that is one of the greatest weaknesses of their regular cousins \u2013 though it should be noted that even a hasted Ghoul only moves as fast as a regular &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;. Just like normal Ghouls, they attack with both claws and bite, which can immobilize the target on hit. They also possess the ability to inflict a debilitating disease with their attacks, just like &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghast&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "35595", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35595", "title": "Greater Lacedon", "text": "Greater Lacedons are more powerful &lt;a href=\"lacedon\"&gt;lacedon&lt;/a&gt;s; aquatic &lt;a href=\"ghasts\"&gt;ghasts&lt;/a&gt; found only in rivers, lakes or ocean environments.\nGameplay.\nA greater lacedon's touch deals 1d8+2 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing&lt;/a&gt; damage (including &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus) with a range of one foot and &lt;a href=\"Speed%20Factor\"&gt;speed&lt;/a&gt; of three.\nAdditionally, two &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saves vs. death&lt;/a&gt; must be made to negate its other effects:\nJust like &lt;a href=\"ghasts\"&gt;ghasts&lt;/a&gt;, greater lacedons prefer to attack &lt;a href=\"wizards\"&gt;wizards&lt;/a&gt;.\nExternal Links.\n[[Category:Immune to poison]]"}
{"id": "4865", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4865", "title": "Greater Malison", "text": "Greater Malison afflicts all enemies in its area of effect with a penalty to all their &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; values.\nGameplay.\nThe caster directs this spell at a designated targeting point location on a part of map - use the targeting cursor to select the desired point.\nWhen the spell casting is finished a projectile travels rapidly to the target point and then expands a sparkling effect to all enemy creatures in a 15-feet radius area of effect.\nAny enemy creature affected will display a combat log text reading \"Saving Throws Lowered\", a 3D effect, and a fade from color graphic renders over the creature's sprite.\nA party member affected by this spell will display an icon (No. 45) titled \"Greater Malison\" on their portrait, for as long as the spell is active.\nWhen the malison expires, a sound effect is audibled.\nCreatures affected by this spell are afflicted with a -4 penalty to all saving throw values (Death/Poison, Wands, Petrification/Polymorph, Breath Weapons, and Spells modifiers).\nThis spell can be negated by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and blocked by a &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; - likewise, a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt; will protect against the spell.\nThe spell's effects can be removed with various &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects.\nThis spell does not \"stack\" with itself but can be used in conjunction with a spell such as &lt;a href=\"Doom\"&gt;Doom&lt;/a&gt; for greater saving throw penalties.\nIn the classic games, affected creatures are immune to the same spell, enhanced editions change the behavior so that the next identical spell first removes the affected source then implements its own effects, this way, the effects such as duration will be \"refreshed\". This applies to most spells.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset's version of \"Greater Malison\" differs in several ways from the spell design implemented by Bioware. See the external links below.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects. See below for description:\nGreater Malison\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: 2 rounds/level\nCasting Time: 4\nArea of Effect: 15\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nThe spell allows the caster to adversely affect the saving throws of his enemies. The effect is applied to all hostile creatures within the area of effect. Those under the influence of this spell make all their saving throws at a penalty of -2 and take an extra point of spell damage for each die rolled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod Smarter Mage component regularly empowers arcane casters to attempt the Greater Malison spell before other spells are cast, similarly to what a smart player would do."}
