{"id": "55308", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55308", "title": "Greed (Abyss)", "text": "Greed (Abyss) is a sub map area and connected to &lt;a href=\"The%20Abyss\"&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt; area map.\nIt is reachable during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;, Part 2. A descending staircase on the main Abyss area map transitions to this \"Test of Greed\" area.\nGameplay.\nFor description of what occurs when visiting this area, see the &lt;a href=\"Finding%20Irenicus%20in%20Hell\"&gt;Finding Irenicus in Hell&lt;/a&gt; article and the Test of Greed section.\nOnce this area is entered, it may not be exited without the specific Tear of Bhaal from the test."}
{"id": "55316", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55316", "title": "Greed (Fiend)", "text": "Greed (Fiend) is present when the party descends stairs leading below to the &lt;a href=\"Greed%20%28Abyss%29\"&gt;Greed (Abyss)&lt;/a&gt; area during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;, part 2.\nGameplay.\nThe Greed Fiend will initiate and administer the \"Test of Greed\". The player's bhaalspawn PC will be presented dialogue choices to navigate the test, which will determine if the final choices made will be determined as either the \"good\" or \"evil\" path. Some of these will be presented by the &lt;a href=\"Enslaved%20Genie\"&gt;Enslaved Genie&lt;/a&gt; who is also in this area.\nThe player's goal in all of the various tests is to obtain one of the &lt;a href=\"Tears%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Tears of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; - which are required to complete the &lt;a href=\"Finding%20Irenicus%20in%20Hell\"&gt;Finding Irenicus in Hell&lt;/a&gt; questline, and eventually lead to unsealing \"The Abyssal Door\" (also referred to as the \"Watcher's Door\").\nThose dialogue choices during the test determine what reward is assigned to the protagonist when a Tear of Bhaal is added to the door. It may also result in an alignment shift.\nThis fiend is not meant to be attacked, provides no experience points or dropped treasure, and can't be killed by the party (it is equipped with the &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt; protective item). The fiend is simply a plot actor to present the specific Tears of Bhaal test involving fear."}
{"id": "56413", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56413", "title": "Green Dragon Breath", "text": "Green Dragon Breath is an innate ability available to green dragons in the game saga, such as the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20%28Watchers%20Keep%20Final%20Seal%29\"&gt;Dragon (Watchers Keep Final Seal)&lt;/a&gt;. This innate ability is initiated via internal creature scripting during combat. \nThe purpose of the spell is to apply &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; to a single creature as well as an Area of Effect around the target.\nEffects.\nThe ability is uninterruptible and takes almost no time to deploy. The scripted targeting will fire over a single target creature, which is typically within the creature's sight detection range. All creatures in the area of effect are subject to the effects. This breath weapon is a projectile that will burst (similar to a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;) and spread in a ring of greenish colored poison toxicity. \nWhen a dragon deploys a Green Dragon Breath, a blast explodes upon the target and creatures within the AoE who are then subjected to 24d6 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;. \nA quick reaction &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs Breath Attack will apply, and a successful save will reduce the damage by half. Perhaps the victim was able to dive aside, roll away from the burst, or raise a shield up to deflect some of the poison spray and mist.\nWhen a party member is affected by the poison, their portrait will briefly display an icon (No. 6) \"Poisoned\", lasting only 2 seconds.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mods have removed the \"secondary type\" classification of \"Offensive damage\" and made it \"None\". This means that the Cloak of Mirroring won't interact with it."}
{"id": "51376", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51376", "title": "Green Dragon Potion", "text": "Although this potion provides one major benefit (it sets the user's &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to 25 for 24 hours), it comes with a few major negative effects as well (&lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; set to 3 and slowness). Noteworthy, however, is the fact that (unlike other strength-enhancing potions, such as &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Cloud%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potions of Cloud Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;) this potion's effects are considered nonmagical and, therefore, cannot be dispelled.\nThese negative effects can, however, be counteracted in some ways. For example: equipping &lt;a href=\"Edventar%27s%20Gift\"&gt;Edventar's Gift&lt;/a&gt; before imbibing will prevent the slow effect altogether (one can even unequip the ring afterward) and level 5+ Monks are simply immune to slow. As for the Constitution loss, the &lt;a href=\"Girdle%20of%20Fortitude\"&gt;Girdle of Fortitude&lt;/a&gt; allows a character to raise it to 18 after this potion lowers it (and, once again, the girdle can be unequipped after it's used).\nIn , five of them can be acquired via the &lt;a href=\"Where%27s%20Wilson%3F\"&gt;Where's Wilson?&lt;/a&gt; quest."}
