{"id": "30116", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30116", "title": "Green Globe", "text": "Colored globes are produced by interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Globe%20Machine\"&gt;Globe Machine&lt;/a&gt;, located on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon level.\nSelect which globe color is desired in the dialogue box presented by the machine. The machine can produce red, blue, green and purple globes, and a limit of four of each color. \nWhen the button is pressed to select a globe, the dialogue box displays a text, reading:\nGreen globes - gameplay.\nAll four green globes look identical, except three of them will have a numeric \"1\" displayed on them, indicating a use \"charge\". This means that particular globe is a consumable/usable item.\nAs there isn't any information about what the globes do, the party would need to experiment and see the results. This feature is avoided by the wiki filling in that information.\nEven so, it may prove difficult to remember which globe does what, especially later in the adventure when managing an inventory. It will be up to the player to come up with some kind of tracking method."}
{"id": "11163", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11163", "title": "Green Slime", "text": "Green Slime is one of the most common forms of &lt;a href=\"Slimes\"&gt;slime&lt;/a&gt; encountered. A green slime attack has the ability to poison or infect its target upon a successful hit.\nIn both BGEE and BG2EE, a green slime can only engage in melee, with an unenchanted attack that exposes the target to two effects on a failed saving throw vs. Death/Poison (with a +4 bonus): a poison that inflicts 2 poison damage per round for 8 seconds and a delayed &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; effect that may kill the target after 10 seconds. Both effects are nonmagical and, therefore, cannot be dispelled via &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;. Immunity to kill target effects can prevent that effect from taking place even on a failed save, but poison immunity prevents both effects (poison + kill target) at once. \n In the original game, the poison simply does 4 points of damage over 8 seconds and then kills the target after two more seconds. Both of these effects can be avoided with a save vs. death with a +4 bonus. Curing the poison will not prevent the delayed death, and it cannot be dispelled, but spells like &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt; can protect from it.\nGame play.\nThe Green Slimes encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; are tougher than the typical Green Slime creature. They have many more resistances to physical and elemental damages. You will find your axes, clubs and swords doing very little damage, and acids having no effect. Even fire and cold damage will be resisted to a high extent. See the &lt;a href=\"Green%20Slime%20%28WK%20Elemental%20level%29\"&gt;Green Slime (WK Elemental level)&lt;/a&gt; page for more details."}
{"id": "55704", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55704", "title": "Green Slime (WK Elemental level)", "text": "The Green Slime encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; is a different more robust version of the ordinary &lt;a href=\"Green%20Slime\"&gt;Green Slime&lt;/a&gt; found elsewhere in the game saga. \nGameplay.\nThis creature is exceptional because it is a mutated and bio-engineered by the \"Slime laboratory\" area of the keep, where potent poisons, powerful corrosives, and foul and putrid chemicals were the specialty of the former arch mage who developed it.\nSeveral of these slimes appear in the hazardous Slime laboratory in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;, alongside some other rank creatures, and the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Snake%20%28Guardian%20of%20Slime%29\"&gt;Guardian of Slime&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn reality, these slimes probably can't strike anything without rolling a critical hit. their jelly forms can get electrocuted easily with even a low-level lightning bolt.\nTheir main characteristic is the ability to hang around and shrug off many damages other creatures are harmed by. In large groups they can be a real annoyance. Should an unlucky adventurer be struck by one these, and them miss their saving throw, it could be the final thing they see while still breathing."}
