{"id": "29987", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29987", "title": "Guard (Helm and Cloak)", "text": "Two Guards are found standing near the stairs on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20and%20Cloak\"&gt;Helm and Cloak&lt;/a&gt; inn. They are there to protect the &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;ian emissary &lt;a href=\"Sarah\"&gt;Sarah&lt;/a&gt; from unwanted visitors. Speaking to either of them three times will trigger hostilities. Killing them does not harm your reputation."}
{"id": "29988", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29988", "title": "Guard (Iron Throne)", "text": "There are four \"types\" of Guards (based on their armour and weapons) who are employed by the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt;. They are found throughout the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; area and inside the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt;. Below is a complete breakdown of each type of guard encountered in both areas.\nLight guards.\n&lt;br&gt;\nThe light guards in service to the Iron Throne are easily recognizable, as they, in almost every encounter, will first talk and only then \u2013 perhaps \u2013 fight. They are equipped with &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nSwordsmen.\nThese guards are better trained swordsman than the Iron Throne's light guards. They're better equipped since they wear &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt; and have a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shield\"&gt;Medium Shield&lt;/a&gt; for defensive protection, and they don't talk very much.\nBowmen.\nThese rarely encountered characters are perhaps the most dangerous of the various Iron Throne guards. Their experience levels are the same as the swordsmen and they are wielding &lt;a href=\"Longbow\"&gt;Longbow&lt;/a&gt;s with deadly &lt;a href=\"arrows%20of%20biting\"&gt;arrows of biting&lt;/a&gt;. They also possess the same limited dialogue as the swordsmen.\nHeavy guards.\nThis elite guard protects one very special person: the master of the Cloakwood Mines operations, and this fellow does not allow anybody to visit &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; without getting past him first.\nThe deeper the mines, the heavier armored the guards \u2014 this guy is equipped with &lt;a href=\"Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt;, carries a &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield\"&gt;Large Shield&lt;/a&gt;, and has a &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; of 18/52, a &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; of 17 and sports 48 &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;. All dialogue with him ends in hostilities.\nDialogue.\n\"The bunch of you better have a good reason for being here.\""}
{"id": "29990", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29990", "title": "Guard (Merchants' League Estate)", "text": "Two guards are stationed near the front door on the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Estate\"&gt;Merchants' League Estate&lt;/a&gt;'s main floor in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The guards may or may not support &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party during the &lt;a href=\"Investigating%20the%20Merchants%27%20League%20Estate\"&gt;investigation&lt;/a&gt; they agreed to perform for &lt;a href=\"Aldeth%20Sashenstar\"&gt;Aldeth Sashenstar&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "41719", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41719", "title": "Guard (Saerk's House)", "text": "Saerk's House Guards at the &lt;a href=\"Estate%20of%20Saerk%20Farrahd\"&gt;Estate of Saerk Farrahd&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; come in four flavors, but they all have the same intention: protect &lt;a href=\"Saerk%20Farrahd\"&gt;Saerk Farrahd&lt;/a&gt; and his possessions.\nThere are three archer type and one melee variety with Plate mail, an enchanted bastard sword and large Kite shield. The latter is most probably the Estate Guard Captain. All are non-kit fighters of experience levels 4 to 6.\nOn the first floor (ground floor) the one greeting the party as they enter is the guard 1 version, accompanied by three of the Guard 3 variety.\nOn the second floor you are greeted by Guard 2 and the \"welcoming committee\" is joined by two of Guard 3 and four of Guard 4.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the guards in this estate with default SCS Fighter AI for smarter tactical behavior. All assigned weapon proficiencies and weapon fighting styles are updated to reflect the creature's experience level and class."}
{"id": "29986", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29986", "title": "Guard (Undercellar)", "text": "One of the five guards in the &lt;a href=\"Undercellar\"&gt;Undercellar&lt;/a&gt; that's located beneath the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; will demand payment from the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; for entrance to the area. He's located near the entrance/exit to the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt;. The other four guards are near the entrance/exit to the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20Sewers%20East\"&gt;eastern sewers&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "29995", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29995", "title": "Guard (Vampire)", "text": "This &lt;a href=\"Vampires\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; guard will shortly greet &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; before turning hostile while the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;'s looking for a solution to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;regain&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;'s soul in the &lt;a href=\"lower%20tombs\"&gt;lower tombs&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. This Guardian vampire is part of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt; and found only in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis vampire is down the corridor that leads to the \"Room of Blood and Blades\" (it doesn't have a map name or its own Area number in the game files).\nThe guard is similar to a &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;Fledgling Vampire&lt;/a&gt; in durability, but is assigned a level 14 Mage script, and essentially functions as a spell caster. The vampire can be struck with normal weapons, and its melee attack can drain 3 experience levels. The creature will open hostilities with a protective buff contingency, and periodically reapply others as scripted. Offensive spell casts will be attempted, if able, as long as the vampire can identify a target, and complete a spell cast. Examples include &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Power Word, Stun&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Malison\"&gt;Greater Malison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt; and others.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod with the \"Improved Vampires\" component revises this creature. See the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article and the \"Mod content\" section for a discussion of the mod's revisions to vampires (including this one) in the game.&lt;br&gt;\nThe vampire guard is now a level 14/14 Fighter/Mage class, 165 HP, STR 22, DEX 21, CON 20. He has 4 attacks per round, THAC0 0 and -4 Armor Class. His melee strike drains 3 experience levels or 3 CON. The creature utilizes a default SCS \"Smarter Mage\" script rather than the \"Improved Vampire\" one. As such, the guard will behave as a spell caster, but still be able to fight in melee as a vampire effectively as well. At least +3 or better enchanted weapons are needed to strike the vampire, and it regenerates at 1 HP/second. \nUpon initial hostilities, the vampire will self-buff (Cast Previously) with uninterruptible instant cast spells such as &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. The creature has a mostly different set of memorized spells, and all of them are scripted for use as determined by opponent threat assessments, their protections, and what spells are still available as the vampire uses them up. The creature can cast &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; to take down the party's protections and has a number of offensive damage dealing spells as well as disabling type as well. If the vampire cannot find a spell applicable to the target, it can engage in melee attack."}
