{"id": "47642", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47642", "title": "Guild Contact", "text": "The Guild Contact, who is also referred to by the name \"Gracen\", is the individual from the &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;rival guild&lt;/a&gt; that the turncoat &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Caehan\"&gt;Caehan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jaylos\"&gt;Jaylos&lt;/a&gt;, are supposed to meet with on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Flagons%20Inn\"&gt;Five Flagons Inn&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nHe'll either appear after some initial dialogue with the two shadow thieves, in which you can extract the name of the contact from the thieves, or he'll appear after you have killed them, with Caehan blurting out the contact's name before the fight begins.\nOnce the fight with the guild contact has begun, the quest section of your &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; will be updated under the title \"Aran's tasks to receive the Shadow Thieves' aid\":\nThis fighter is not unskilled, and with Plate Mail beneath his robes, and a well-crafted great sword at the ready he can engage in melee. The warrior is not proficient with it however, which tempers his swordsmanship abilities. This warrior will consume potions when scripted to do so for healing purposes.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod corrects the lack of weapon proficiency, and assigns 5 pips in two-handed sword as well as 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style. The warrior will consume a potion at the beginning of hostilities for boosting skills. several more are available to heal wounds at set thresholds of damage."}
