{"id": "4456", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4456", "title": "Gullykin", "text": "Gullykin is an area where the &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; village is located. There is no store, only a temple and winery along with several burrow homes. There are two secret entrances to the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Ruins\"&gt;Firewine Ruins&lt;/a&gt; located in the village, which are shortcuts, of sorts, to the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Bridge\"&gt;Firewine Bridge&lt;/a&gt;.\nAssassination Attempt.\n&lt;a href=\"Drakar\"&gt;Drakar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Halacan\"&gt;Halacan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Molkar\"&gt;Molkar&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Morvin\"&gt;Morvin&lt;/a&gt; are waiting in the southeastern area of the map. The four of them are a formidable group of enemies and two of them are spellcasters.\nBuildings.\nAll of the houses are round, naturally, for halfling burrows; all have the same layout when entered, no matter which side the door is on. They all contain a ground floor and a basement. The ground floors all have three containers: two cupboards, which may be locked or unlocked, and a bookshelf. The bookshelves only ever contain books and scrolls, and books and scrolls are never found in the other containers. The basements all have have two bookcases, a writing desk, a cupboard and a locked chest. A list of treasure is included with each building description. The temple and winery contains no containers.\nTransitions.\nThere are also two entrances in the village to the\u00a0Firewine Ruins:"}
{"id": "42680", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42680", "title": "Gurgle and Floss", "text": "Gurgle and Floss refers to both a pair of NPCs in and to a side quest associated with those NPCs.\nThe NPCs.\nGurgle and his companion Floss are a pair of &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; who can be encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt; area, in a small chamber north of the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; camp at the cavern entrance and just over the river that divides the cavern into its northern and southern halves. The rather dimwitted pair have made a nuisance of themselves by barricading their chamber and threatening any passers-by, which the Crusaders in the supply camp at the cavern's entrance have used as an excuse to stop their work.\nThe Quest.\nIn addition to &lt;a href=\"Ladle\"&gt;Ladle&lt;/a&gt; asking &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to do something about the &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt;, Gurgle and Floss will automatically challenge the player when they attempt to move through their \"territory\" in order to reach the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt; needed to progress this chapter. As such, dealing with them is mandatory.\nThere are several options for gaining passage.\nFirstly, the player can simply fight the two. They are standard &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; warriors and worth 2,000 EXP each.\nSecondly, the player can trick them into leaving, whereupon they will be shot down by the crusader archers waiting outside; this gives no rewards.\nThirdly, the player can intimidate them into allowing passage, which is worth 5,000 EXP.\nFinally, the player can answer their demands for a story. There are several suboptions here:\nRegardless of which story is chosen, the party will be granted the right to freely move through the sahuagin's chamber as they wish."}
