{"id": "7298", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7298", "title": "Gurke's Cloak", "text": "Gurke's Cloak is a side quest which is started inside the &lt;a href=\"Jovial%20Juggler\"&gt;Jovial Juggler&lt;/a&gt; inn, where &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; will find the dwarf &lt;a href=\"Gurke\"&gt;Gurke&lt;/a&gt;. He is rather grumpy, because his &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Non-Detection\"&gt;Cloak of Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt; has been stolen by a &lt;a href=\"Tasloi\"&gt;Tasloi&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Forest\"&gt;Cloakwood Forest&lt;/a&gt; of all places.\nAlthough the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will probably pick up this quest early in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt;, it cannot be completed until the Cloakwood Forest\u00a0areas have\u00a0been unlocked when reaching &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;Chapter Four&lt;/a&gt;. After the cloak has been retrieved, it should be brought back to Gurke in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;, who won't want it anymore and tell you to keep it.\nThe Tasloi with the cloak itself can be found among others of his kind in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Lodge\"&gt;first area&lt;/a&gt; of the Cloakwood Forests, in the bottom right (southeast) corner of the map."}
{"id": "41374", "revid": "261956", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41374", "title": "Gurn Coldhearth", "text": "Gurn Coldhearth is a dwarf priest of Dumathoin, the dwarven god of mining and buried secrets i.a., who has turned his back on his former faith, following the dwarven god of greed Abbathor instead, and betrayed his former comrades-in-arms to pursue immortality by becoming a &lt;a href=\"lich\"&gt;lich&lt;/a&gt;.\nSome time before his transformation, he penned the &lt;a href=\"Journal%20of%20Gurn%20Coldhearth\"&gt;Journal of Gurn Coldhearth&lt;/a&gt;, where it's described one of the Shadow King's liches (&lt;a href=\"Hexxat%27s%20request%23Throne_of_Bhaal\"&gt;Korkorran&lt;/a&gt;) offered Coldhearth lichdom in return for being freeing from the Shadow King's control. Together with his journal &lt;a href=\"Parchment%20%28BDMISC43.itm%29\"&gt;a letter&lt;/a&gt; is found, written to a Karella from Agda Coldhearth, which possibly led Gurn to search for a \"cure\" to his ailment by seeking out the lich. His discarded &lt;a href=\"Cleric%27s%20Vestments\"&gt;vestments&lt;/a&gt; and some &lt;a href=\"Notes%20on%20a%20Failed%20Experiment\"&gt;Notes on a Failed Experiment&lt;/a&gt; can also be found, which mentions his failure in the process of creating a phylactery, which led to several &lt;a href=\"Failed%20Phylactery\"&gt;Failed Phylactery&lt;/a&gt;. Amongst the overflowing bookcases can be found some books and notes, which likely helped in his research; the &lt;a href=\"Mortal%20to%20Lich%20Notes\"&gt;Mortal to Lich Notes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"A%20Philosophical%20Treatise%20on%20the%20Nature%20of%20Lichdom\"&gt;A Philosophical Treatise on the Nature of Lichdom&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Ancient%20Knowledge\"&gt;Tome of Ancient Knowledge&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Volume%20MCXII%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Netherese%20Empire\"&gt;Volume MCXII of the History of the Netherese Empire&lt;/a&gt;.\nAchievements.\nIf one feels inclined to destroy the lich, one needs to throw &lt;a href=\"Coldhearth%20Phylactery\"&gt;his phylactery&lt;/a&gt;, found in a nearby chamber in the &lt;a href=\"Repository%20of%20Undeath\"&gt;Repository of Undeath&lt;/a&gt; unlocked by the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Key\"&gt;Ancient Key&lt;/a&gt;, into a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Plane%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Elemental Plane of Fire&lt;/a&gt; in the western part of the area, south of the entrance. Making the ordeal challenging is that he reforms, to aid in the endeavor &lt;a href=\"Brother%20Deepvein\"&gt;Brother Deepvein&lt;/a&gt; bestowes a magical gemstone &lt;a href=\"The%20Secret%20Revealed%20%28item%29\"&gt;The Secret Revealed&lt;/a&gt;. If one sides with the lich, he requests five &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20the%20Keeper%20of%20Secrets%20Under%20the%20Mountain\"&gt;Amulet of the Keeper of Secrets Under the Mountain&lt;/a&gt; carried by Deepvein and the other &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Cleric\"&gt;priests&lt;/a&gt; (and one dropped from a zombie in the fight with the undead) at the &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Dig%20Site\"&gt;Dwarven Dig Site&lt;/a&gt;. He will then reward his former weapon, the &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Hammer\"&gt;Dread Hammer&lt;/a&gt;."}
