{"id": "51368", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51368", "title": "HGTRL01.ITM", "text": "HGTRL01.ITM is an undroppable weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Troll\"&gt;Fire Troll&lt;/a&gt; creatures and is typically equipped in the first \"Quick weapon\" slot.\nEffects.\nThe weapon is considered a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapon of &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; level 2 and deals 2d6 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of one.\nAdditionally, any successful hit with the item inflicts 2d4 damage as well. This damage bypasses magic resistance and spell level protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;."}
