{"id": "34968", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34968", "title": "Hakeashar", "text": "The Hakeashar is a creature that will only appear when &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hakeashar\"&gt;summoned&lt;/a&gt; by a wizard. It will not attack the wizard who summoned it, but it will instantly move to attack the nearest wizard in its line of sight, as it feeds on the energies surrounding and used by wizards.\nThe creature does not make use of a physical attack. Instead, each time it touches the wizard, wrapping its tendrils around the target, two things will occur:\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, a Nishruu and &lt;a href=\"Hakeashar\"&gt;Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; can be destroyed with three specific spells other than &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;. Both can be slain by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;. Other forms of Dispel magic won't work, such as the &lt;a href=\"Inquisitor\"&gt;Inquisitor&lt;/a&gt; Dispel magic innate ability.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, for all intents and purposes removes the Hakeashar from the game, because it replaces that with its own version of the &lt;a href=\"Nishruu\"&gt;Nishruu&lt;/a&gt;. The spell &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hakeashar\"&gt;Summon Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; is replaced by &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Nishruu\"&gt;Summon Nishruu&lt;/a&gt; (which SR changes and makes a level 7 spell)."}
{"id": "5445", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5445", "title": "Hakt", "text": "Hakt is a unique &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin%20Elite\"&gt;hobgoblin elite&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He is a likely second-in-command of the &lt;a href=\"Chill\"&gt;Chill&lt;/a&gt; mercenary group, and can be found among three other mercenaries - &lt;a href=\"Britik\"&gt;Britik&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Raemon\"&gt;Raemon&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Venkt\"&gt;Venkt&lt;/a&gt; - within &lt;a href=\"Tazok%27s%20Tent\"&gt;Tazok's tent&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt;. They are guarding a captured spy named &lt;a href=\"Ender%20Sai\"&gt;Ender Sai&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs he is a hobgoblin elite, his arrows may poison his target, though he wields no ordinary bow; the unique &lt;a href=\"Longbow%20of%20Marksmanship\"&gt;Longbow of Marksmanship&lt;/a&gt; is yours to take after he is dealt with."}
