{"id": "42235", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42235", "title": "Halatathlaer", "text": "Halatathlaer is the ghost of a female metallic dragon who guards the entrance to the ruined city of &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt; located within the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt; beneath &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;. Her essence was bound against her will inside of a &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Jar\"&gt;Ghost Jar&lt;/a&gt; by the evil necromancer &lt;a href=\"Kherriun\"&gt;Kherriun&lt;/a&gt; and she commands the dragon to do her bidding.\nDestroying the ghost jar will free her spirit from the enslavement and she will come to the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;'s aid during the confrontation with Kherriun and her &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Magician\"&gt;Dark Magician&lt;/a&gt; minions. After the battle is over, she will give her thanks and some sage words of wisdom before she enters the waters of the Nepenthe and travels to the Fugue Plane:\nIf you have found and entered one of two caves located within the Underground River area that contains several &lt;a href=\"Blind%20Albino%20Wyrmling\"&gt;Blind Albino Wyrmling&lt;/a&gt;s and have killed them, Halatathlaer will thank you for being merciful in ending their wretched existence.\nHer long-lost eggs were captured by the necromancer Ithtaerus long ago and the resulting hatchlings have been corrupted into the twisted beasts that attacked the party in the cave."}
{"id": "3341", "revid": "26182140", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3341", "title": "Halbazzer Drin", "text": "Halbazzar Drin is the owner and proprietor of &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He sells many magical items such as scrolls, wands, and ammunition, many of which aren't sold elsewhere. He also buys the &lt;a href=\"Lock%20of%20Nymph%27s%20Hair\"&gt;lock of hair&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Abela\"&gt;Abela&lt;/a&gt; for , or you can give him and the lock for the &lt;a href=\"Nymph%20Cloak\"&gt;Nymph Cloak&lt;/a&gt;. You may also pickpocket the cloak, even before receiving either the quest or the lock of hair itself."}
{"id": "2886", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2886", "title": "Halberd", "text": "The Halberd is a combination of a spear and an axe. It requires two hands and 13 &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to be wielded and it deals piercing or slashing damage, depending on which is better in a particular situation. However, it only lists piercing damage in its item descriptions. This weapon is favored by and the companion &lt;a href=\"Kivan\"&gt;Kivan&lt;/a&gt;. It is sold at most stores that sell weapons."}
{"id": "3794", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3794", "title": "Halberd +1", "text": "Halberd +1 is an magically enchanted halberd. When this weapon is compared to a normal halberd, it has +1 bonus to damage and thaco, weighs 1 lbs less and has speed factor which is 1 point lower, increasing the attack rate. This item appears in the games of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and ."}
{"id": "5869", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5869", "title": "Halberd +2", "text": "Halberd +2 is an enchanted weapon. It deals 1d10 +2 points of piercing damage, has +2 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and a speed factor of 7. The weapon is 3 lbs lighter than a normal &lt;a href=\"halberd\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in and this item will probably appear in . It's for sale at the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%27s%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer's Mart&lt;/a&gt; and is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Reviane\"&gt;Reviane&lt;/a&gt;. In Throne of Bhaal it is sold at the &lt;a href=\"Tankard%20Tree\"&gt;Tankard Tree&lt;/a&gt; and by &lt;a href=\"Karthis%20al-Hezzar\"&gt;Karthis al-Hezzar&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn it is briefly possible to obtain this item from crusaders from the cut-scene just before the portal to Avernus is opened in the portal room in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough even though this item can be obtained in without cheats; it is quite hidden and not obvious to do so. A sort of portal door clip is required. Where a party member is 'forced' though the locked door into the portal room before the cut-scene is triggered by dialog. This door clip could be an exploit but it can be done without using cheats and it can be done with various methods in an unmodified game. Then from there multiple traps (such as &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt;) must be placed (on top of one another) where the crusaders will spawn during the portal opening cut-scene. A party member must then trigger the cut scene via dialog on the castle basement side of the still locked portal room door. If enough traps were placed effectively before the cut-scene starts, the crusaders will spawn in during the cut-scene and be killed by the traps.\nThe cut-scene crusaders in the portal room of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt; drop many magical +1 and +2 weapons and armour; as well as various magical potions, ammunition, wands and mage robes. Some of these magical items include a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow%20%2B1\"&gt;Composite Longbow +1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor%20%2B2\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor +2&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"https%3A//static.wikia.nocookie.net/baldursgategame/images/c/c8/ILEAT1500000.PNG\"&gt;BG2 v2&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail%20%2B2\"&gt;Chain Mail +2&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B2\"&gt;Quarterstaff +2&lt;/a&gt;, a duplicate of the Short Sword +2 &lt;a href=\"The%20Whistling%20Sword\"&gt;The Whistling Sword&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%2B3\"&gt;Battle Axe +3&lt;/a&gt;. Some magical items may even be unique and or first encounters of said items within and ; this is the case for this Halberd +2."}
