{"id": "6907", "revid": "278753", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6907", "title": "Halfling", "text": "Classes.\nClass Accessibility.\n&lt;a href=\"Barbarian\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;.\nMulti-Class Accessibility.\n&lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Thief\"&gt;Fighter / Thief&lt;/a&gt;.\nHalflings, like &lt;a href=\"Gnome\"&gt;Gnome&lt;/a&gt;s, are far more useful than they appear. Their main failing is the incredibly shallow pool of playable &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; available to them. They make the best thieves in the game in terms of raw thieving abilities because of their ability to naturally raise &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; to 19, best thieving bonuses out of the demihuman races, and the big bonus to saving throws. In spite of the slight penalty for a max &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt; score, they make good single-class &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s because of the saving throw bonuses, dexterity bonus and &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to slings. There's also a strong argument for halfling saves outweighting their Strength penalty for &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"barbarian\"&gt;barbarian&lt;/a&gt;s, and halfling versions of these characters may simply focus on ranged weaponry instead. It is generally accepted that &lt;a href=\"half-orc\"&gt;half-orc&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;Dwarves&lt;/a&gt; make better tanks, because it's quite possible for them to attain a natural Constitution of 20."}
{"id": "46752", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46752", "title": "Halfling Enforcer", "text": "Halfling Enforcer's are the local authority for the village of &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt;. They are summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Halfling\"&gt;Halfling&lt;/a&gt;s when thievery is witnessed in their &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Gullykin%29\"&gt;burrow homes&lt;/a&gt;. As with other authority-types found throughout the region, killing them will result in a decrease in &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "47474", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47474", "title": "Halfling Man (Gullykin)", "text": "Halfling Men are only found in &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin Village&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and the . Some are found wandering around within the village while others are found inside some of the burrow homes or in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Yondalla%20and%20Alvanhendar%27s%20Fine%20Wines\"&gt;Temple of Yondalla and Alvanhendar's Fine Wines&lt;/a&gt; building. A few carry items that can be pick pocketed and they all carry 1 if you're really hard up for some gold.\nThere's a total five different creature \"types\" that are found in the village and each type has their own specific dialogue.\nHALFG3.\nThis halfling man is found in the basement of &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Gullykin%29%23AR4007\"&gt;generic burrow home 2&lt;/a&gt;. He will engage the party in dialogue that focuses on the hospitality of halflings and how it is rude to be insulting his home and hearth with threats of thievery.\nHALFG4.\nThis halfling man is found on the ground floor of &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Gullykin%29%23AR4007\"&gt;generic burrow home 2&lt;/a&gt;. From the dialogue it seems that he may be a little younger than the other halfling men in the village. He will engage the party in dialogue that focuses on adventuring and treasure.\nWhen charmed, he'll give you a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Potion of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nHALFG5.\nThis halfling man is found in the basement of &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Gullykin%29%23AR4009\"&gt;generic burrow home 3&lt;/a&gt;. He will engage the party in dialogue that focuses on his dead brother and his dislike of wanderers. \nHALFG6.\nThis halfling man is found during the day on the ground floor of &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Gullykin%29%23AR4011\"&gt;generic burrow home 4&lt;/a&gt;. From the dialogue it seems that he may be a little older than the other halfling men in the village. He will engage the party in dialogue that focuses on his traveling days of the past.\nWhen charmed, he'll give you a &lt;a href=\"sling\"&gt;sling&lt;/a&gt;.\nHALFGU.\nThis halfling man is found wandering around the village and inside the Temple of Yondalla and Alvanhendar's Fine Wines . He will engage the party in dialogue that focuses on the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Ruins\"&gt;Firewine Ruins&lt;/a&gt; and the halflings relative indifference to them. There is no opportunity to reply to any of his statements.\nHe doesn't have much to say when charmed.\nTwo of his statements result in &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entries in the quest section under the title \"The Firewine Ruins\":"}
{"id": "34462", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34462", "title": "Halfling Treasures", "text": "Halfling Treasures is a &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" that can be acquired by talking to &lt;a href=\"Takos\"&gt;Takos&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt;; he reveals that he lost all his\u00a0heirlooms in a fire. &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can offer to help him recover them.\nRecovering the heirlooms.\nCloak of the Beluir Watch.\nThis can be found in a locked chest outside of the burned inn, next to its eastern wall.\nGentrus's Hand Mirror.\nThe mirror is in a small hidden stash inside the burned inn, somewhere in the center. (There are several like this one there, other stashes might only have trash inside or be empty).\nThe Suncatcher.\nThe &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; must venture to\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Forest\"&gt;Coast Way Forest&lt;/a&gt;, where it's in the possession of vampire hunter &lt;a href=\"Isabella\"&gt;Isabella&lt;/a&gt;. They can complete the quest &lt;a href=\"Isabella%20and%20Ikros\"&gt;Isabella and Ikros&lt;/a&gt; in order to get it as a reward. Alternatively, they can side with the vampire and get it off Isabella's dead body, or pickpocket it."}
{"id": "51420", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51420", "title": "Halfling Warrior (Athas)", "text": "Halfling Warrior (Athas) are creatures introduced in the Planar Sphere. These creatures are from Athas, a world on another plane. They are vicious and cannibalistic fighters with ill intent and will aggressively charge forward and attack any detected party members. \nThese helmeted and chain mail clad warriors will move deliberately at any party members detected and attempt to bash the fresh meat to death, and possibly tenderize the player characters as well, for a cannibal feast upon the party's flesh.\nThese creatures only attack with melee weaponry and have no dialogue. They carry no valuables, but their equipment can be taken when defeated. There are about a dozen of these Halfling warriors within the Planar Sphere.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to these creatures scripts, and abilities. An SCS tactical fighter script is supplied for more intelligent attack and defense behavior. 2-pips in Single weapon fighting style are also assigned to the warrior which boosts critical hit chances and improves Armor Class by 2. SCS random treasures are supplied into the creature's inventory."}
{"id": "47476", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47476", "title": "Halfling Woman (Gullykin)", "text": "\"Halfling Women\" are only found in &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin Village&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and the . Two are found wandering around within the village while a third one is found during the day in the basement of &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Gullykin%29%23AR4007\"&gt;generic burrow home 2&lt;/a&gt;. They have no items that can be pick pocketed but they do carry 10 .\nShe will engage the party in dialogue that focuses on adventuring and the hospitality of halflings.\nWhen charmed, she will mention the Firewine Bridge and update your world map to show its location (even if you've already discovered the area on your own). "}
