{"id": "52043", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52043", "title": "Hand of Vecna", "text": "The Hand of Vecna is a &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; for the release of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", but promoted on its now archived official website, under the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//web.archive.org/web/20010617185502/http%3A//www.interplay.com%3A80/bgate/fae_magic.html\"&gt;\"Magic\" section&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe hand of Vecna is described in the \"&lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3AEncyclopedia%20Magica%20Volume%20II\"&gt;Encyclopedia Magica Volume II&lt;/a&gt;\", an &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3ACategory%3A2nd%20edition%20sourcebooks\"&gt;accessory&lt;/a&gt; for the \"\", the original is based upon. According to its entry, it will irreversibly replace a user's normal hand, leaving them one-handed even after removing it. Every use of its primary powers, though, reduces the chances to remove the hand again, and it will be permanently attached after having used them ten times. In addition, it will cause the \"wearer\" to become &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt;.\nPowers.\nThe hand's primary powers are &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28disambiguation%29\"&gt;spell-like abilities&lt;/a&gt; for up to three times per &lt;a href=\"rest\"&gt;rest&lt;/a&gt;, including the &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Finger of Death&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning\"&gt;Monster Summoning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sleep\"&gt;Sleep&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;; locating various forms of treasure in a certain vicinity; teleport; x-ray vision; and a sense of danger. Secondary powers are the ability to &lt;a href=\"Find%20Traps%20%28skill%29\"&gt;detect traps and secret doors&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=\"infravision\"&gt;infravision&lt;/a&gt;; and levitation and flying. If a &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt; is touched with the hand, this will once per day turn their bones to jelly.\nThe more often powers are used, the higher the chances for the user to become ethereal when, for example, facing danger or being uncertain of situations otherwise."}
{"id": "31090", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31090", "title": "Handmaiden's Mace", "text": "Her mace can be looted from a &lt;a href=\"Handmaiden%20of%20Lolth\"&gt;Handmaiden of Lolth&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;priestess&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Lolth\"&gt;Queen of Spiders&lt;/a&gt; who tries to hunt down &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt; if the latter is &lt;a href=\"romance\"&gt;romance&lt;/a&gt;d in \"\"."}
{"id": "51781", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51781", "title": "Handmaiden of Lolth", "text": "Handmaiden of Lolth is a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; cleric and a handmaiden of the spider queen &lt;a href=\"Lolth\"&gt;Lolth&lt;/a&gt;. She is within the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Lolth\"&gt;Temple of Lolth&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis priestess of Lolth is inside the temple, and passively turns her gaze to those in range. She is robed, armored and keeps two flails at her side.\nSpeaking with a Handmaiden without invitation or command is considered risky in drow society, especially by males. Do so as you desire.\nIf the drow are made hostile, she'll quickly launch a few force-cast defensive buffs and engage in spell use and melee combat with enemies. \nWill begin with &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;, then any detected spell casters will be targeted by a &lt;a href=\"Miscast%20Magic\"&gt;Miscast Magic&lt;/a&gt; spell. \nIf able, she'll next attempt to get up a &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;. The remaining scripted spell cast AI options are shown in her InfoBox.\nBug.\nUnlike almost every drow in the Underdark or Ust Natha, this creature has no natural &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; assigned. Probably an error, especially for a Cleric of Lolth.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the Handmaiden. A new set of memorized spells is provided. The \"Smarter Priest\" AI will improve spell casting behavior. If anyone nearby is invisible, will cast &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Invisibility\"&gt;Detect Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;. \nUpon hostilities breaking out she'll insta-cast &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;. A few tics later an &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Animate Dead (priest)&lt;/a&gt; will go off. \nAfter that the priest will use offensive and disabling spells based on the AI's target assessment and vulnerability analysis. She'll be melee attacking with Spiritual Hammer instead of her flails.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed; all the divine spells will be the SR versions."}
