{"id": "55741", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55741", "title": "Handwritten Note (LUM1)", "text": "Handwritten Note (LUM1) is one just one of eight Lum machine notes found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in and . \nThe note's subject matter pertains to the &lt;a href=\"Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis particular note is found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt details in an abbreviated manner a combination sequence that must be selected to initiate the \"big muscles\" result. \nThe machine will bestow a permanent effect that grants a point of &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to the character entering the combination - which is pulling the Short Lever, then the Medium Lever, and pressing the Square Button. The player's info screen will display a text reading:\nNote that repeating the same combination a second time (or more) will result in an unpredictable effect, such as being &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisoned&lt;/a&gt;, permanently losing a point of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps being &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55742", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55742", "title": "Handwritten Note (LUM2)", "text": "Handwritten Note (LUM2) is one just one of eight Lum machine notes found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in and . \nThe note's subject matter pertains to the &lt;a href=\"Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis particular note is found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt details in an abbreviated manner a combination sequence that must be selected to initiate the \"tough guy\" result. \nThe machine will bestow a permanent effect that grants a point of &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; to the character entering the combination - which is pulling the Long Lever, turning the Red Dial, and pressing the Circular Button. The player's info screen will display a text reading:\nNote that repeating the same combination a second time (or more) will result in an unpredictable effect, such as being &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisoned&lt;/a&gt;, permanently losing a point of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps being &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55743", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55743", "title": "Handwritten Note (LUM3)", "text": "Handwritten Note (LUM3) is one of eight Lum machine notes found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in and . \nThe note's subject matter pertains to the &lt;a href=\"Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis particular note is found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt details in an abbreviated manner a combination sequence that must be selected to initiate the \"storm in hand\" result. \nThe machine will grant the weapon &lt;a href=\"Storm%20Star\"&gt;Storm Star&lt;/a&gt; (unidentified) to the character entering the combination - which is pulling the Medium Lever, turning the Green Dial, and pressing the Triangular Button. The player's info screen will display a text reading:\nNote that repeating the same combination a second time (or more) will result in an unpredictable effect, such as being &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisoned&lt;/a&gt;, permanently losing a point of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps being &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55744", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55744", "title": "Handwritten Note (LUM4)", "text": "Handwritten Note (LUM4) is one of eight Lum machine notes found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in and .\nThe note's subject matter pertains to the &lt;a href=\"Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis particular note is found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt details in an abbreviated manner a combination sequence that must be selected to initiate the \"no magic\" result. \nThe machine will bestow a permanent effect that grants 5% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance\"&gt;Magic Resistance&lt;/a&gt; to the character entering the combination - which is pulling the Long Lever, turning the Blue Dial, and turning the Green Dial. The player's info screen will display a text reading:\nNote that repeating the same combination a second time (or more) will result in an unpredictable effect, such as being &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisoned&lt;/a&gt;, permanently losing a point of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps being &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55745", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55745", "title": "Handwritten Note (LUM5)", "text": "Handwritten Note (LUM5) is one just one of eight Lum machine notes found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in and . \nThe note's subject matter pertains to the &lt;a href=\"Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis particular note is found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt details in an abbreviated manner a combination sequence that must be selected to initiate the \"words to the wise\" result. \nThe machine will bestow a permanent effect that grants a point of &lt;a href=\"Wisdom\"&gt;Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; to the character entering the combination - which is pressing the Circular Button, pressing the Square Button, and pressing the Triangular Button. The player's info screen will display a text reading:\nNote that repeating the same combination a second time (or more) will result in an unpredictable effect, such as being &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisoned&lt;/a&gt;, permanently losing a point of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps being &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt;."}
