{"id": "9252", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9252", "title": "Harbinger", "text": "The Two Handed Sword +3 'Harbinger'&lt;a href=\"%23Bugs\"&gt;b&lt;/a&gt; is a two-handed weapon in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" that inflicts &lt;a href=\"slashing%20damage\"&gt;slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; and has a chance to evoke &lt;a href=\"%23Fireball\"&gt;fireballs&lt;/a&gt; and is able to petrify .\nGameplay.\nWith its weight of 10 pounds, the Harbinger +3 much lighter than an ordinary &lt;a href=\"two-handed%20sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;. \nComparing the common combat statistics furthermore, it adds a bonus of 3 to the &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Speed%20Factor\"&gt;attack speed&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"slashing%20damage\"&gt;slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; dealt with it. As usual for melee weapons, hit chance and damage are additionally modified by the wielder's strength.\nFlesh to Stone ability.\nAny creature of the &lt;a href=\"race\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt; that is hit with this sword must make a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spell or be &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt;. This effect bypasses &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and can't be &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt;.\nFireball ability.\nOn each hit with the sword, there's a 5%-chance to evoke a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; spell centered on the target. If the event is triggered, the weapon instantly casts the arcane third level spell and produces a 10d6 &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt; explosion. As with the wizards 'spell, magic resistance can block it, and a save vs. spells will half the damage. \nThe Harbinger weapon version &lt;a href=\"Eric%20Vanstraaten\"&gt;Eric Vanstraaten&lt;/a&gt; is using in the \"\" lacks this effect, so to not accidentally hurt allies."}
