{"id": "5941", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5941", "title": "Hardiness", "text": "Hardiness\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt; classes and their kits.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects this ability from the \"Special Abilities\" button on the chosen party character menu (also from the default F12 key).\nThe ability initiates with a zero-casting time on the caster. At this moment a sound effect is audible, the caster undergoes a brief color fade and a 3D graphic plays over the character's sprite. The character's portrait will display a \"Hardiness\" icon until the ability expires/is removed.\nHardiness provides the caster with a +40% &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance bonus while the ability is active.\nOther sources of physical damage resistance are additive to this, for example, &lt;a href=\"Defender%20of%20Easthaven\"&gt;Defender of Easthaven&lt;/a&gt; flail, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt; divine spell, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Form\"&gt;Shadow Form&lt;/a&gt; ability or the &lt;a href=\"Helmet%20of%20Dumathoin\"&gt;Helmet of Dumathoin&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis ability cannot be removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects. However, the ability is classified as a \"Combat Protection\" and can be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell or effect.\nThe Hardiness ability in the Enhanced Editions limits the ability from cumulative/additive protection from three sources:\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns warrior High Level Class abilities to eligible creatures. This results in the party facing this ability when used by enemies/opponents in combat. Nearly any warrior class with at least 20 experience levels may have an HLA assigned and scripted for use. As the XP levels climb, so will the number of available HLA's, in similar fashion to a player's warrior party members.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this ability, revising its effects. See below for description:"}
{"id": "7982", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7982", "title": "Hareishan (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "Hareishan is a &lt;a href=\"neutral%20good\"&gt;neutral good&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who works for the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; guarding the lower levels of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nHareishan can be found in the central Dining Hall on the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%202\"&gt;second level&lt;/a&gt; of the Cloakwood Mine, surrounded by guards and &lt;a href=\"Blacktalon%20Elite\"&gt;Blacktalon Elite&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs the fight begins, she casts &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; on herself, then turns to offensive spells, including:\nThe remaining spells in her spellbook are unused.\nTrivia.\nA &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; by the &lt;a href=\"Hareishan%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;same name&lt;/a&gt; is working for &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and can be met in a random encounter in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"."}
{"id": "29642", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29642", "title": "Hareishan (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "Hareishan is a female &lt;a href=\"Vampires\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and a loyal member of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nChapters 2 or 3.\nThe most likely appearance of Hareishan will be during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; (Chapter 3 is technically possible, but actually difficult to achieve) she may appear in any district of the city during a night cycle (midnight to dawn). Hareishan is the first member of Bodhi's Vampire Coven that the protagonist will encounter this way.\nThe party will witness her battling three &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;. Although she appears neutral during this fight, you may attack the vampire for 8,500 XP without getting in trouble with anyone but her. If you choose to simply watch her, she will make short work of her enemies, which you can loot thereafter.\nIf the party has not yet decided to support any side yet in this guild war, after the thieves are slain by the vampire, she'll hiss a warning:\nThere will be several other lines of dialogue if the party has decided to support the shadow thieves.\nIt's also possible to assist the Shadow Thieves, force the vampire into gas cloud escape mode, and briefly converse with one of the thieves, who'll likely say:\nThis is followed by:\nThe most noteworthy treasure they drop is a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Opal\"&gt;Black Opal&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Water%20Opal\"&gt;Water Opal&lt;/a&gt;, and a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Contingency\"&gt;Contingency&lt;/a&gt; from the first thief (VVSHAD1), a &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;Sphene Gem&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Bloodstone%20Gem\"&gt;Bloodstone Gem&lt;/a&gt;, one scroll of &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and one of &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt; from the second thief (VVSHAD2), and a &lt;a href=\"Pearl%20Necklace\"&gt;Pearl Necklace&lt;/a&gt; from the third one (VVSHAD3).\nThe first shadow thief also has a note on him which reads:\n\"Proclamation of warning to all guild members:\"\n\"The Shadow council itself decrees that all chapters should be on their guard against the upstart assassins' guild usurping our membership. The lure of coin is naught but bait, and it is suspected that the end of those that have defected has been most bloody. No guild can rival the Shadow Thieves, so any that claim as such must have darker motives.\"\n\"You have been warned of the cost of treachery.\"\nIf you encounter her during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; and don't make her turn hostile, she will give you a warning before turning into a bat and escaping after the battle (regardless of whether you've taken on &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; as your &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild%20Stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt;).\nIf you encounter her during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt; and you've &lt;a href=\"Aran%27s%20tasks%20to%20receive%20the%20Shadow%20Thieves%27%20aid\"&gt;sided with the Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;, she will attack the party.\nHareishan uses a general script that allows her to launch a &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; innate ability at a single target, after the first two rounds of combat. She also will turn into a bat if helpless, and a gas form cloud when hit points are at zero to flee the battlefield. She can only be struck by +2 or better enchanted weapons.\nChapter 6.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;, she will be encountered again in &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Bodhi's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; scenario, regardless of whether she was \"killed\" during the first encounter. Her HP has increased to 115 and several other stats have also changed (see infobox). She has a worse THAC0 and Armor Class, does less crushing damage, but drains 3 experience levels on any hit. She can attempt a Vampire Domination after two rounds of combat are initiated. Additionally, normal weapons can strike her.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod with the \"Improved Vampires\" component revises all appearances of Hareishan. See the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article and the \"Mod content\" section for a discussion of the mod's revisions to vampires (including Hareishan) in the game.&lt;br&gt;\nThe first version of this vampire (VVHAREIS.CRE) is a level 11/11 Fighter/Thief with 124 HP, STR 19, DEX 19, CON 18. She has 2.5 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;, THAC0 6 and -3 Armor Class. A default SCS script is assigned allowing Vampire Domination ability every 2 rounds, and attacks with either a level drain or \"\"Blood Drain\" temporarily reducing CON by 3. She can only be struck by +3 or better weapons. She can shape change into bat or wolf form, and summon bats, rats or wolves with the \"children of the night\"\" ability.\nThe second version of this vampire (C6HAREI.CRE) is a level 12/12 Fighter/Thief with 160 HP, STR20, DEX 20, CON 19. She has 2.5 attacks per round, THAC0 4 and -3 Armor Class. Her melee strike drains 3 experience levels or 3 CON. She also has a different default script, making her akin to an ancient vampire, that has all the abilities of the former version plus the innate &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20Fear\"&gt;Vampire Fear&lt;/a&gt; ability and the \"Mesmerize\" feeblemindedness attack. She will recognize opponents protected from level drain and charm and many other \"buffs\" for intelligent targeting."}
{"id": "5204", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5204", "title": "Harm", "text": "The Harm spell is the reverse of &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; and causes massive damage instead of healing.\nMod content.\nRegarding the Harm spell, the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod will do the following:\nModify the Harm spell so it does damage rather than reducing target to 1 hp (BG2,BGT)\nThe Harm spell reduces its target to 1 hp in 2nd edition D&amp;D; in 3rd edition, it does a large amount of damage instead. This component modifies Harm to work more like the 3rd edition spell: it inflicts 150 hp damage, with no saving throw, on a successful touch attack, to a minimum of 1 hp. The rationale for this is that Harm (especially combined with Critical Strike) is otherwise an almost-instant way of eliminating even foes with hundreds of hit points. Harm remains lethal in this component, but is not quite so overwhelming.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod makes changes to Harm, spell description below:\nHarm&lt;br&gt;\nLevel: 6&lt;br&gt;\nSchool: Necromancy&lt;br&gt;\nSphere: Necromantic&lt;br&gt;\nRange: Personal&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: 1 turn&lt;br&gt;\nCasting Time: 6&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: 1 creature&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: Spell half&lt;br&gt;\nThis spell is the reverse of Heal. Instead of healing the creature touched, it causes damage. On a successful touch from the priest, the spell inflicts 90 points of damage upon the target. Harm cannot reduce the target\u2019s hit points to less than 1. The spell expires once the priest makes a successful melee attack or after 1 turn has passed. The priest gains a +4 bonus to hit the target. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.\nIf both SCS and SR are installed, the SR version will be the one implemented."}
