{"id": "46453", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46453", "title": "Haste effect", "text": "Haste is a status effect that comes in three different kinds: Weak, normal, and improved. Weak Haste is not available to players in .\nEffect on tick rate.\nThe following only applies to . In the original edition of , the multiplier discussed below is always x2, and the extra tick occurs halfway within the period.\nAny effect that triggers repeatedly based on time is affected by the Haste effect. The main ones are &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Regeneration\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; and the damage-inflicting types of &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt;. All of them follow the same rules: The amount of triggers (or ticks) per unit of time is multiplied by the following factor.\nNote: Regeneration granted by having a &lt;a href=\"Constitution%23Scores%20table\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; of 20 or higher is not sped up by Haste at all.\nBesides the Poison, damage-inflicting Disease and Regeneration effects, the following items or spells obey the rule: \nFinally, effects from &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Blades\"&gt;Globe of Blades&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Repulse%20Undead\"&gt;Repulse Undead&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Cloak of the Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Night%20Club\"&gt;Night Club&lt;/a&gt; are special in that they trigger approximately once per 100 AI ticks (once per 6\u2154 seconds), and Haste grants them a x2 factor.\nIt is worth noting that extra ticks are not spread out evenly within the effect's un-hasted tick period. Instead, each extra tick occurs at 50% of the remaining time in the period. For example, an effect that ticks once per 60 seconds will tick 7 times per 60 seconds under Haste. But of the 6 extra ticks, the first one will not occur until the 30s mark, the second one until the 45s mark, the third one until 52.5s, etc, meaning that 4 out of the seven ticks will occur within the last 4 seconds. The 7th tick will occur at the 60s mark; it is the initial, un-hasted tick.\nWhat Haste does NOT do.\nThe Haste effect halves round duration, but this doesn't have the wide implications of the &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt;. In particular, the Haste effect does NOT: "}
