{"id": "6338", "revid": "276279", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6338", "title": "Haz", "text": "Haz is a mage who works for the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf you sided with &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;, he will task the party with killing &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and her vampires. Haz will be waiting for you in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; district with a golem, willing to help you defeat Bodhi.\nIf the player sided with Bodhi, you will need to kill Haz to gain possession of the &lt;a href=\"Key%20to%20Aran%27s%20Lair\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; to Aran Linvail's chamber. Haz is found in a storage/dining room back near the eastern side of Aran Linvail's hideout which is accessible through a secret door from the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\nLower Tombs:\n\"At last, you've arrived. These spiders were starting to make me nervous. Allow me to open these doors for you.\"\n\"Fleshy! Go forth and open the doors! Now, you stupid creature! Now! &lt;Gorion's Ward&gt;, I trust you're prepared.\"\nAran's Hideout:\n\"I wondered if you might eventually drag yourself over to me. I'm afraid your Mistress Bodhi shall have to remain in her graveyard lair. Your little invasion shall end here and her plans with it!\""}
