{"id": "32542", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32542", "title": "Throwing Hammers", "text": "Throwing Hammers are a &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Class\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; of one-handed ranged and melee weapon that shares the Hammers &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;weapon proficiency&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"War%20Hammers\"&gt;War Hammers&lt;/a&gt; in all games except for classic Baldur's Gate, in which they did not exist. They cannot be used by the following &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;character classes&lt;/a&gt; and class kits: Beast Master, Druid (including Fighter/Druid) Monk, Shaman, Mage, Sorcerer and Thief. When thrown, the basic Throwing Hammer has a range of 30ft and deals 1d4+1 missile damage with a speed factor of 3. When used in melee, they have a range of 1ft and deal 1d3+1 crushing damage with a speed factor of 4. Lastly, they require a strength of 6 to use.\nUnique Throwing Hammers however do not have a speed factor bonus when thrown nor a damage penalty when used in melee. Most have a base damage of 2d4 instead of 1d4+1. They have a range of 20ft (or 100ft) when thrown and require a strength of 9 (or 18) to use.\nDescription.\nGeneric Throwing Hammers in do not have a description. Unique Throwing Hammers in use the description of generic War Hammers before they are identified.\nList of Throwing Hammers.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nIn Baldur's Gate = &lt;dpl&gt;\nnamespace = \ncategory = Throwing hammers\ncategory = Items in Baldur's Gate|Items, added by Tales of the Sword Coast|Items in Tales of the Sword Coast|Items, new in Tales of the Sword Coast|Items in Baldur's Gate (Enhanced Edition)|Items, new in Baldur's Gate (Enhanced Edition)\nnotcategory = Cut items\nnotcategory = Mod items\nordermethod = sortkey\nuses = Template:Infobox item\ninclude = {Infobox item}.list weapons|hide_type=yes|dpl_game=bg1\nformat = ,\\n,\n&lt;/dpl&gt;\nIn Siege of Dragonspear = &lt;dpl&gt;\nnamespace = \ncategory = Throwing hammers\ncategor