{"id": "38658", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38658", "title": "Thug (Tanner Shop)", "text": "These \"Tanner\" Thugs (or by association, \"Rune Thugs\") have been hired as \"Tuffs\" by &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; and, under certain circumstances, may be encountered within Rejiek's &lt;a href=\"Tanner%20Shop\"&gt;Tanner Shop&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nTanner Thugs.\nAll Tanner Thugs have the following in common: Lawful Neutral &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Alignment&lt;/a&gt;, 6th level Human &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighters&lt;/a&gt; protected by &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt;. Differences are summarized below:\nTanner Thug 1.\nThis Thug is protected further by a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shield\"&gt;Medium Shield&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=\"Basic%20Helmets%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Open-Faced Helmet&lt;/a&gt;. He must close to melee with his &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;, as he does not have a ranged weapon. He carries no other items or gold.\n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug02\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a02&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug03\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a03&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23Notes\"&gt;Notes&lt;/a&gt;\nTanner Thug 2.\nThis Thug is protected further by a Medium Shield. She must close to melee with her &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt;. She has , and is worth \n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug01\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a01&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug03\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a03&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23Notes\"&gt;Notes&lt;/a&gt;\nTanner Thug 3.\nThis Thug is also protected by an Open-Faced Helmet. He can attack at range with a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow\"&gt;Composite Longbow&lt;/a&gt; and mundane &lt;a href=\"Arrows\"&gt;Arrows&lt;/a&gt; , or close to melee with his &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;. He carries no other items or gold, and is worth \n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug01\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a01&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug02\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a02&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23Notes\"&gt;Notes&lt;/a&gt;\nNotes.\n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug01\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a01&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug02\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a02&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TanTug03\"&gt;Tanner\u00a0Thug\u00a03&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "2517", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2517", "title": "Thunderhammer Smithy", "text": "Thunderhammer Smithy is the store of renowned blacksmith &lt;a href=\"Taerom%20Fuiruim\"&gt;Taerom Fuiruim&lt;/a&gt; that's located in the town of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;. Taerom and his three &lt;a href=\"Smith\"&gt;Smith&lt;/a&gt;s are present from 4:30 am to 9:30 pm every day. The store is likely the first store &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will encounter that offers enchanted items, with many +1 variants of weapons, armor, and ammunition available, as well as a few even more powerful items, such as a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20of%20Venom\"&gt;Dagger of Venom&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlongside the selling of weapons, armor, and projectiles, Taerom also identifies items of those aforementioned categories. It is also possible to obtain a set of Ankheg armor from him.\nLoot.\nThe chest near Taerom is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;. The other two chests are also locked with the one against the wall containing a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Bastard Sword +1&lt;/a&gt; and six more spears and the other one containing the following swords:"}
{"id": "19818", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19818", "title": "Thurston", "text": "Thurston is a wealthy &lt;a href=\"nobleman\"&gt;nobleman&lt;/a&gt; who is encountered standing near the stone fireplace in a backroom located on the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Inn\"&gt;Candlekeep Inn&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". His name is only given if his wife &lt;a href=\"Lovey\"&gt;Lovey&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href=\"charmed\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt; \nInvolvement.\nThough Thurston's wife, who is also standing in the room, isn't very talkative when addressed herself, she adds to the conversation during dialogue with the nobleman.\nStandoffish \u2013 or not?\nIf spoken to for the first time, Thurston and Lovey, unless charmed, express how standoffish and inhospitable all the &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; behave. There are four options for &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to answer this: two try to provide an understanding of the life at Candlekeep (#1 and #4), one is a rude defense (#2), and one makes wealth and jewelry the topic (#3) \u2013 with these latter two dialogue paths depending on Thurston's reaction to the speaker, &lt;a href=\"%23jewelry\"&gt;the one about jewelry&lt;/a&gt; in the \"Enhanced Edition\" possibly even ending up in an opportunity to gain such oneself.\nSomeone killed \"Lovey\".\nIf for whatever reason Lovey dies before the above dialogue options were chosen, all of them become impossible. In the original \"Baldur's Gate\", he still addresses her, but without her response the dialogue ends.&lt;a href=\"%23wd1\"&gt;b1&lt;/a&gt; In the \"Enhanced Edition\", he then has only default lines left (as little sense as they make),&lt;a href=\"%23wd2\"&gt;b2&lt;/a&gt; which ends the dialogue as well.\nCharming the man.\nThurston has a special line if he is charmed before spoken to:\nTrivia.\nThurston and his wife Lovey are a spoof of the millionaire couple Thurston Howell III and Eunice \"Lovey\" Howell from the 1960's television show Gilligan's Island."}
{"id": "8890", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8890", "title": "Tiana", "text": "Tiana is a female in the tavern area of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;, she's seen looking around intently as if to find someone. \nGameplay.\nIf you speak with her, she will ask you if you have seen her husband, &lt;a href=\"Rumar\"&gt;Rumar&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf you have spoken with Rumar, you can tell her you saw him in the backrooms in which case Tiana will find Rumar with his new lover &lt;a href=\"Priss\"&gt;Priss&lt;/a&gt;. \nAfter a short debate, Tiana and Priss will attack each other and fight to the death over him. Rumar will then go off with the victor. Love hurts.\nNote.\nTiana's alignment is True Neutral in the original game and changed to Lawful Evil in the Enhanced Edition."}
{"id": "3750", "revid": "273719", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3750", "title": "Tiax", "text": "Tiax is a chaotic evil gnome &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Multi-class\"&gt;multi-class&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Thief\"&gt;cleric / thief&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in .\n&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; &amp;.\nRecruitment.\nTiax\u00a0is available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt; and can be found in front of the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, at &lt;a href=\"coordinates\"&gt;coordinates&lt;/a&gt; (1447, 1616). Talk to him, agree to join him, and he'll be off to conquer the world - doing you the honor of permitting you to accompany and serve him.\nGameplay.\nTiax has Summon &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghast&lt;/a&gt; as a special ability, which is particularly useful against &lt;a href=\"basilisk\"&gt;basilisk&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"sirine\"&gt;sirine&lt;/a&gt;s because ghasts (as undead) are immune to petrification and charm. Despite its slow movement, the ghast is one of the best offensive summons, having 3 attacks per round (apr) that will paralyze opponents with successful hits unless the target &lt;a href=\"save\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt;s vs. death, and/or cause disease unless the target saves vs. breath.\nTiax is the only companion who can stay safe from a failed pickpocket attempt against a dangerous target - the target will go hostile but Tiax is safe if he has &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; active.\nAs a gnome with 16 &lt;a href=\"constitution\"&gt;constitution&lt;/a&gt;, Tiax has a +4 bonus on saves vs. Spells and Wands. His starting equipment is a mace, leather armor, a sling and 15 bullets.\n\nTiax finally gets himself locked in jail. Travel to the Flaming Fist Headquarters in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt; and you'll find him in a cell northwest. He won't be available as a companion, and most of the dialogue options you have are to mock him; he'll fall unconscious after trying to attack you bare-handed from behind the bars.\nWhen you return to the headquarters later in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Thirteen%20%E2%80%93%20Epilogue\"&gt;Chapter Thirteen \u2013 Epilogue&lt;/a&gt;, you'll find &lt;a href=\"Clara\"&gt;Clara&lt;/a&gt; in the same cell instead.\nIn \"Shadows of Amn\", Tiax is in a cell in the asylum &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, a place where the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; keep their prisoners. He is put there because of his want for world domination as it would cause destruction if he tried. He cannot be recruited.\nTiax will participate in a battle against Irenicus, along with several other inmates of the Asylum as well as the &lt;a href=\"Party\"&gt;Party&lt;/a&gt;. Tiax won't survive the battle, because the scripted plot Rules All.\nPersonality.\nTiax is quite insane and lives under the delusion of grandeur. He believes he was chosen by &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt; himself to rule over all, and his ego far surpasses his stature or abilities. Most of the time he is oblivious to anyone other than himself."}
{"id": "23377", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23377", "title": "Tibbit", "text": "Tibbit is a goblin &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; hiding out in the &lt;a href=\"Marching%20Mountains\"&gt;Marching Mountains&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Chinchilla\"&gt;Chinchilla&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Merlinious\"&gt;Merlinious&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Toop%20the%20Brave\"&gt;Toop the Brave&lt;/a&gt;. When the party comes within sight of the group, Chinchilla will shout \"Oh no! We've been discovered, my Bhaalspawn friends! Fight! Fiiighhht!\" and they will immediately turn hostile.\nBugs.\nIn the original Shadows of Amn goblins are classified by race as either &lt;a href=\"hobgoblin\"&gt;hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt; and classified by class as either hobgoblin or &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; (usually when the creature is equipped with armor and/or weapons unusable by a thief). This is not fixed in the Enhanced Edition of either game. However, it is fixed in the where goblins are now properly classified as race: Goblin and class: Fighter.\nFor the sake of proper classification within this wiki and to follow the correct D&amp;D classification, goblins are classified using the Siege of Dragonspear classifications. In Tibbit's case the developers gave him a race of kobold, but since the developers used goblin animation for him, it must be surmised that he is a goblin and not a kobold. The got his class correct. "}
{"id": "7918", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7918", "title": "Tiber", "text": "Tiber is a peasant in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" who is encountered standing in the shade of a large tree on the other side of the creek from the spot where the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party enter the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Nest\"&gt;Cloakwood Nest&lt;/a&gt; area.\nTiber and his brother Chelak decided to go into the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood\"&gt;Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; to clear the woods of a spider infestation. His brother had found \nthe enchanted sword &lt;a href=\"Spider%27s%20Bane\"&gt;Spider's Bane&lt;/a&gt; and they thought they'd become famous for performing the deed. He asks you to look for his brother, who went into the woods a week ago and hasn't returned. If you agree to search for Chelak, the side quest &lt;a href=\"Spiders%20in%20the%20Cloakwood\"&gt;Spiders in the Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; is added to your &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; in the \"Quests\" section. Tiber has an exceptionally timid and cowardly demeanor, so it is hardly surprising that his brother left to explore the Cloakwood alone."}
{"id": "8368", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8368", "title": "Tick", "text": "Tick is a person who is found standing in the street in the southwest corner of &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He will approach the party upon sight - recognizing them as adventurers - and will advise them to visit the &lt;a href=\"Sewers\"&gt;sewer system&lt;/a&gt;, as it is an urban analogue of a dungeon. When the dialogue is finished he'll walk away and disappear.\nDialogue.\n\"Hey, you look like sewer-running types if ever I saw any.\""}
{"id": "13808", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13808", "title": "Tiefling", "text": "Tieflings are the product of &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;-fiend crossbreeding. They are similar to , their half-human, half-fiend counterpart, though tieflings are the result of half-fiends breeding with ordinary mortals\nTieflings tend to have an unsettling air about them, and most people feel uncomfortable around them. Most tieflings retain some physical characteristics of their demon parents; the most common features being horns, tails and pointed teeth, while others have more subtle markings such as unusual skin or eye color.\nTieflings\u2019 abilities in general reflect their heritage. They are intelligent and agile creatures and in spite of their appearance, alluring and charming. However, they were also quick to anger. They make excellent &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s.\nLike other races that were the result of cross-breeding, tieflings have no true culture they could call their own. Tieflings are generally scattered among all planes and there is no nation that can claim to be their homeland. Their personality and beliefs are dependent on their upbringing and their attitude towards their fiendish ancestry. While some embrace their demonic side, others fear and shun it. In general, tieflings are not necessarily evil, though they usually retain the chaotic nature of their demon parents.\nTieflings, nonetheless, are generally feared due to their heritage and this prejudice has turned them into self-reliant loners that are hard to trust others of any race, even their own.\nThey receive the exact same proficiency bonuses that Elves do: -1 THAC0 bonus to Long Swords, Short Swords, Longbows and Shortbows."}
{"id": "55920", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55920", "title": "Tiefling (Fighter)", "text": "The Tiefling (Fighter) is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; when traveling through a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Tieflings%20%28AR3005%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Tieflings (AR3005)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThis Tiefling is a fighter that will empower its &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; ability when an enemy is detected, and then move forward and attack the nearest opponent it can reach.\nThe creature wields a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%2B2\"&gt;Battle Axe +2&lt;/a&gt; in each hand.\nIf the creature is hit aby any &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; it will quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Fire Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the Tiefling is wounded to 50% of its hit points, it will consume a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Superior%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Superior Healing&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature slightly with a new Fighter AI script for improved tactical awareness. \nSCS changes the creatures weapon proficiencies in Axe to 3 pips but boosts the 2-weapon fighting style to 3 pips.\nSCS also adds scripted use of &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;, as the fighter has a Berserker kit."}
{"id": "55923", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55923", "title": "Tiefling (Mage)", "text": "The Tiefling (Mage) is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; when traveling through a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Tieflings%20%28AR3005%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Tieflings (AR3005)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThis Tiefling is a mage with will cry out an alarm when the party is detected. She also initiates the summoning of &lt;a href=\"Aranthis\"&gt;Aranthis&lt;/a&gt; the Tiefling planar hound.\nThe mage will initially be able to chain cast several protective buffs to include &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter that her spell casting is driven by various script factors as outlined in the InfoBox. \nThe mage has her &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Spell%20Striking\"&gt;Wand of Spell Striking&lt;/a&gt; in the quick weapon slot and is scripted to fire it if any detected opponent has any kind of Globe spell, or spell turning, or some kind of spell shield or deflection up.\nThis creature will try and quaff a potion of Superior Healing if damaged to 50% of hit points.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature a new AI script for smarter spell casting, with improved opponent protection and vulnerability recognition.\nWhen the mod is installed, it randomly assigns a mage kit to most wizards. So, this Tiefling could be a Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer. The kit assigned will alter the mage's scripted spell selection.\nExpect a more protective initial series of buffs at the beginning of the conflict with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Mesthil's Acid Sheath\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20The%20Elements\"&gt;Protection From The Elements&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with SR), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, and \"Mind Blank\" with SR.\nThis level 20 mage has a prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; for instant deployment based on battle conditions.\nDepending on the player's game difficulty selection, this mage has scripted mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; choices such as &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis mage can attempt to take down party protections with &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt;. \nExpect a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Malison\"&gt;Greater Malison&lt;/a&gt; and other disabling, offensive damage spell casts. Summoned help is also likely, and especially if she is a conjurer."}
{"id": "55922", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55922", "title": "Tiefling (Thief)", "text": "The Tiefling (Thief) is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; when traveling through a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Tieflings%20%28AR3005%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Tieflings (AR3005)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThis Tiefling is a Thief with an assassin kit that will empower its &lt;a href=\"Assassination\"&gt;Assassination&lt;/a&gt; ability when an enemy is detected, and then attempt to either attempt a Hide in Shadows (100% skill) or use a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; to achieve hidden status and then move forward and attack the nearest opponent. \nThis may achieve a &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; attack with a X6 multiplier.\nThe Thief may also apply its &lt;a href=\"Avoid%20Death\"&gt;Avoid Death&lt;/a&gt; ability during battle as well.\nThe creature wields a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword%20%2B2\"&gt;Short Sword +2&lt;/a&gt; in the main hand, and a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B2\"&gt;Dagger +2&lt;/a&gt; in the offhand, although its &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; penalty for \"dual-wielding\" is a factor and accounted for in the InfoBox, as well as its racial Tiefling THAC0 modifier.\nIf the Tiefling is wounded to 50% of its hit points, it will consume a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Superior%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Superior Healing&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis creature is scripted to use its Detect Illusion ability, but it will probably be defeated and dead well before it ever gets to that script timer to even try.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature slightly with a new AI script for improved tactical function. \nThe Assassin's XP level is raised to 24. A further &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; damage +2 modifier is added, so as an Assassin kit it receives a higher backstab damage modifier.\nThe assassin uses potions of invisibility to attain hidden status.\nSCS changes the creatures weapon proficiencies in Short Sword to 1 pip, and 1 pip in single weapon fighting style, which is correct by rule for a Thief/assassin.\nSCS also goes with a single Short Sword +2 and removes the off-hand dagger use. SCS uses the same &lt;a href=\"Assassination\"&gt;Assassination&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Avoid%20Death\"&gt;Avoid Death&lt;/a&gt; abilities.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod installed (with or without SCS) then this assassin is scripted to use that mod's revised assassin abilities, to include \"\"Assassin Poison\" and \"Death Attack\"\"."}
{"id": "56052", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56052", "title": "Tiefling Cleric (Aesgareth)", "text": "The Tiefling (Cleric) is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; when traveling through a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Aesgareth%20%28AR3015%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Aesgareth (AR3015)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis female servant of the cambion &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; is neutral when first encountered. It is possible to converse with the tiefling if desired, although discussion is limited in scope.\nThis Tiefling is a cleric that will favor divine spell casting as its first choice in combat but can still lay a few licks with its mace.\nThe creature wields the &lt;a href=\"Skullcrusher\"&gt;Skullcrusher&lt;/a&gt; for melee combat, and a &lt;a href=\"Sling%20%2B1\"&gt;Sling +1&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bullet%20%2B3\"&gt;Bullet +3&lt;/a&gt; ammunition for missile fire. \nIf made hostile, the cleric will be able to initiate a chain of protective spells.\nHer scripted spell casting actions are summarized in the InfoBox.\nIf this cleric survives initial contact, expect a &lt;a href=\"Creeping%20Doom\"&gt;Creeping Doom&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Insect%20Plague\"&gt;Insect Plague&lt;/a&gt; attempt at the beginning stage of the battle.\nThis cleric is scripted to help allies at certain wounded status thresholds and if they are shouting for assistance.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature moderately with a new smarter AI script for improved targeting and situational awareness. The mod raises the cleric's XP level to 25. Just about every divine spell is in this cleric's spell casting repertoire. Spells are cast at target's who generally aren't immune or protected. A substitute target or another spell is utilized if a target is immune.\nWill self-protect with an extensive blanket of spell buffs, including: &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nAn &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20Servant\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt; will also be summoned right away, and possibly aimed to manifest next to a party member.\nThe cleric is scripted to recognize damaged allies and heal them and or self and try to cure certain status effects. Cloud spells may be blown away with &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt;.\nDepending on the player's mod difficulty selection, the cleric can attempt &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fallen%20Deva\"&gt;Summon Fallen Deva&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Implosion\"&gt;Implosion&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56047", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56047", "title": "Tiefling Fighter (Aesgareth)", "text": "The Tiefling (Fighter) is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; when traveling through a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Aesgareth%20%28AR3015%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Aesgareth (AR3015)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis servant of the cambion &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; is neutral when first encountered. It is possible to converse with the tiefling if desired, although discussion is limited in scope.\nThis tiefling is a male fighter that will favor missile bow fire attacks as its first choice in combat.\nThe creature wields a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow%20%2B2\"&gt;Composite Longbow +2&lt;/a&gt; and fires &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B3\"&gt;Arrow +3&lt;/a&gt; ammunition. \nIt will initiate its innate &lt;a href=\"Called%20Shot\"&gt;Called Shot&lt;/a&gt; ability when using it's bow attacks and can do so up to 3 times.\nIf the fighter is pressed and cornered in close quarters combat, it switches to its melee weapon, equivalent to a &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword%20%2B3\"&gt;Long Sword +3&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe fighter is scripted to quaff potions for boosting abilities and to heal damage.\nIt will probably apply an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; when an enemy creature is detected.\nIf the creature is hit by any &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; it will quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Fire Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the tiefling is wounded to 50% of its hit points, it will consume a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Superior%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Superior Healing&lt;/a&gt; and can do this more than once.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature slightly with a new Fighter AI script for improved tactical awareness. \nSCS changes the creature's weapon proficiencies to 5 pips in both weapons, and 1 pip in single weapon fighting style.\nSCS also adds scripted use of &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20Attack\"&gt;Power Attack&lt;/a&gt; but doesn't use the Called Shot ability (which in SCS is for the Archer kit only)."}
{"id": "56050", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56050", "title": "Tiefling Mage (Aesgareth)", "text": "The Tiefling (Mage) is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; when traveling through a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Aesgareth%20%28AR3015%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Aesgareth (AR3015)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis female servant of the cambion &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; is neutral when first encountered. It is possible to converse with the tiefling if desired, although discussion is limited in scope.\nThis Tiefling is a mage that will favor spell casting as its first choice in combat.\nThe creature wields a &lt;a href=\"Cleric%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Cleric's Staff&lt;/a&gt; for melee combat, and a &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20the%20Good%20Archmagi\"&gt;Robe of the Good Archmagi&lt;/a&gt; for protection. \nIf made hostile, the mage will initially be able to initiate a chain of protective spells.\nHer scripted spell casting actions are summarized in the InfoBox.\nSome of this mage's AoE spells can and will damage allies. She doesn't seem to hold back with a Sunfire, lightning bolt or fireball.\nThis mage summons no help and doesn't use any spell removing magic.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature moderately with a new smarter AI script for improved targeting and situational awareness. The mod raises the mage's XP level to 25, and assigns a random speciality kit (Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer), which affects how her spell book is populated.\nWill self-protect with an extensive blanket of spell buffs, rendering the mage mostly immune to all attacks, and will be under a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; with Non-Detection with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, meaning she can't be seen or targeted. The player will have to either dispel everything (although with SR she'll also be protected with a \"Dispelling Screen\", which will stop one Dispel magic effect/Breach).\nThe mage also has a prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; which are scripted to instantly release.\nShe can take down a character's protections with &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spellstrike\"&gt;Spellstrike&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe might get off a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, coupled with &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Alacrity\"&gt;Improved Alacrity&lt;/a&gt; and try an &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Planetar&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56054", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56054", "title": "Tiefling Thief (Aesgareth)", "text": "The Tiefling (Thief) is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; when traveling through a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Aesgareth%20%28AR3015%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Aesgareth (AR3015)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis servant of the cambion &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; is neutral when first encountered. It is possible to converse with the tiefling if desired, although discussion is limited in scope.\nThis tiefling is a male thief with an Assassin kit that will favor melee attacks, from invisibility if possible.\nThe creature wields a &lt;a href=\"TELSWD.ITM\"&gt;Long sword +3&lt;/a&gt; in the main hand, and a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B2\"&gt;Dagger +2&lt;/a&gt; in the off hand. \nThis thief will try and attain invisibility at the outset of battle, and routinely use a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; before and after it attacks or if he has been revealed by divination magic/skill. \nThe thief is scripted to first select mage class characters for targeting once it is invisible.\nIt can also attempt to hide using its averaged Hide in Shadows/Move Silently skill, but it will move away from the nearest enemy it can detect before trying. The hide script may trigger even when the the creature is still neutral, and the party may notice this creature disappearing and reappearing from view on a sporadic basis before any hostilities begin.\nIf the tiefling is wounded to 50% of its hit points, it will consume a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Superior%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Superior Healing&lt;/a&gt; and can do this more than once.\nTrying to steal from this thief is possible, but the party rogue will be penalized by this creature's own skill level, which is 135%. Failure will turn the cambion and tieflings hostile.\nNote.\nThe creature has an assigned assassin kit, but the creature file is not coded to correctly apply the kit's passive bonuses. The creature will not &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; with a X6 damage modifier, but a X5 modifier as a normal thief.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature slightly with a new Assassin AI script for improved tactical awareness. \nSCS changes the creature's weapon proficiencies to 1 pip in long sword and 1 pip in single-weapon fighting style. It also gets rid of the Dagger +2, and no longer has any two-weapon fighting going on. \nSCS also adds scripted use of the &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Weapon\"&gt;Poison Weapon&lt;/a&gt; skill and adds all the passive assassin kit modifiers necessary for the creature to implement the kit's abilities.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed (with or without SCS), this assassin will get a +1 &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; damage multiplier, and use of the mod's \"Assassin Poison\" and \"Death Attack\" skills."}
