{"id": "34308", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34308", "title": "Tinderbox (Siege of Dragonspear)", "text": "This Tinderbox can be found in a troll-filled cavern in the Troll Claw Woods and can be used to uncover a hidden cache of items if you have a party member with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Infravision\"&gt;Infravision&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0that can see the place to use it."}
{"id": "27815", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27815", "title": "Tinderbox (Throne of Bhaal)", "text": "The \"Tinderbox\" is a plot item and can be found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; during or .\nGameplay.\nThis item is part of a necessary step to advance the &lt;a href=\"Open%20the%20portal%20to%20the%20temple%27s%20lower%20levels\"&gt;Open the portal to the temple's lower levels&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nThe item is in a trapped and locked alcove behind a statuette in the bedchamber south of the Crypt.\nIt's needed to ignite the fireplace in the northwestern Kitchen. Using the tinderbox will result in another encounter with &lt;a href=\"Archivist%20Giltham\"&gt;Archivist Giltham&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nPerhaps the loading screen's hint that \"your character doesn't need to eat\", the Tinderbox serves to lend weight to a supposition that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; doesn't carry the necessary implements to start a fire and cook food."}
{"id": "7973", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7973", "title": "Tipian", "text": "Tipian is one of many slaves found in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; during \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He's one of the seemingly weaker slaves, as a dialogue option for &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; includes beckoning him towards the surface. Otherwise, the player may ask about the mine, in which case Tipian will serve as yet another informer regarding &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; - an apparent mage.\nDialogue.\n\"What's going on? You're not our captors...\""}
{"id": "15564", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15564", "title": "Tirdir", "text": "Tirdir is a kidnapping victim found at the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen walking through the Graveyard District you might eventually see an open grave near the Northeastern District Exit. You will \"hear\" a \"moaning\" coming from the grave area, which is to say, Floating Text (and a Status Message if the \"Duplicate Floating Text\" option is enabled):\"Nearby you see an open grave. A chill runs up your spine as you hear a sound emit from it. You shake your head and continue walking. The sound is clearer now. You are not imagining it. Muffled cries for help are coming from the grave.\"Investigating the grave (by hovering the mouse over it and clicking) will lead to the protagonist helping Tirdir climb out of the grave.\"The grave is only partially filled. The grave keeper must be lazy. Within a few minutes you have reached the coffin. You open it to find a corpse and a man who is quite obviously alive. You help him out of the coffin.\"The unfortunate man claims he was attacked by unknown assailants, drugged and then dragged to this area, where he was left for dead in the grave.\nTirdir doesn't know his attackers but he has some clues to their identity: a &lt;a href=\"Piece%20of%20Red%20Cloth\"&gt;piece of cloth&lt;/a&gt; he tore from one of the kidnappers and the faint memory of having heard them talk to the &lt;a href=\"Sethle\"&gt;Grave keeper&lt;/a&gt;.\nRelated Quests.\nTalking to Tirdir initiates the eponymous quest, &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20kidnappers%20who%20buried%20Tirdir\"&gt;Find the kidnappers who buried Tirdir&lt;/a&gt;."}
