{"id": "48899", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48899", "title": "Toady", "text": "Toady is a &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; appearing in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nGameplay.\nThis diminutive well-dressed fellow is part of &lt;a href=\"Pehllus%20Tanislove\"&gt;Pehllus Tanislove's&lt;/a&gt; retinue. If in conversation with the nobleman, Toady, will politely interject and attempt to interpret what the lord says, softening the often insensitive and demeaning tone of his superior.\nToady is subservient and overtly obsequious, akin to a lapdog, and living up to his actual name."}
{"id": "48738", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48738", "title": "Togan", "text": "Togan is a vicious, cannibalistic Halfling &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Athas\"&gt;Athas&lt;/a&gt; who has been abducted along with his fellow halflings and now resides within the &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere%23The%20Caverns\"&gt;Caverns&lt;/a&gt; inside of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nUpon first sighting the party, he grins, then joins his fellow halflings in the next cavern. The party sees this status message:\"A bloodied halfling sits, chewing on a human leg bone still partially covered by dirty leather armor. It looks up, smiles, and says 'More to feast!'\"Along with his fellows, &lt;a href=\"Kayardi\"&gt;Kayardi&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mogadish\"&gt;Mogadish&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Entu\"&gt;Entu&lt;/a&gt;, Togan can present even a high-level party with quite a challenge.\nTogan will focus his attack efforts by using his magical Composite Longbow and arrows in missile combat, until forced to engage in melee.\nNotes.\nAs Togan has no proficiency with \"Spiked Weapons\" and instead is assigned \"Blunt weapons\" proficiency, he is somewhat ineffectual in melee combat with the Morning Star. Probably a developer misassigned data error.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature with a new default AI script, for smarter tactical behavior. The weapon proficiencies are changed to Morningstar/Flail and given 3 pips. Longbow proficiency is changed to 5 pips. This will improve the fighters THAC0, APR and damage output. As the creature has a fighter class, the Strength has been changed to 18/82, also providing extra melee attack benefits. The mod has basically fixed all the creature errors."}
{"id": "53744", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53744", "title": "Token Machine", "text": "This page is for advance information about the Token Machine located in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%203\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 3&lt;/a&gt; and part of saga. \nIt is separated from the main area article in case the player did not wish to know ahead of normal gameplay how many &lt;a href=\"Mithral%20Token\"&gt;Mithral Token&lt;/a&gt; coins are needed to receive a particular item or items.\nThe game does not tell the player this information through gameplay, and thus only trial and experimentation will reveal the machine's capabilities."}
