{"id": "2612", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2612", "title": "Tolerating Noober", "text": ""}
{"id": "6669", "revid": "284957", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6669", "title": "Tolgerias", "text": "Tolgerias is a &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizard&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; who is found in the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Six%20Building\"&gt;Council of Six Building&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; looking for mercenaries eager to do some bounty hunting for him.\nInvolvement.\nWhen first met, Tolgerias will try to hire &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; for a &lt;a href=\"The%20hunt%20for%20Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;mysterious mission&lt;/a&gt;. He will refuse to disclose any details before Gorion's Ward accepts to fulfill a contract for a predefined sum of gold. The quest will only begin if Gorion's Ward accepts the Cowled Wizard's terms.\nShould Gorion's Ward accept the contract, Tolgerias will ask the party to find, kill &lt;a href=\"Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; and bring his body to him. The wizard will never reveal why he wants Valygar dead, but the &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt; will reveal that Tolgerias believes it is the only way to gain entry to &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party decides to spare Valygar's life and enters the Sphere at any point after that, Tolgerias will be encountered in the depths of the Sphere and confront the party.\nGameplay.\nIf somehow the party has made Tolgerias hostile in the Council of Six building, then most likely the entire cast of NPCs within will also become hostile, leading to a huge debacle and lowering the party's reputation very low. Tolgerias, if not killed outright will fight back as detailed a little further on.\nMost probably, the party will encounter Tolgerias, and his assistant mage (a level 9 Female elven mage - ref: TOLMAGE02) within the Planar Sphere (the Power Core room) - see the &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Inside the Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; page. Regardless of whether the party has added Valygar Corthala as a companion or not, Tolgerias and lackey mage will inevitably turn hostile to the party, and a fight could break out.\nAssuming that Tolgerias is not killed or made helpless before he can launch his defenses, then expect the mage to near instantly self-protect with &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Electricity%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Protection From Electricity (spell)&lt;/a&gt;.\nNext a &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Simulacrum\"&gt;Simulacrum&lt;/a&gt; and then &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted. From then on, the battle will shift depending on certain recognized threats in his script. Most likely Tolgerias will then go on the offensive and start casting various offensive damage spells and disabling types. A &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; can be cast to banish summoned foes, and a &lt;a href=\"Vocalize\"&gt;Vocalize&lt;/a&gt; is ready to counter silence. \nHis mage assistant will also be getting up some magical defenses and then try and attack via spell casting as well.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises Tolgerias (and his assistant mage in the Planar Sphere) assigns a default \"Smarter Mages SCS AI for improved tactical behavior and spell casting. A different arsenal of spells is memorized, and the mage will utilize his already prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; during hostilities. Tolgerias may be assigned a Conjurer kit, and the female elven mage lackey an Enchanter kit. \nAs a level 21 mage, SCS ensures that Tolgerias has access to a few &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; innate ability uses, as well as a handful of 9th level spells. These will be used dependent on the game difficulty setting. \nWhen confronted in the Planar Sphere, after his opening dialogue (unless snuffed out by a hidden party member before that), Tolgerias will have the following {previously cast) buffs: &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Mestil's Acid Sheath\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt;).\nTolgerias assistant Mage buffs with &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI: Divination&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Armor (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;.\nTolgerias will quickly summon and conjure assistance in this battle. Expect two Fiends (&lt;a href=\"Cornugon\"&gt;Cornugon&lt;/a&gt;), two &lt;a href=\"Efreeti\"&gt;Efreeti&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Djinni\"&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps other creatures to deal with.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, the mages spells will be the SR versions, and the summoned spell casting creatures will also be using the SR versions.\nIf you want Tolgerias to have possession of a special book, install the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Summoning%20Ritual%20-%20Unholy%20Gate%20Opening%20Ritual%20Book\"&gt;Demon Summoning Ritual - Unholy Gate Opening Ritual Book&lt;/a&gt;. He won't have it until he is in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;, and you'll have to take it from him by force. Usable by evil Mage class only. Read more in the link."}
{"id": "48012", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48012", "title": "Tolmas Bendelia", "text": "Tolmas Bendelia is an influential local merchant who is involved in one of the problem's-to-be-solved cut scenes that take place if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has met the &lt;a href=\"class\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; qualifications to take on the &lt;a href=\"The%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20has%20been%20Invaded\"&gt;liberated&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"de%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt;.\nMister Bendelia is a mite bit upset that his latest caravan was waylaid by bandits. He has the temerity to demand restitution, or he shall forswear traveling through the surrounding lands again, which will limit the availability of goods for the locals. It appears that he is also a substantial lender of sorts to numerous farms throughout the region and threatens to foreclose on all the farms that he holds a deed to.\nSolving the problems by spending gold will make the locals happy and gain the party XP, while ignoring the issue will give the locals pause and they may begin to contemplate revolt."}
