{"id": "48020", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48020", "title": "TorGal", "text": "TorGal is the leader of the Rocksmash pack of &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt;s that attacks and invades the &lt;a href=\"de%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt;. He is found in the sanctuary that's located in the cellar of the keep, along with two more &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Troll\"&gt;Giant Troll&lt;/a&gt;s and the corpse of &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia's&lt;/a&gt; father, Lord de'Arnise.\nLimited conversation reveals that the trolls made a deal with an outside source named \"Stronger\" to invade the keep. And this Stronger paid off the majority of the other guards with gold to abandon their posts and leave. But TorGal won't reveal any other information about who this Stronger might be.\nGameplay.\nTorGal is a powerful creature, with a fair number of immunities and resistances. He has an effective melee attack that can inflict significant damage. Take care when engaging in close combat with this one. \nAside from the damage output of its melee attack, whenever a strike lands the target must save vs. Death with a -4 penalty or be inflicted with a &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt; lasting 10 seconds, or a -1 point of strength drain which lasts 1 turn. There is a 50-50 chance of each. The strength drain can be additive with multiple hits. &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block these effects, and they can be dispelled as well. Torgal's melee weapon also furnishes him &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt; and strikes as a +3 enchanted item.\nDialogue (w/ Nalia only).\n\"CowardalRrrrr, you no fight? We come to fight! Stronger ask for things, but we fight anyway! You worthlessrrr if you gerrtragg no fight! What good you?!\"\n\"Your words are fancy like Stronger, but he pay in meat and land! You not strong in pay like him! Should have left with gold like other small grrthed guards!\"\nMod content.\nMods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises TorGal. \nThe SCS Torgal script is revised to bring in additional help, which is affected by the game difficulty setting. For example, on Hardcore or Insane, Torgal will be present with two &lt;a href=\"Yuan-ti%20Mage\"&gt;Yuan-ti Mage&lt;/a&gt;s, and an &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;Umber Hulk&lt;/a&gt; Elder. This is in addition to whatever other creatures are added if you have installed the \"Improved de'Arnise Keep\" component. That component adds more regular &lt;a href=\"Troll\"&gt;Troll&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Troll\"&gt;Giant Troll&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Troll\"&gt;Spirit Troll&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Spectral%20Troll\"&gt;Spectral Troll&lt;/a&gt;s. With TorGal in the final battle, you can expect three Giant Trolls, three Spirit Trolls (they will start off invisible) and a Spectral Troll, plus the Yuan-ti Mages and Umber Hulk (Elder)."}
