{"id": "41479", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41479", "title": "Torsin de Lancie", "text": "Torsin Cedric de Lancie, more commonly referred to as simply \"Torsin de Lancie\", is the representative leader of the forces of &lt;a href=\"Waterdeep\"&gt;Waterdeep&lt;/a&gt; in the Coalition against the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt;. Counterpart to &lt;a href=\"Marshal%20Nederlok\"&gt;Marshal Kyrill Nederlok&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"General%20Stonehand\"&gt;General Haither Stonehand&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Daggerford\"&gt;Daggerford&lt;/a&gt;, he is regarded with disdain by his fellow leaders. A deeply unpleasant fellow, de Lancie is arrogant and demanding, quick to try and exploit the size of Waterdeep's contributions as an excuse to wield more power in the alliance, he is also a coward who tries to avoid actually committing his forces unless he can't avoid them. Incredibly ambitious, he has few scruples and is willing to stoop to considerable lows in order to achieve his goals."}
{"id": "55323", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55323", "title": "Tot", "text": "Tot is Jan's young nephew. Tot and his sister &lt;a href=\"Tat\"&gt;Tat&lt;/a&gt; are seen and heard as part of the &lt;a href=\"Jan%20Jansen%20Summoned%20Home\"&gt;Jan Jansen Summoned Home&lt;/a&gt; questline when first entering the Jansen home.\nGameplay.\nHe and his sister are excited to see Jan return, and the two siblings shout in glee - arguing and playfully scampering about.\nTot wants to have fun and \"flash\" his sister's kitty and she doesn't want him to do that. \nThe party can speak to him if they wish.\nHe and his sister are provided as actors to spice up the storyline. Harming these children counts as attacking an innocent, so expect up a -10 &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; loss if one of them is killed."}
