{"id": "45099", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45099", "title": "Tourist", "text": "When you agree to take &lt;a href=\"Ike%27s%20Guided%20Tour\"&gt;Ike's Guided Tour&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;, your tour group will consist of the party and three Tourists. They can be found standing inside the foyer as you first enter the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Ground%20Floor%29\"&gt;ground floor&lt;/a&gt; of the tower. The tourists don't move and provide some very limited dialogue if you attempt to speak to them, while Ike walks around the foyer, giving his (probably well memorized) spiel about the cruel history and unfathomable dangers of the tower.\nAfter his fourth dialogue line about the tower, he tells the group that it's time to take a small break and implores everyone to \"TOUCH NOTHING!\nOnce Ike finishes speaking, one of the tourists (called Francis or known as tourist 1 in the game mechanics) will wander off towards an open doorway, triggering an unseen trap that unleashes a column of flame which instantly kills him.\nWhen you talk to Ike again after this unfortunate incident, he'll offer to sell you an authentic wardstone that will allow the party to reach the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Three%29\"&gt;third level&lt;/a&gt; of the labyrinth of dungeons located beneath the tower. The ensuing, brief dialogue choices all end with the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Knight\"&gt;Demon Knight&lt;/a&gt; instantly teleporting into the foyer and informing everyone present that the tower is now his and that the tour is now over. He then proceeds to conjure up a couple of fireballs, killing Ike and the remaining two tourists, and immediately teleports out. This brings Ike's guided tour, and the lives of a huckster and three peasants, to an abrupt end."}
{"id": "49499", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49499", "title": "Tower of Deception", "text": "The Tower of Deception mod is an older quest mod that provides a self-contained small adventure to a tower out at sea.\nStatus.\nThe original author is no longer maintaining it, but other modders have updated it, made it compatible with and &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition%20Trilogy\"&gt;EET&lt;/a&gt;, and keep it available on Github to download. Please note that there is also an unofficial repository on github: the Infinity Mods download linked in the infobox should be considered the authoritative version.\nOverview.\nThe Mod begins in the &lt;a href=\"Crooked%20Crane%20Inn\"&gt;Crooked Crane Inn&lt;/a&gt; in Athkatla. Speak with Tian the Mage in the Inn's main pub area. Tian will ask for help and attempt to hire your Party to obtain a special Spellbook owned by an Arch Mage named Ustrain. If you accept, then the adventure will begin, and you will be transported to a shore area where a Captain Kergo will ferry you to a small Island - on which sits the Tower of Deception. Your quest and hunted book are inside, somewhere.\nOptional sequel (separate mod component) \"Encounter with Ustrain\". The owner of the tower tracks the party down after some time and ambushes them during rest. The sequel is just a high-level tactical encounter that may give the party excessive XP and some powerful (overpowered for some) loot. The sequel does not add content to the plot otherwise.\nFor more information see the links.\nCharacters.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
