{"id": "40607", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40607", "title": "Tree of Life", "text": "The Tree of Life is an area reachable only during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe party must first pass through &lt;a href=\"The%20Palace\"&gt;The Palace&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt; before transitioning to this area, by way of a revealed staircase.\nDescription.\nThis area depicts a part of the Forest of Tethir below the platforms of Suldanessellar, but still elevated above ground level. The ancient Tree of Life stretches massive branches in all directions, both vertically and horizontally. For the purposes of party movement (and gravity) the gameplay here is focused on the branches that are horizontal and can be moved upon by foot.\nThe artwork of the map indicates that smaller trees and undergrowth are visible at lower elevations below the Tree of Life, so it is likely that the party is still over a hundred feet from the forest floor below.\nThis area is technically considered an outdoor area and is subject to the effects on daylight and nighttime. Resting/camping can occur here, with no disturbances from attacking creatures.\nGameplay.\nEnter the Tree of Life.\nThe party descends stairs revealed in The Palace, previously hidden at the bottom of a pool of water.\nThey appear in the northeast corner of the Tree of Life map on a staircase formed from a tree trunk.\nWithin detection range is seen a blurred image of &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt; to the west of the arrival point.\nConverse with Ellesime's image.\nA few seconds after arrival, &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt;, seen as a blurred image of herself and projected by her magic and will - initiates dialogue, she says:\nGorion's Ward may reply. Ellesime will continue:\nThe ward asks about the parasites, the Queen replies:\nThe PC asks how to find the parasites, Ellesime answers:\nWith that the image fades, and the player's Journal updates with the &lt;a href=\"Freeing%20Queen%20Ellesime\"&gt;Freeing Queen Ellesime&lt;/a&gt; questline - which reads:\nFind and destroy the parasites.\nThe party can now begin exploring the branches and look for anything out of place, especially any \"parasites\" that are supposedly somewhere sapping the Tree of Life of its vigor and vitality.\nThe party can go any direction it wishes. It doesn't matter really - and visual indicators that may seem to be gaps in the tree branches may be crossable as long as the party has the &lt;a href=\"Small%20Tree%20of%20Life%20Nut\"&gt;Small Tree of Life Nut&lt;/a&gt; items in their inventory. If the player doesn't have these nuts, then they won't be able to complete the game properly.\nAs the Queen has previously stated, they will facilitate a hyper growth branch repair at sections that are eligible for that action. \nThis effect will happen automatically by the game engine script - and a text message will be displayed indicating when it occurs. \nEach time it happens, one of the small nuts is consumed. The player can just control the party's movement and move forward as normal without having to worry about falling to their death or similar.\nIrenicus and Ellesime in a cage.\nAs the party explores, it is possible that they will come upon Irenicus and Ellemise (who is in a cage) on a small platform. \nThis can occur before any parasites are found. Irenicus is seemly oblivious and in a trance of some sort - unaffected by the outside world and within a protective magic shell of unknown power. The tree's life force is being drawn out by the parasites and funneled to Jon. He doesn't react to the party, and no attacks will do anything to him (immune to all arcane and divine spells and most damage types). \nIf the party tries to select to talk with Irenicus a text displays:\nEllesime cannot be spoken to in her cage either. For now, the party can safely resume their exploration for the parasites.\nA parasite is located.\nNavigating the tree branches will lead to discovering a strange object as shown in the screenshot.\nEvery few seconds an \"Acid Attack\" animation plays next to it, indicating the parasite is damaging and draining the Tree of Life.\nThe parasite can be targeted with the player's \"sword/attack\" icon. If the attack is commenced, a message is displayed on the information box:\nA second attack generates and another text message:\nThe guardians appear adjacent to the parasite and will be a pair of 12-HD elementals, either Air, Earth or Fire variety depending on which parasite is attacked.\nWhen the elementals are destroyed, attack the parasite again. This displays a final message:\nThat's all there is to the process of destroying one of the three parasites on the tree.\nDestroy all three parasites.\nAfter destruction of the second parasite, Ellesime's projected image appears by the party and speaks some encouragement and warning to continue and to make haste.\nThe player's Journal now updates the &lt;a href=\"Freeing%20Queen%20Ellesime\"&gt;Freeing Queen Ellesime&lt;/a&gt; quest, and a text displays:\nOnce the third and final parasite is destroyed, the game script takes over and transfers the party to the central platform with Irenicus and Ellesime in her cage.\nIrenicus is interrupted.\nThe player's party is positioned near Irenicus and Ellesime is now outside her cage. Irenicus is surprised and says:\nMore dialogue continues, and eventually Ellesime enters the with her remarks. Jon and the queen have a back-and-forth exchange, revealing more background regarding Jon's ties to the elven court, and the lost love connection between he and Ellesime.\nLater in the dialogue Imoen, Jaheria and Minsc (if they are in the party) have their own interjections.\nEllesime disappears from the map now that she has been freed and is done with her dialogue with Irenicus. The player's Journal updates the &lt;a href=\"Freeing%20Queen%20Ellesime\"&gt;Freeing Queen Ellesime&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nJon eventually reverts back to his unrepented self, with only revenge left as his driving purpose, and says:\nBattle Irenicus on the Tree of Life.\nJon is scripted to \"Applyspell\" command an initial preparatory string of protective buffs (even if damaged it won't be interrupted).\nFor a more in-depth look at of this version of Irenicus, see the &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus%20%28Tree%20of%20Life%29\"&gt;Jon Irenicus (Tree of Life)&lt;/a&gt; article.\nAssuming the protagonist and party are able to get Jon to one Hit Point, he will make a final incredulous remark about being killed.\nGorion's Ward will now show several introspective dialogue boxes that describe a strange sensation and realization that something weird is occurring.\nThe incessant tug and pull of the force draws Gorion's Ward and the party into the void.\nA cinematic cut scene will take over - eventually culminating with the party transported to &lt;a href=\"The%20Abyss\"&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt; area. See that page for what transpires next.\nContainers.\nA small nonvisible niche is located right at the area entrance stairs. A rich &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt; is within for the taking.\nBug.\nThe Irenicus version that is found within his magical shell was clearly designed to be mostly impervious to being killed. But there are some loopholes, and he can be killed if the player is determined to do so (verified by testing). This version of Irenicus is just for looks and animation at this point in the plot. \nHowever, if Irenicus is killed here, it will foul up the script that triggers opening dialogue between the party, Ellesime and Jon Irenicus (and everything following that). This will mean the game can't progress properly. The player's game will essentially end right here with no further developments happening. So, don't break your game. Wait for the scripted dialogue between the party, Ellesime and Irenicus to play out, and allow Jon to turn hostile before attacking him."}
