{"id": "34816", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34816", "title": "Tunic of Blindeye", "text": "Tunic of Blindeye is a robe (or rather a tunic), without any armor class or saving throw bonuses. Instead it increases movement rate by 2, provides +25% magic damage resistance and allows the user to cast Wildzone, an ability that creates a 15' radius area (duration: 10 rounds) where any creature must save vs spell every round or have their spells cause &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge\"&gt;Wild Surges&lt;/a&gt; for the next 7 seconds (ie a full round + 1 second).\nThe Wildzone ability is considered nonmagical, therefore, it bypasses magic resistance and its effects can't be dispelled. Plus, despite the fact most Conjurers can't wear this item, it is considered a Conjuration, so a Conjurer dualed to Thief who wears this tunic via Use Any Item inflicts a penalty of 2 to saves against it.\nLocation.\nCan be bought from &lt;a href=\"Gul%20Dukeem\"&gt;Gul Dukeem&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Neera%27s%20Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Neera's Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt; quest."}
