{"id": "14090", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14090", "title": "Twinkle", "text": "Twinkle +3, also known as Scimitar +5, Defender in the original games, is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"scimitar\"&gt;scimitar&lt;/a&gt;, wielded by the famous hero &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; who appears in (SoA)(SoA). The Scimitar is labelled as a \"Twinkle +3\" in the EE games, yet it still has a +5 Enchantment value in terms of what it can strike.\nOnly creatures of Good &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; can use Twinkle.\nAcquisition.\nTake the weapon from Drizzt's corpse."}
{"id": "20085", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20085", "title": "Twinkle +3", "text": ""}
{"id": "7455", "revid": "279027", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7455", "title": "Twisted Rune", "text": "The Twisted Rune is a secret organization of undead and human evil spellcasters, operating in southern &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;. and controlled by eight rune masters.\nIn , &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has several encounters with this organization. During the quest &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; you chase &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Reijek&lt;/a&gt; the skinner and the mage &lt;a href=\"Vellin%20Dahn\"&gt;Vellin Dahn&lt;/a&gt;, who escape you with the help of &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Assassin\"&gt;Rune Assassins&lt;/a&gt;. Following a hint found in the skinners house, you search for another of &lt;a href=\"Find%20Rejiek%27s%20ally\"&gt;Reijek's allies&lt;/a&gt; in the Umar Hills. \nThere you can obtain the quest to &lt;a href=\"finish%20the%20leather%20armor%20begun%20by%20Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;finish the leather armor begun by Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt;, which involves killing a good aligned Silver Dragon in the Underdark. \nFinally, you find and kill Rejiek in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Tradesmeet&lt;/a&gt; during the quest &lt;a href=\"Helping%20Tiris%20in%20Trademeet\"&gt;Helping Tiris in Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;. \nDuring the companion quest &lt;a href=\"Cernd%27s%20Child\"&gt;Cernd's Child&lt;/a&gt; you stumble over the &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lagole%20Gon\"&gt;Lagole Gon&lt;/a&gt; recruiting the evil mage &lt;a href=\"Deril\"&gt;Deril&lt;/a&gt; for the Twisted Rune and with skill you manage to kill both and save the child. \nDuring your exploration of Atkhatlas &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; you find a &lt;a href=\"Guarded%20Compound\"&gt;guarded compound&lt;/a&gt; with strong and aggressive inhabitants, one of them the Kensai &lt;a href=\"Koshi\"&gt;Koshi&lt;/a&gt;, who, according to rumors, carried a special (non-stackable) &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Stone\"&gt;rogue stone&lt;/a&gt; with the inscription \"Come and find me\" (at least in some versions of the game). Without further hints the following step will happen only randomly (due to \"unfinished quest line design\" in order to meet release deadlines, as some fans state). \nThe final encounter with the Twisted Rune will be in their hideout, which you find accidentally having an arbitrary rogue stone (the special one is not needed) in your inventory while investigating a sinister house door near the &lt;a href=\"house%20of%20the%20Elemental%20Lich\"&gt;house of the Elemental Lich&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. The sinister house door turns out to be a portal that teleports you to their &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune%20Hideout\"&gt;hideout&lt;/a&gt;, where you find and kill two of the rune masters, the Lich &lt;a href=\"Shangalar\"&gt;Shangalar the Black&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampiress&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Shyressa\"&gt;Shyressa&lt;/a&gt;. According to Shangalars dialogue lines, the hideout is not in Athkatla and you have to find a way to teleport back.\nIn , &lt;a href=\"Balthazar\"&gt;Balthazar's&lt;/a&gt; mercenaries imply that he had been cooperating with members of this organization."}
{"id": "48550", "revid": "8506165", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48550", "title": "Twisted Rune Building", "text": ""}
{"id": "13135", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13135", "title": "Twisted Rune Hideout", "text": "The Twisted Rune Hideout is a secretive chamber accessible from the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20the%20Elemental%20Lich\"&gt;House of the Elemental Lich&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. It serves as a base of operations for the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\".\nThe entrance faces the water and is just around the corner from the door that leads to the crypt of the &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Lich%20%28Bridge%20District%29\"&gt;Elemental Lich&lt;/a&gt;. The trapped \"(&lt;a href=\"Find%20Traps%20%28skill%29\"&gt;80&lt;/a&gt; | Disintegrate)\" and locked door is really a portal and cannot be passed through without having a &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Stone\"&gt;Rogue Stone&lt;/a&gt; (which gets consumed by the portal) in your inventory.\nAlso, it's not possible to leave again without having to defeat the inhabitants first.\nGameplay.\nStumbling into the blackness for accidentally possessing a Rogue Stone while trying to enter this building, the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will find themselves in a small circular antechamber that connects to a larger circular room with a round table that offers seats for seven persons.\nSurprisingly, the entrance is not an exit, and when looking for one or trying to examine the symbol on the table, &lt;a href=\"Shangalar\"&gt;Shangalar&lt;/a&gt; a lich, will appear in the center of this \"rune\", stopping the party and interrogating them before finally summoning more members of the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt; to defeat the intruders, as follows:\nSee each rune members creature page for more details.\nThere are two items in the main chamber that can be examined. \nThe first is a cauldron, a text message displays on the combat log:\nThe second is an odd mechanical machine, and the following text displayed when its examined:\nThe clue on the cauldron will solve the how to move the lever on the machine - which seems to be the only way to leave this area. See spoiler guarded solution below if desired.\nInteract with the Cauldron while in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Beholder%20Eye\"&gt;Beholder Eye&lt;/a&gt;, and another text message displays.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises each creature found within the Hideout. Much improved scripting and intelligent use of their abilities over the unmodded game. &lt;a href=\"Revanek\"&gt;Revanek&lt;/a&gt; is now a fully armed and armored fighter. &lt;a href=\"Vaxall\"&gt;Vaxall&lt;/a&gt; is a spell casting &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Orb\"&gt;Elder Orb&lt;/a&gt; that can also use eye stalks. &lt;a href=\"Shyressa\"&gt;Shyressa&lt;/a&gt; is a Fighter/Thief &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Ancient%29\"&gt;Vampire (Ancient)&lt;/a&gt; with SCS vampire abilities. &lt;a href=\"Layene\"&gt;Layene&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shangalar\"&gt;Shangalar&lt;/a&gt; can and will use prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; activation. On \"Hardcore\" or \"Insane\" difficulty settings they can employ &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; mage powers. Expect at least three &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; spells between them.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod will change all twisted rune spell casts to the SR versions.\n&lt;a href=\"Tactics%20for%20BG2EE\"&gt;Tactics for BG2EE&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a number of changes to this encounter. It is mostly compatible with &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;SCS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt;. See SCS, Tactics and SR mod screenshots below. All three work together.\nSome add unofficial content to allow discovery of the Rune's entrance less of an accident. They are not available for the original \"Shadows of Amn\", however."}
