{"id": "4361", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4361", "title": "Ulcaster", "text": "Ulcaster is an area located to the southeast of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; and is notable for being the location where a school of wizardry once stood. The school was founded by the conjurer &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20of%20Ulcaster\"&gt;Ulcaster&lt;/a&gt;, who is now a ghost that wanders the ruins of the destroyed school.\nThe area is a mix of narrow and wide rocky scrub-lands interspersed with flat-topped, cliff-faced outcrops. The school ruins are located on a large grassy plateau that occupies the northeastern portion of the area. All of these raised areas are accessible by narrow, single file paths. There are a couple of ambushes in the zig-zag, switchback paths in the south, and unless pathing nodes are set to a high count, party members will walk away from the main party, sometimes three at a time. "}
{"id": "8899", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8899", "title": "Ulcaster's Dusty History Book", "text": "Ulcaster's Dusty History Book is a special copy of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Sisters%20of%20Light%20and%20Darkness\"&gt;History of the Sisters of Light and Darkness&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0found in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ulcaster%20Dungeon\"&gt;Ulcaster Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in the\u00a0\u00a0version of the game. In this version, it is the \"only\" book that will complete the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Tomes%20of%20Magic\"&gt;Tomes of Magic&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0side quest. It is found in a large pile of bodies at the heart of the dungeon (&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;1400.1050&lt;/a&gt;), protected by a &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Wolf\"&gt;Vampiric Wolf&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4362", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4362", "title": "Ulcaster Dungeon", "text": "Ulcaster Dungeon is an area with some decent loot, mostly things that can be purchased; it is loot that could never be found on the type of enemies faced. A &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; with a good find/disarm trap is recommended, and fire resistent items/spells as well. Because some enemies in this dungeon are immune to normal weapons, enchanted weapons/ammunition are necessary.\nIt is not really a maze as such; there is one diversion off to the mustard jellies to the East / right, and then an anti-clockwise route to the good loot at the end. Melee enemies that have every advantage in this setting, and are very hard for low levels. There are three fireball traps, any one of which could completely wipe out a low level party.\nMod content.\nWith \"&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG1\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG1&lt;/a&gt;\"| installed, a further creature is encountered, &lt;a href=\"Mal-Kalen\"&gt;Mal-Kalen&lt;/a&gt;, who brings his own quest."}
