{"id": "8666", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8666", "title": "Ulene", "text": "Ulene is a &lt;a href=\"dryad\"&gt;dryad&lt;/a&gt; found on the first floor of &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. She and two of her fellow dryads, &lt;a href=\"Elyme\"&gt;Elyme&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cania\"&gt;Cania&lt;/a&gt;, have been trapped by &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; in the Dryad Grotto that's located between Irenicus's master bedroom and &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt;'s bedroom. \nWhen you get near them, they will speak to you and &lt;a href=\"Helping%20Irenicus%27s%20captive%20dryads\"&gt;ask you to retrieve&lt;/a&gt; their &lt;a href=\"acorns\"&gt;acorns&lt;/a&gt; from the duergar clan leader &lt;a href=\"Ilyich\"&gt;Ilyich&lt;/a&gt; and give them to the &lt;a href=\"Vaelasa\"&gt;Fairy Queen&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area. Doing this will free the dryads from their captivity. If you kill the dryad instead, the Fairy Queen will know about this and attack you when she sees you.\nIf you have already &lt;a href=\"Free%20the%20Djinn\"&gt;dealt with the djinn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Malaaq\"&gt;Malaaq&lt;/a&gt; and are searching for his &lt;a href=\"The%20Genie%27s%20Flask\"&gt;flask&lt;/a&gt;, they will offer to give you the flask if you promise to take their acorns to the Fairy Queen."}
{"id": "8826", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8826", "title": "Ulf", "text": "Ulf is a &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League\"&gt;Merchants' League&lt;/a&gt; guard who can be found on the first floor in the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Counting%20House\"&gt;Merchants' League Counting House&lt;/a&gt; after having spoken to &lt;a href=\"Mendas\"&gt;Mendas&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party say the wrong things, he and several &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Counting%20House%20Guard\"&gt;guards&lt;/a&gt; will become hostile. Safe options are either telling him that your business with the Merchants' League is private or that you need to clear your debt for items purchased in &lt;a href=\"Kara-Tur\"&gt;Kara-Tur&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4499", "revid": "220250", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4499", "title": "Ulgoth's Beard", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt; is an area added by the expansion pack and many quests added by the expansion can be started here.\nGetting There.\nUlgoth's Beard appears on the world map northeast corner anytime Tales of the Sword Coast or the is installed, including during the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; Prologue.\nUlgoth's Beard\u00a0becomes an attainable destination when you reach Wyrm's Crossing.\nOther People.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Bartender\"&gt;Bartender&lt;/a&gt; in the inn is selling basic weapons and armor as well as a decent assortment of magical items, some of which are found nowhere else in the game.\n&lt;a href=\"Baresh\"&gt;Baresh&lt;/a&gt; will confront &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party upon their return from the Isle of Balduran.\n&lt;a href=\"Calahan\"&gt;Calahan&lt;/a&gt; is a fisherman in\u00a0Ulgoth's Beard\u00a0who will approach you after you talk to\u00a0Mendas. For 20 he will give you hints that Mendas may be a bit shady.\n&lt;a href=\"Cult%20Enforcer\"&gt;Cult Enforcer&lt;/a&gt;s will confront Gorion's Ward and party upon their return to Ulgoth's Beard while carrying the &lt;a href=\"Soultaker%20Dagger\"&gt;Soultaker Dagger&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Delsvirftanyon\"&gt;Delsvirftanyon&lt;/a&gt;, slightly south of center on the area map, announces that he is having a \"going out of business\" sale of his Durlag's Tower adventuring supplies business, and offers to sell you his remaining stock for 500. Sounds like a scam, but it's (mostly) not. You get &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Rune%20Wardstone\"&gt;Dwarven Rune Wardstone&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Leather Armor +1&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20Forgery\"&gt;Wardstone Forgery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Ring\"&gt;Gold Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Ring\"&gt;Silver Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Onyx%20Ring\"&gt;Onyx Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Necklace\"&gt;Silver Necklace&lt;/a&gt;. This shows up in your journal as a finished &lt;a href=\"A%20Curious%20Business%20Proposal\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Dushai\"&gt;Dushai&lt;/a&gt;, an old gnome who may offer to tell the party the story of &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt; if they expressed interest in the pursuit of knowledge while talking to Mendas.\n&lt;a href=\"Fenrus%20Boulon\"&gt;Fenrus Boulon&lt;/a&gt;, a nobleman by the docks in the southwest, will give you a lecture on the history\u00a0of Durlag's Tower. This shows up in your journal contributing to the Durlag's Tower &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28quest%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Galken\"&gt;Galken&lt;/a&gt;, a mage located in the inn, wants you to clear up his 900 tab with the innkeeper in return for a Dwarven Rune Wardstone that supposedly gives entry to the dungeons beneath Durlag's Tower. This shows up in your journal as a finished &lt;a href=\"Galken%27s%20Wardstone\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nBuildings.\nThere are also &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%29\"&gt;two locked homes&lt;/a&gt; on either side of the entrance to town."}
{"id": "4503", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4503", "title": "Ulgoth's Beard Inn", "text": "Ulgoth's Beard Inn is the only inn to be found in &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt;. The inn sells gear which can come in handy when exploring &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt; and magical items plundered from the tower as well. It also offers the normal services of renting rooms and serving drinks.\nLoot.\nThere are three lootable containers within the inn. The barrel in the kitchen is empty. The nightstand next to the bed in the small bedroom is locked and contains 52 . The armoire in the master bedroom is locked and contains 70 and a &lt;a href=\"War%20Hammer%20%2B1\"&gt;War Hammer +1&lt;/a&gt;.\nBuying and Selling.\nThis merchant sells items for 150% of their item value, if reputation and charisma have no effect, and buys them for 50% of their value if the item is not in stock.\nNote.\nThis store, the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Inn\"&gt;Candlekeep Inn&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Erdane\"&gt;Erdane&lt;/a&gt; are the only shops which sell &lt;a href=\"Scimitar\"&gt;Scimitar&lt;/a&gt;s throughout the adventure. However, this shop and Erdane are the only two which make this item available beginning in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt;, while the Candlekeep Inn can only be visited during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Wand of Frost&lt;/a&gt; that this store sells has 29 charges and the &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20the%20Heavens\"&gt;Wand of the Heavens&lt;/a&gt; has 25 charges. In comparison, those in &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt; contain 20 charges for both wand types. Partial recharge of those wands is cheaper per charge in this store by a small fraction of a gold piece."}
{"id": "25528", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25528", "title": "Ulitharid", "text": "A Ulitharid is a noble of society and is treated as a minor demi-god being by their lesser &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; brethren.\nUlitharids are also extremely rare within mind flayer enclaves; less than one in a hundred illithid tadpoles would develop into an ulitharid. Their rarity supports the reverence they receive from other illithids, who view them as a blessing and second only to the &lt;a href=\"The%20Master%20Brain\"&gt;The Master Brain&lt;/a&gt;. Their ego reflects their privileged position, as they view the common mind flayer as a lesser being.\nThe game plays fast and loose with the supposedly rarity factor of this creature. For example, in the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayers%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Mind Flayers in Underdark&lt;/a&gt; area there are at least five of them.\nLocations.\nUlitharids typically inhabit mind flayer lairs in various dungeons. They are usually accompanied by regular mind flayers and &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;umber hulks&lt;/a&gt;. They carry no gold nor any treasure, however the &lt;a href=\"Ulitharid%20%28Spellhold%29\"&gt;Ulitharid&lt;/a&gt; encountered in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%203\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 3&lt;/a&gt; will drop the &lt;a href=\"Flame%20of%20the%20North\"&gt;Flame of the North&lt;/a&gt; when defeated. The game will award different experience point values for different varieties of the Ulitharids encountered. The XP noted in the info box is for the fully implemented and common form.\nGameplay.\nUlitharids are an effectively more powerful version of the ordinary mind flayer. Ulitharids are able to force cast &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; upon themselves when their &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; level is reduced to 50 percent of their maximum HP. Ulitharids also have better stats \u2013 greater &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; value, better &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt;. In addition are fifty percent resistant to &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt;. Their movement rate is slightly faster than the ordinary illithid. These creatures are highly resistant to magic.\nA ulitharid also attacks with a 5 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; round (the ordinary Mind Flayer has 4). \nWhen an enemy is detected with current hit points at 25% of maximum, a &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt; spell will be attempted at that enemy.\nThe first &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; normally attempted is a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Domination\"&gt;Psionic Domination&lt;/a&gt; power, at the closest enemy detected. After that the &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt; ability is launched at targets, about every two rounds. If an enemy is in melee range, the ulitharid may attempt to strike with the \"devour brain\" melee attack, which temporarily drains 5 points of intelligence per successful hit.\nBugs.\n As ulitharids have no &lt;a href=\"Class%23Class%20kits\"&gt;class kit&lt;/a&gt; assigned, they receive due to a bug the &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt; bonuses of a &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;specialist mage&lt;/a&gt; who would be trained in no specific school: they save with a bonus of -2 against school-less abilities and add a penalty of +2 for recipients of their own such attacks. This applies to their &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Domination\"&gt;Psionic Domination&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; improves illithids of all varieties. The Ulithatid is no exception and SCS raises their Hit Dice to level 14. A reworked AI script is also designed to improve the decision logic of the creature, and to recognize opponent's vulnerabilities and protections to act in a smarter tactical manner. For example, it knows if a player is under effects of &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;. It can detect the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Charm%20Protection\"&gt;Helm of Charm Protection&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Harmony\"&gt;Shield of Harmony&lt;/a&gt;. It makes different targeting or attack option decisions with this information.\nIf any kind of &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warrior&lt;/a&gt; are detected, they will be attacked with the &lt;a href=\"Detonate\"&gt;Detonate&lt;/a&gt; ability, which destroys the creature in SCS.\nThe Ulitharid will quaff potions or apply oils to heal or boost abilities (the same as a party member). They carry three or more different potions (random SCS selection).such &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Potion of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Freedom\"&gt;Potion of Freedom&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe creature is scripted to use the following innate psionic abilities: Planar Travel , &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Maze\"&gt;Psionic Maze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ballistic%20Attack\"&gt;Ballistic Attack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Detonate\"&gt;Detonate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt; , and &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Domination\"&gt;Psionic Domination&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that the Ulitharid uses the more potent Psionic Blast version, with a -4 saving throw penalty.\nThe Ulitharid's devour brain melee attack has a range of 3 in SCS.\nSCS Ulitharids often begin the battle under Improved Invisibility. These crafty creatures will use the \"Planar Travel\" ability to dimension door to parts of the area map, including adjacent to vulnerable characters, or party members in the rear or even in another room from the main battle."}
{"id": "27231", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27231", "title": "Ulitharid (Spellhold)", "text": "This Ulitharid is found on the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%203\"&gt;Asylum labyrinth Level 3&lt;/a&gt; underneath &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. This creature is a type of &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt;, with slightly increased stats, though still lower than other ulitharids in other areas of the saga. This may be the first game encounter of this creature type for the party. \nGameplay.\nThis ulitharid will usually commence attacks on the nearest enemy using &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Domination\"&gt;Psionic Domination&lt;/a&gt;, within 2 rounds of hostilities. \nAny creature in melee range may be attacked with the devour brain melee attack, and this creature has 5 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;, although the &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; is not particularly accurate.\nIf still able to function after a few rounds, the illithid will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt; at the nearest enemy. More of these can be tried over the course of the battle, with only a scripted delay between uses. In between these psionic abilities the creature will continue with devour brain melee strikes.\nWhen the creature is wounded to a certain threshold it applies a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; ability to self.\nIn the unlikely case where a party member's &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; total is at 25% of its maximum, the ulitharid will attempt to actually cast a &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt; spell (which can be interrupted) at the wounded person.\nWhen the creature is defeated, find the &lt;a href=\"Flame%20of%20the%20North\"&gt;Flame of the North&lt;/a&gt; great sword as a loot item on the illithid's corpse.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature and makes it a full-fledged ulitharid with 14 HD. See the &lt;a href=\"Ulitharid\"&gt;Ulitharid&lt;/a&gt; Mod content section for potential changes. This creature is provided with two potions for use during the fight, which it scripted to quaff to boost abilities and heal itself. \nNote that with SCS this illithid will most likely not be faced alone and will be participating in battle with Yuan-ti and Noble Djinni companions.\nThis creature starts off under &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;. When it attacks it can be detected, but is still improved invisible, so targeting can be impossible for some party spells, and it also has the augmented armor class bonus. If the invisibility is removed, the Illithid may apply it again. They aren't dumb with SCS.\nExpect a more aggressive and robust use of &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; when battling this illithid with SCS. Some screen shots provided below."}
{"id": "27230", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27230", "title": "Ulitharid (The Black Pits II)", "text": "In the fifth arena battle of the third tier, a group of gladiators consisting of three &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"Thrall%20Wizard\"&gt;Thrall Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Thrall%20Archer\"&gt;Thrall Archer&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Thrall%20Fighter%20%28Black%20Pits%20II\"&gt;Thrall Fighter&lt;/a&gt;s has to be defeated. They are overseen by a single ulitharid that's protected by a special &lt;a href=\"CAMBION.ITM\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. The ulitharid has many resistances and immunities and can be regarded as invulnerable, but it also doesn't engage in the fight. When the battle's over it will vanish from life and the plane with a last &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48686", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48686", "title": "Ulma", "text": "Ulma is a tavern wench in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign, and can be found in &lt;a href=\"Vyatri%27s%20Pub\"&gt;Vyatri's Pub&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialog.\nAnimal Trouble.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Animal%20trouble%20in%20Trademeet\"&gt;Animal trouble in Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; if &lt;a href=\"Cernd\"&gt;Cernd&lt;/a&gt; is in the party:\n\"If you're bringing that druid in here, you can forget being served! Out you go!\"\nEven if &lt;a href=\"Cernd\"&gt;Cernd&lt;/a&gt; is not in the party yet, Ulma is suspicious of strangers but she grudgingly she says:\n\"Hmph. You're probably working for those druids and have come to kill us all, haven't you? Weellll, I suppose if Vyatri's willing to serve you, I can too.\"\nGenie Trouble.\nThe animal trouble is over, but the genies aren't gone yet:\n\"If you folk are so brave, why don't you do something about those genies? Then we could get some real wine here, again, for once.\"\n\"All anyone does, now, is complain about those genies. Food's becoming scarce... I suppose there's no pleasing people, is there?\"\nMazzy.\nThe animal trouble is over, and Mazzy is \"not\" in the party:\n\"You look familiar... do you know Mazzy Fentan? She's a famous adventurer from here in town. I think maybe she's mentioned you.\"\n\"Mazzy Fentan is our best adventuress... a real fighter, and that's something... for a halfling. She grew up here, you know.\"\nTrouble No More.\nAfter the animals and genies have been dealt with:\n\"Greetings to you, patron. This is Vyatri's inn, and I'm willing to serve you your drinks, so long as there's no groping, pinching or other unpleasantness.\"\n\"I suppose you folk are heroes or something, hm? Well, that won't get you your drinks any faster. Sit down, I suppose... or talk to Vyatri.\""}
{"id": "14370", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14370", "title": "Ulraunt", "text": "Ulraunt is a &lt;a href=\"lawful%20neutral\"&gt;lawful neutral&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;. The party can encounter him in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt; on the sixth floor of &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Library\"&gt;library&lt;/a&gt;. He won't engage in conversation and all of his replies are of a curt nature, but his pockets can be picked for a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Sleep\"&gt;Wand of Sleep&lt;/a&gt; with 14 charges.\nHe will also appear in the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; during a brief cut scene when the party is arrested and placed in the jail cell. He enters the barracks and officially accuses &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; of murder. If you reply that you're innocent and question why he is accusing you of such a deed, both of Ulraunts replies rely on accusations made by a man named &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Koveras&lt;/a&gt;. He then leaves the scene and &lt;a href=\"Tethtoril\"&gt;Tethtoril&lt;/a&gt; appears and, after a short back and forth dialogue, teleports the party to the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs\"&gt;catacombs&lt;/a&gt; located below the library."}
{"id": "26861", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26861", "title": "Ulvaryl", "text": "Ulvaryl is the first &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; encountered in the saga. After a brief declaratory exchange with her foes, she attacks the three &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Ulvaryl is allowed to kill all three would-be assassins, she will transform into an unassailable Vampire bat and exit the room.\nIf Gorion's ward party attacks and destroys her hit points to zero or less, she morphs into a 'Gas cloud form' and will flee the area instead.\nGame Play.\nUlvaryl is not immune to normal weapons. Her abilities are similar to a &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;Fledgling Vampire&lt;/a&gt;. In order to maximize the experience point gain from this encounter, you need to defeat the Vampire before all the Assassins are killed, as she will flee and leave the dungeon once her quarry is dead. \nIf the party doesn't wish to face the vampire at all, and decides to remain unengaged in combat, then it will not affect the questline - other than leaving some potential experience points unattained.\nFor a review of abilities and discussion of this creature and similar ones, click on the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire Information Link&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nMods:.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a number of changes to Ulvaryl. See the \"Mod Content\" section of the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; page. With this mod, the creature can only be struck with a +2 enchanted weapon or better, unlike the unmodified creature. These weapon items are scarce at this stage of the game. It is possible you may only possess one item that can strike her, so may have to rely on damage dealing spells or wands."}
{"id": "47788", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47788", "title": "Umar", "text": "Umar is a female mage who is the antagonist during the third subquest in the &lt;a href=\"Ranger-Protector%20of%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; ranger stronghold questline. She will appear in the village of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; portraying herself as the evil \"Umar Witch\", threatening the villagers, and ordering them to leave immediately.\nIn reality she is just someone who wants to lay claim to the abandoned &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Temple of Amaunator&lt;/a&gt; and is scaring the villagers to prevent them from finding out what her plans are before she's finished setting up her land grab.\nGameplay.\nUmar will probably open up the battle by a &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; spell cast, followed by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; Invocation, then &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. She'll cast &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; if any summoned creatures are observed. If a mage or cleric is seen they may be targeted with &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Silence\"&gt;Power Word, Silence&lt;/a&gt;. The remaining spells shown in the InfoBox are all scripted for use by either timing or if certain conditions are met. Most spell casts by Umar can be interrupted, so she can be rendered ineffective with the right tactics. \nMod Content.\nPlaying with &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod and or the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod and selecting the Smarter Mages Component will replace the AI script for Umar with script dw#mg405. This script will be much more challenging than the basic or EE version of Umar. Expect contingencies and sequencers, and arcane level 6 and 7 offensive spells directed at you. Umar is now assigned a Necromancer specialist mage kit by SCS.\nUpon hostilities commencing, she will launch a series of uninterruptible self-buffs including &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Invocation&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Armor\"&gt;Spirit Armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter the self-buff, another instant preparation spell will go off adding a summoned &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warrior&lt;/a&gt; to Umar's allies to contend with. From now on the advanced SCS script will select further spell casting from the witch based on opponent vulnerability assessments and targeting options. She can deploy many different spells including offensive damage types, divination, disabling and also can cast &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Secret%20Word\"&gt;Secret Word&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; if certain protections are observed on the party. Additional protective contingencies will also instantly reapply if he defenses are removed, dispelled or stripped away, such as Minor Globe, &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, Stoneskin, shield etc.\nThe witch has the following prepared to launch:\nWatch out for more summoned creatures (such as shadows or a fiend) and the &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Finger of Death (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;.\nHer Imp familiar is also a spell caster with SCS and has use of many first through third level arcane spells like &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spook\"&gt;Spook&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that with Spell Revisions she will have the SR spell versions, which means no Spell Immunity but \"Dispel Shield\", and Mantle replaced with \"Prismatic Mantle\". Her most powerful summoned creature will also be a gated Death Knight (a truly deadly creature - especially with SCS's Improved Fiends component)."}
{"id": "13408", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13408", "title": "Umar Cave", "text": "Umar Cave is a cave in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nBesides the &lt;a href=\"Killer%20Mimic%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;mimic creature&lt;/a&gt; that lurks here, you might also encounter &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;Umber Hulks&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warriors&lt;/a&gt;. Some creatures may respawn after your first visit. The party may rest here if they want.\nMod content.\nMods:.\nThe &lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/SpellholdStudios/Check_the_Bodies\"&gt;Check the Bodies&lt;/a&gt; Mod, \"Ancient Library (or Drow Library)\" module begins inside this cave. The first Pool of Water could be an entrance to another area and unknown adventure - and it is a really good one, and very challenging - beware, but the rewards are superlative."}
{"id": "5935", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5935", "title": "Umar Hills", "text": "The Umar Hills is a series of hills that conceal the village of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; can be recruited here.\nThere have recently been numerous deaths in the hills, leaving the locals very afraid. Some blame the return of an ancient evil, the Umar Witch, whilst others look to more recent threats, in the form of a band of monstrous warriors that recently began camping in the caves nearby. The village is desperate for salvation, and will turn first to &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt; and then to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to be rescued from their plight.\nMod content.\nMods:.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Invasion\"&gt;Imnesvale Invasion&lt;/a&gt; mod provides a tactical encounter that will take place the first visit to Imnesvale/Umar Hills after returning from the Underdark. The mod will automatically begin, with no chance to do anything before its initiation. See the link for details.\nWithin the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; you can initiate the &lt;a href=\"Trials%20of%20the%20Luremaster\"&gt;Trials of the Luremaster&lt;/a&gt; mod by speaking with \"Hobart Stubbletoes\" the halfling - this exceptionally well-done quest and adventure scenario has as much content and more than all of the Umar Hills questlines. See the link for further reading.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes many revisions to most creatures found on the Umar Hills area map, whether permanently placed or if a random encounter. Most of the revisions are to the creature's AI and tactical behavior, and sometimes it is to creature abilities and weapon proficiencies.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; mod makes revisions associated with &lt;a href=\"Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; and his ranger guardians. Additionally, the items &lt;a href=\"Boots%20of%20the%20West\"&gt;Boots of the West&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Taragarth%20the%20Bloodbrand\"&gt;Taragarth the Bloodbrand&lt;/a&gt; will be restored to the game within buildings and creatures in the Umar Hills map."}
{"id": "17103", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17103", "title": "Umar Witch Project Journal", "text": "Numerous copies of the Umar Witch Project Journal can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThis is a reference to ', which also features three researchers who disappeared while documenting a local witch legend. The film was released in 1999, during the development of '."}
{"id": "9076", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9076", "title": "Umber Hulk", "text": "Umber Hulks are subterranean, insectoid monsters that have a &lt;a href=\"confusion\"&gt;confusion&lt;/a&gt;-inducing attack. Four are found in the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;De'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt; and in any place with &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;mind flayers.&lt;/a&gt; Six umber hulk elders are featured as the fourth battle in the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Pits%20II\"&gt;Black Pits II&lt;/a&gt;. They are most often found in caves or other underground locations.\nGameplay.\nThis creature will act with immediate hostility when a party member is detected. It's first action is almost always to use the &lt;a href=\"Confusion%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Confusion (innate)&lt;/a&gt; ability which fires a projectile at a single target in range. If the ability works upon the target, they will be temporarily under the &lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nTheir next action is to rush forward toward the enemy and attack with their mandibles and limbs which inflict great crushing damage. Most of this breed can strike three times each round. Umber hulks &lt;a href=\"UMBER01.ITM\"&gt;attack&lt;/a&gt; with a adjusted &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; of 8 at 1\u00a0ft range and a speed of 1, dealing 3d4+8 &lt;a href=\"crushing%20damage\"&gt;crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; modifications included. Their attack counts as &lt;a href=\"enchanted\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; +3 in terms of what it can strike.\nThe creature will periodically be able to apply another confusion ability attack as the battle continues, but it doesn't occur if the creature is engaged in melee attacks. If for some reason the party disengages or moves away from the creature it will attempt another innate projectile, and the cycle will continue until it is destroyed or otherwise is made ineffective.\nThe basic game AI has no ability to determine if the target is protected against confusion or spells in any way, so it will use the confusion attack regardless of if it is futile. It can however determine if a target is already confused, and if so, will not apply another innate confusion attack on a target in that state.\nDue to their special innate attack, before engaging them it is advisable to first protect party members from confusion effects. Spells like &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; or items that protect from confusion will all work. Boosting saving throws against spells is also effective. Magic resistance can block this ability, as well as spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; will also stop it. The innate ability has spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; of 4.\nUmber Hulks are also notable for their low Hit Die, which makes them vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; (no save allowed) and &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; (they must make a saving throw or be instantly killed).\nSpell immunity - enchantment- does not protect you from their confusion attacks, as the innate ability has no assigned spell school.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; provides a new default script that controls the behavior of Umber Hulks to better chase down and move toward opponents in a smarter fashion. Such as pursing attackers firing missiles and spells at them from outside their detection range. It isn't perfect, but it assists them being smarter. The script also provides more threat detection awareness, and better tactical movement decision logic."}
{"id": "51697", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51697", "title": "Umber Hulk Elder", "text": "Umber Hulk Elder are subterranean, insectoid monsters that have a &lt;a href=\"confusion\"&gt;confusion&lt;/a&gt;-inducing attack. Several are found in an interior area of &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;. Six umber hulk elders are featured as the fourth battle in the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Pits%20II\"&gt;Black Pits II&lt;/a&gt;. They are most often found in caves or other underground locations.\nGameplay.\nThis creature will act with immediate hostility when a party member is detected. It's first action is almost always to use the &lt;a href=\"Confusion%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Confusion (innate)&lt;/a&gt; ability which fires a projectile at a single target in range. If the ability works upon the target, they will be temporarily under the &lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nTheir next action is to rush forward toward the enemy and attack with their mandibles and limbs which inflict great crushing damage. Most of this breed can strike three and a half times each round. Umber hulk elders &lt;a href=\"UMBER02.ITM\"&gt;attack&lt;/a&gt; with a adjusted &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; of 5 at 1\u00a0ft range and a speed of 1, dealing 3d6+9 &lt;a href=\"crushing%20damage\"&gt;crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; modifications included. Their attack counts as &lt;a href=\"enchanted\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; +3 in terms of what it can strike.\nThe creature will periodically be able to apply another confusion ability attack as the battle continues, but it doesn't occur if the creature is engaged in melee attacks. If for some reason the party disengages or moves away from the creature it will attempt another innate projectile, and the cycle will continue until it is destroyed or otherwise is made ineffective.\nThe basic game AI has no ability to determine if the target is protected against confusion or spells in any way, so it will use the confusion attack regardless of if it is futile. It can however determine if a target is already confused, and if so, will not apply another innate confusion attack on a target in that state.\nDue to their special innate attack, before engaging them it is advisable to first protect party members from confusion effects. Spells like &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; or items that protect from confusion will all work. Boosting saving throws against spells is also effective. Magic resistance can block this ability, as well as spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; will also stop it. The innate ability has spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; of 4.\nUmber hulk elders are slightly resistance to elemental damage and magic. Unlike their ordinary kin, they are not vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;. \nSpell immunity - enchantment- does not protect you from their confusion attacks, as the innate ability is school less.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; provides a new default script that controls the behavior of Umber Hulks and elders to better chase down and move toward opponents in a smarter fashion. Such as pursing attackers firing missiles and spells at them from outside their detection range. It isn't perfect, but it assists them being smarter. The script also provides more threat detection awareness, and better tactical movement decision logic."}
