{"id": "5516", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5516", "title": "Undercellar", "text": "The undercellar is a public underground place of rest underneath &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; that can be entered through the sewers or the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt;. If you enter through the Blushing Mermaid, a guard will talk to you and demand money to walk through the undercellar. He will let you pass whether you pay or not.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Quenash\"&gt;Quenash&lt;/a&gt; will be in one of the undercellar's rooms and is involved in the &lt;a href=\"Searching%20for%20Balduran%27s%20Helmet\"&gt;Searching for Balduran's Helmet&lt;/a&gt; side quest. She will give the player a clue to where the helmet is which points to the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20and%20Cloak\"&gt;Helm and Cloak&lt;/a&gt; inn in &lt;a href=\"northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;northwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;, assassins &lt;a href=\"Slythe\"&gt;Slythe&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Krystin\"&gt;Krystin&lt;/a&gt; will engage in dialogue at the center of the crossroads. Krystin will be initially invisible though. The &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; must obtain the &lt;a href=\"Invitation\"&gt;Invitation to Coronation&lt;/a&gt; Slythe is holding. This will allow passage into the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Palace\"&gt;Ducal Palace&lt;/a&gt;. Besides the invitation, the rewards for killing them both are 8000 XP, a &lt;a href=\"Letter%20from%20Sarevok%20to%20Slythe\"&gt;letter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Grave%20Binder\"&gt;the Grave Binder&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Sling%20%2B1\"&gt;Sling +1&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword%20of%20Backstabbing\"&gt;Short Sword of Backstabbing&lt;/a&gt;, ten &lt;a href=\"Bullets%20%2B1\"&gt;Bullets +1&lt;/a&gt;, ten &lt;a href=\"Bullets%20%2B2\"&gt;Bullets +2&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Master%20Thievery\"&gt;Potion of Master Thievery&lt;/a&gt;, third level spell scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Clairvoyance\"&gt;Clairvoyance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Touch\"&gt;Vampiric Touch&lt;/a&gt;, a fourth level spell scroll of &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning%20I\"&gt;Monster Summoning I&lt;/a&gt;, and "}
{"id": "5456", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5456", "title": "Undercity", "text": "The Undercity is an ancient ruined city underneath &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, which is infested with undead monsters. Part of the undercity is the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; which is where &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; and his most loyal followers are. You can get to the undercity in Chapter 7, by going downstairs in the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; and correctly finding your way through the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Maze\"&gt;Thieves' Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Rahvin\"&gt;Rahvin&lt;/a&gt;, who leads a &lt;a href=\"The%20Undercity%20Mercenaries\"&gt;party of six mercenaries (including him)&lt;/a&gt;, was hired by the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; to kill &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;. They will also try to kill your party, no matter what you say. This is probably your last assassin party you come across in the game of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and they prove to be the strongest party in the game.\n&lt;a href=\"Tamoko\"&gt;Tamoko&lt;/a&gt;, can be found near the entrace to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;. She doesn't want &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to kill &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; and she makes a futile attempt to convince you. You can convince her to leave Sarevok behind or otherwise she will fight to death. She will drop the &lt;a href=\"Plate%20of%20the%20Dark\"&gt;Plate of the Dark&lt;/a&gt; if she is killed.\nWhilst the main street will bring the party into conflict with Rahvin and Tamoko, the ruins above and below are crawling with sizable groups of undead monsters. East of the Temple of Bhaal there is a ruin inhabited by four &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;skeleton warriors&lt;/a&gt;, which may be very dangerous. Two of them will drop &lt;a href=\"Two%20Handed%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Two Handed Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;."}
