{"id": "23396", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23396", "title": "Underdark", "text": "The Underdark is a massive underground complex of tunnels and caverns, sprawling beneath the surface of Faer\u00fbn. \nDescription.\nIt is home to many subterranean races, including but not limited to, the Svirfneblin, the Duergar, and the Drow. Within the Underdark lie many wonders as well as cities, such as Menzoberranzan, possibly the most infamous and largest of the Drow City-States and is where both &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia De'Vir&lt;/a&gt; hail from. The Underdark is infamous for being deadly to both outsiders and those who consider it their home in no small part due to being infested with monsters like Aboleths, Illithids, Beholders, Hook Horrors, and Umberhulks, as well as natural disasters like cave-ins.\nPlot recap and entry into the Underdark.\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is in pursuit of Irenicus and Bodhi. Clues obtained from &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt;, statements from Irenicus, as well as the &lt;a href=\"First%20Journal%20of%20Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;First Journal of Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Second%20Journal%20of%20Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Second Journal of Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; all point to the underdark as the location of their quarry.\nThe party eventually transitions to the underdark, from either the portal in the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Basement\"&gt;Spellhold Basement&lt;/a&gt; or by way of the shaft and &lt;a href=\"Magical%20Rope\"&gt;Magical Rope&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon the transition, a cut scene plays exhibiting a meeting between Jon and a matron mother of Lolth in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. Some insight is gleaned from this in that Irenicus has worked out some kind of alliance with the dark elves in the city. \nThe party then arrives in the underdark, and shortly after another cutscene movie plays for the beginning of chapter 5, introducing the chapter's plot and a sinister description of the underdark.\nGameplay begins afterwards, and it is up to the party to explore and investigate this strange place and track down Irenicus. For a first-time player, the game does not specify exactly what to do, where to go, or any initial \"must do\" actions.\nCreatures.\nRespawning\nOne-time\nMod content.\nTactical Mod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes various changes to Underdark creatures and assigns new AI scripts as part of various optional components selected during installation. The Balor, Mind Flayers, Beholders, Adalon the Silver Dragon, Kuo-toans, drow warriors and spell casting drow are all potentially improved. The game difficulty setting will adjust the numbers and type of creatures found as determined by the SCS Spawn scripts. Aside from individual creature improvements, there will also be potentially more enemies included in the Drow ambush, drow war party and Kuo-Toan bridge guardian areas, as well as more Umber Hulks and Mind flayers. The harder the difficulty, the more the challenge.\nQuest Mod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Afaaq%20the%20Djinni%20Companion\"&gt;Afaaq the Djinni Companion&lt;/a&gt; Mod has significant new quest content added for the Underdark and Ust Natha. Afaaq, the party's djinni, will have much insight and banter here.\n&lt;a href=\"CoM%20Encounters\"&gt;CoM Encounters&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a drow war party encounter with a Matron Mother leading them. This will take place at the landing zone as the player first enters the Underdark. This mod is compatible with the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;SCS&lt;/a&gt; mod's AI scripts and the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; changes if those are also installed. On higher difficulty levels, this encounter is most likely more difficult than anything taking place in the previous areas in Chapter 4. There is little time to prepare for it, so beware. \n&lt;a href=\"Eilistraee%27s%20Song\"&gt;Eilistraee's Song&lt;/a&gt; Mod begins in the Underdark and adds a new adventure and quests that span beyond chapter 5.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; Mod adds a new area and a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; to the Western Tunnels. Extra content is also added for &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;A Mage's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; quest.\n&lt;a href=\"Adalon%27s%20Blood\"&gt;Adalon's Blood&lt;/a&gt; Mod introduces new choices and content for the Underdark and Ust Natha."}
