{"id": "6887", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6887", "title": "Unfinished Business for BG2", "text": "The Unfinished Business mod restores in ' and '.\nStatus.\nAs of Version 28, most all UB components are BG2:EE compatible. For \"\" some components have meanwhile been included in the game itself and are deprecated in the mod.\nNew quests.\n...and how to start them:\nPortrait restorations.\nThe original portraits for &lt;a href=\"Anomen%20Delryn\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; can be restored by installing this mod. In addition, the returning NPCs &lt;a href=\"Coran\"&gt;Coran&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Safana\"&gt;Safana&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Faldorn\"&gt;Faldorn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Garrick\"&gt;Garrick&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tiax\"&gt;Tiax&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Quayle\"&gt;Quayle&lt;/a&gt; can also be given their classic character portraits in their dialog boxes.\nCorrections.\nA number of glitches and errors can be undone by installing this mod.\nNew kits.\nEither of two new Ranger kits can be restored to the game through this mod; the elite tactician known as the &lt;a href=\"Justifier\"&gt;Justifier&lt;/a&gt;, and the bestial &lt;a href=\"Feralan\"&gt;Feralan&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal content.\nFour specific components of the mod are aimed exclusively at Baldur's Gate II: Throne of Bhaal.\nExternal links.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
{"id": "9114", "revid": "276341", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9114", "title": "Unger Hilldark", "text": "Unger Hilldark is a &lt;a href=\"duergar\"&gt;duergar&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSpeaking with Unger won't get very far or be pleasant.\nHowever, if the party has received the &lt;a href=\"Gain%20the%20services%20of%20Sir%20Sarles%20for%20the%20temple\"&gt;Gain the services of Sir Sarles for the temple&lt;/a&gt; quest - additional dialogue options will present themselves.\nThat is, if the party is pursuing getting some real &lt;a href=\"Illithium%20Ore\"&gt;Illithium Ore&lt;/a&gt;, as the party found out from &lt;a href=\"Jerlia\"&gt;Jerlia&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe's found next to the exit on the far west side of the tavern.\nHis tan to golden skin and red to orange hair colour suggests he is a Mountain Dwarf; even though in the dialog it is stated he is a Duergar Dwarf. Also his animation of 'THIEF_MALE_DWARF' with the combination of Chain Mail Armour suggests that Unger Darkhill is a Fighter / Thief class. Yet by his memorization information would suggest he is also a Cleric. A Cleric / Thief could make sense given the equipment of Chain Mail Armour and a War Hammer, while also using the male dwarf thief animation and having priest spell memorization slots. He uses a generic dwarf male voice sound set."}
{"id": "6060", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6060", "title": "Unholy Blight", "text": "Unholy Blight is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s of evil and neutral &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"blackguard\"&gt;blackguard&lt;/a&gt;s. It deals damage and inflicts roll penalties on all &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;good&lt;/a&gt; creatures in its area of effect.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its scaling and description. See below:\nUnholy Blight\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Necromantic\nRange: Long\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 20\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Special\nWith this spell the priest calls up unholy power to smite his enemies. The power takes the form of a chilling, cloying miasma of darkness. Opponents within the spell\u2019s area of effect take 1d4 points of damage for every level of the caster (up to a maximum of 10d4), with a successful saving throw vs. spell for half. If the victim fails his save, then he will also receive a -2 penalty on his attack rolls and saving throws for 4 rounds."}
{"id": "39235", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39235", "title": "Unholy Reaver", "text": "This sword is undroppable and only used by &lt;a href=\"Anti-Paladin\"&gt;Anti-Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Githyanki%20%28Race%29\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt;, who often have the &lt;a href=\"Blackguard\"&gt;Blackguard&lt;/a&gt; kit assigned. For the version obtainable by players, see the &lt;a href=\"Ir%27revrykal\"&gt;Ir'revrykal&lt;/a&gt; article.\nGameplay.\nThe Blackguard using the Unholy Reaver is part of the githyanki group in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; is outlined on the &lt;a href=\"Kruin\"&gt;Kruin&lt;/a&gt; article.\nMore of these Unholy Reaver wielding Anti-Paladins are found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Githyanki Encampment&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6061", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6061", "title": "Unholy Word", "text": "The Unholy Word spell is usable by Clerics of non-good alignment.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, and description. See below:\nUnholy Word\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Conjuration\nSphere: Combat\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nUttering an Unholy Word channels magic of tremendous power. The spell affects all enemies that are caught in the area of effect, while the effects differ according to the level of the target as follows:\nTarget\u2019s Hit Dice \u2013 Effects of Unholy Word\nEqual to caster level \u2013 Deafness for 1 turn\nUp to caster level -1 \u2013 Slowness for 5 rounds\nUp to caster level -5 \u2013 Confusion for 1 round\nUp to caster level -10 \u2013 Death\nThe effects are cumulative and concurrent."}
