{"id": "13386", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13386", "title": "Valygar's Home", "text": "Valygar's Home is a building at the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; during \"\".\nThe house is owned by a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; although, Valygar will return to his &lt;a href=\"Valygar%27s%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; unless told to stay elsewhere when dropped from the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Hervo\"&gt;Hervo&lt;/a&gt;, Valygar's servant, can also be found here. If at anytime the party should be belligerent with Hervo, he may call for the guards. If so, the party will face an &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Centurion\"&gt;Amnian Centurion&lt;/a&gt;, four &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Legionary\"&gt;Amnian Legionaries&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Enforcer\"&gt;Cowled Enforcers&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "4583", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4583", "title": "Valygar Corthala", "text": "Valygar Corthala is a neutral good &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ranger%23Stalker\"&gt;stalker&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in .\nRecruitment.\nValygar\u00a0is available to recruit from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in his &lt;a href=\"Valygar%27s%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; after the side quest &lt;a href=\"The%20hunt%20for%20Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;The hunt for Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; is initiated. He will return to his cabin when removed from the party.\nHis beginning experience level in the Enhanced Edition will not be less than level 8, and his starting weapon proficiencies are:&lt;br&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Katana\"&gt;Katana&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;++ &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;++ &lt;a href=\"Longbow\"&gt;Longbow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;++ &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;Two-Weapon Style&lt;/a&g.\nGameplay.\nWhen he joins the party, he has the following items: his family &lt;a href=\"Corthala%20Family%20Blade\"&gt;blade&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Corthala%20Family%20Armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, a long bow and some arrows.\nValygar is one of the only companions (others being &lt;a href=\"Dorn\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;) that can use &lt;a href=\"Defender%20of%20Easthaven\"&gt;Defender of Easthaven&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Hardiness\"&gt;Hardiness&lt;/a&gt;, reducing physical damage significantly. He cannot, however, use flails for backstabbing, which makes this weapon a better choice for his offhand rather than main hand."}
