{"id": "52803", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52803", "title": "STDEATH.ITM", "text": "STDEATH.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by a specific version of &lt;a href=\"Arkanis%20Gath\"&gt;Arkanis Gath&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered an enchanted item and deals 1d6+3 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of \"fifteen\" feet, and speed factor of 0.\nThe weapon functions as a +3 &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;, however each successful strike on a target exposes the hit creature to a &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; effect. This effect has no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; and can't be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or spell protections, such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt; can prevent the killing effect. &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; will negate the damage but the target will still be exposed to the Slay."}
