{"id": "51261", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51261", "title": "STONSKIN.ITM", "text": "The STONSKIN.ITM is a undroppable item worn in the creature's amulet/necklace slot. The item provides the wearer (typically a &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;) with an instantly cast &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; spell. \nIt casts OHWI408.SPL, and in all ways is the same as the usual Stoneskin spell used by players and most creatures in the game. It scales from 4 to 10 \"skins\" depending on the level of the creature equipped with the item. This item is provided to give the wearer some initial protection, without having to add a special script to do so. \nIt has no other powers or abilities."}
