{"id": "49958", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49958", "title": "Sahana", "text": "The Sun Soul Monk Sahana is a character from . She is one of the members of the &lt;a href=\"Tears%20of%20Sel%C3%BBne\"&gt;Tears of Sel\u00fbne&lt;/a&gt; which intercepts the party in the wilderness after visiting and then exiting the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Amphitheater\"&gt;Abandoned Amphitheater&lt;/a&gt; area map.\nGameplay.\nSahana is one of four Sun Soul Monks who confront the party and state that Rasaad is a known murderer. Various dialogue options are presented. These dialogue selections will determine the direction of the encounter in the Wilderness. \nSahana has all the abilities, immunities and special bonuses afforded to a Sun Soul Monk kit commensurate with her 10th Level experience. She wears the Cowl of the Stars.\nIn battle she will quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; when damaged to a 50% threshold.\nA &lt;a href=\"Lay%20On%20Hands%20%28monk%29\"&gt;Lay On Hands (monk)&lt;/a&gt; ability is used if original HP damage exceeds 60%.\nShe fights with her hands and feet in melee combat.\nShe'll possibly enable the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fists\"&gt;Flaming Fists&lt;/a&gt; spell ability when opponents are detected at a specific range.\nA &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Soulbeam\"&gt;Sun Soulbeam&lt;/a&gt; may be attempted if an opponent is in range and has less than 50% Magic or Fire resistance - and later a &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Sun\"&gt;Greater Sun&lt;/a&gt; if a target is within 30'."}
{"id": "3286", "revid": "284921", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3286", "title": "Sahuagin", "text": "Sahuagin are an predominately underwater species resembling\u00a0anthropomorphic sharks and are\u00a0found in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; , and . They can breathe in or out of water. Most worship Sekolah, the Shark God.\nThese creatures attempt to engage in missile combat as a priority, but will use their spear when forced to close quarters combat. They start off firing the &lt;a href=\"Paralytic%20Bolt\"&gt;Paralytic Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, then the &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Bolt of Biting&lt;/a&gt;, and finally mundane &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt; ammunition.\nThe particular creatures on this page are unskilled (non proficient) with their supplied and equipped weaponry, possibly a developer oversite. They are found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; within the Marine room. These Sahuagin are very much weaker than others found in the saga. They are of no real threat or consequence in battle unless they get a lucky shot and a missed saving throw with a Paralytic bolt and stun their adversary.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new AI script to the creature to improve tactical combat behavior. Appropriate weapon proficiencies are also placed so the creature receives some bonuses with its equipped weaponry choices, thus improving THAC0 and damage output. Hit dice levels are also raised, although hit points remain the same as the original."}
{"id": "51421", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51421", "title": "Sahuagin Baron", "text": "Sahuagin Baron is a predominantly underwater species resembling\u00a0atropomorphic sharks and are\u00a0found in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; , and . They can breathe in or out of water. Most worship Sekolah, the Shark God.\nThis creature will attempt to engage in missile combat as a priority but will use their spear when forced to close quarters combat. They start off firing the &lt;a href=\"Paralytic%20Bolt\"&gt;Paralytic Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, then the &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Bolt of Biting&lt;/a&gt;, and finally mundane &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt; ammunition.\nThe particular creature on this page is unskilled (non-proficient) with their supplied and equipped weaponry, possibly a developer oversite. It is found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; within the Marine room. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new AI script to the creature to improve tactical combat behavior. Appropriate weapon proficiencies are also placed so the creature receives some bonuses with its equipped weaponry choices, thus improving THAC0 and damage output. Hit dice levels are also raised, although hit points remain the same as the original."}
{"id": "52058", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52058", "title": "Sahuagin Baronial Guard", "text": "Baronial Guard is Sahuagin and predominantly underwater species resembling\u00a0atropomorphic sharks and are\u00a0found in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; , and . They can breathe in or out of water. Most worship Sekolah, the Shark God.\nThis creature will attempt to engage in missile combat as a priority but will use their spear when forced to close quarters combat. They start off firing the &lt;a href=\"Paralytic%20Bolt\"&gt;Paralytic Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, then the &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Bolt of Biting&lt;/a&gt;, and finally mundane &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt; ammunition.\nThe particular creature on this page is unskilled (non-proficient) with their supplied and equipped weaponry, possibly a developer oversite. It is found in a locked cell within the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayers%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Mind Flayers in Underdark&lt;/a&gt; dungeon, alongside a &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin%20Prince\"&gt;Sahuagin Prince&lt;/a&gt;. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new AI script to the creature to improve tactical combat behavior. \nThe class is changed to Fighter, and it is a 12th level warrior now. Appropriate weapon proficiencies are also placed so the creature receives 5 pips in Crossbow weapon proficiency and 3 pips in spear. Thus, improving THAC0 and damage output.\nHit points are increased, Strength is raised to 20 and dexterity is boosted to 18. It is after all, a Baronial Guard, and not a 2 HD creature."}
{"id": "51903", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51903", "title": "Sahuagin Chieftan", "text": "Sahuagin Chieftan is a &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Caverns\"&gt;City of Caverns&lt;/a&gt; in \"Shadows of Amn \"campaign.\nGameplay.\nThis Chieftan captain is standing watch nearby the rebel forces area of the city, not far from &lt;a href=\"Prince%20Villynaty\"&gt;Prince Villynaty&lt;/a&gt;. This warrior will acknowledge the party if they are in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Rebel%27s%20Orb\"&gt;Rebel's Orb&lt;/a&gt; - this item signals that you are allowed passage to seek an audience with the rebel Prince. Without the orb, the rebels would be hostile to the party.\nIf for any reason that the party is in combat with the Chieftan, the creature will behave as a crossbow and spear wielding fighting opponent. \nShould the party have the Rebel Orb, but then tell chieftain that they have in interest speaking with the prince, then he will say that the rebels will be prepared for the party (making them hostile). The chieftain does not turn hostile and attempts to walk away and leave the area. As is usual in this game, for a brief period he can be attacked and probably killed before making an escape.\nNotes.\nThere are two Sahuagin Chieftan creature files used by the game. The first is for the initial meeting (with the Orb in hand), while the second is if the party initiates hostilities with the rebel faction.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some changes. It provides a tactical AI script for smarter combat behavior. The captain is assigned a level 14 Fighter class, and increased Hit Points and improved THAC0. The crossbow and bolts are still used, and the creature also has advanced spear combat, with grand mastery weapon proficiency and 2 pips in two-handed fighting style. Some potions are available for quaffing during combat. The creature has a new +2 Spear weapon that applies a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect on any hit. Save vs. Death to negate or take 2 damage/sec for 15 seconds."}
