{"id": "51423", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51423", "title": "Sahuagin Priestess", "text": "Sahuagin Priestess is predominantly an underwater species resembling\u00a0atropomorphic sharks and are\u00a0found in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; , and . They can breathe in or out of water. It worships Sekolah, the Shark God.\nIf forced into close quarters combat, the Priestess will engage with its spear, of which it has specialized proficiency.\nUpon detecting a hostile opponent, the Priestess will prep with a &lt;a href=\"Barkskin\"&gt;Barkskin&lt;/a&gt; on self, and the wizard's spell &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; on nearest enemy, and then a &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt; onself, then a &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt; on the entire Sahuagin group. Depending on her own and allies hit point loss, various cure serious and light wounds will be attempted to heal damage. The priestess will not cast any disabling or offensive spells. If any party member is invisible or hidden, the Priestess will attempt an Invisibility Purge.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new AI script to the creature to improve tactical \"Smarter Priest\" spell casting behavior. Additionally, a new repertoire of memorized Priest spells is carried, and all can be used by the script as determined by the opponent's actions and immunities/vulnerabilities. Most likely the Priestess will force cast (previously cast) the following spells at the outset of hostilities: &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Skins\"&gt;Iron Skins&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action\"&gt;Free Action&lt;/a&gt;. See the screenshot below for a depiction of this:"}
{"id": "51557", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51557", "title": "Sahuagin Prince", "text": "Sahuagin Prince are a predominately underwater species resembling\u00a0anthropomorphic sharks and are\u00a0found in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; , and . They can breathe in or out of water. Most worship Sekolah, the Shark God.\nThe Prince variety uses the Large Sahuagin animation.\nThis particular page is about a creature that has been captured by the drow, and is the third opponent beast to battle in the &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha%20Tavern\"&gt;Ust Natha Tavern&lt;/a&gt; fighting pit. Speak with &lt;a href=\"Szordrin\"&gt;Szordrin&lt;/a&gt; after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Nabassu\"&gt;Nabassu&lt;/a&gt; in the second battle. He'll say:&lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Dare you continue? There is a prince amongst the shark-fiends... the ones called \"sahuagin.\" A strong one captured with difficulty during a raid on their city.\"\"&lt;br&gt;\nEnter the fighting arena and slay this prince. The shark creature will only possess its own hand to hand weaponry (bite and claws). It can attack 5 times per round.\nIf you defeat the opponent, the party gains 2,000 XP for the kill and a 750 gold victory purse.\nNotes.\nA second Sahuagin Prince (SAHPRI01.cre) is imprisoned in a locked cell in the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayers%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Mind Flayers in Underdark&lt;/a&gt; (Eastern Tunnels) area of the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new AI script to the creature to improve tactical combat behavior. Appropriate weapon proficiencies are also placed so the creature receives some bonuses with its equipped weaponry choices, thus improving THAC0 and damage output. \nThe mod changes the prince to a level 16 fighter, with increased Hit points, and some stat boosts. It will perform better in combat now and won't only be a 2 HD creature (that might be a developer error). In addition, the prince has an undroppable Spear +2 wielded with grand mastery proficiency and 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style. "}
