{"id": "33004", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33004", "title": "Saladrex", "text": "Saladrex is a powerful, &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;chaotic&lt;/a&gt; chromatic Red dragon. In the original ', he is &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20evil\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt;. In the ' he is chaotic neutral. Saladrex the Ancient One (as referred to by the Githyanki Captain) has his &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Saladrex%20%28Dragon%29\"&gt;Lair&lt;/a&gt; connected to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Githyanki encampment&lt;/a&gt;. \nHe provides useful information about &lt;a href=\"Carston\"&gt;Carston&lt;/a&gt; and the warring factions created by his mischief, as well as some insight about the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt;, including how to solve a puzzling problem and how to get Carston out of his glass prison. You can ask him all sorts of questions, even about the \"Imprisoned One\". However, he has grown very suspicious of outsiders, thinking they come to steal his hoard. He enjoys adulation and is not overtly looking for conflict or violence. Should you indulge his penchant for flattery, and perhaps \"stroke his ego\" a bit more, you may find out exactly why he is in Watcher's Keep. If you are short with him or rebuff his boasting then he will tire of you. This could lead to hostilities. \nIf defeated, Saladrex drops the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20the%20Ram%20%2B4\"&gt;Staff of the Ram +4&lt;/a&gt;, arguably the best &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaves\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt; and highest &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;damaging&lt;/a&gt; weapon for a &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt; in the saga.\nGameplay.\nSaladrex will initiate dialogue when a party member is in detection range, which is also the same range as the nearest party member can see - the dragon is neutral at the outset of the dialogue.\nThe dialogue can lead to a peaceful outcome, or hostilities. It is up to the player and the choices selected that will determine this.\nIf the party undertakes certain actions in sight of the dragon, it will turn hostile, including directly attacking it, setting traps or snares, and the presence of summoned/conjured creatures.\nAnother trigger for a response is certain arcane or priest spells cast on the party within the dragon's detection range - examples include &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Energy&lt;/a&gt;, and others.\nSaladrex can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nCheck the InfoBox for Saladrex's scripted actions and general triggers for use of spells, and innate abilities.\nExpect several &lt;a href=\"Wing%20Buffet\"&gt;Wing Buffet&lt;/a&gt; attacks and &lt;a href=\"Red%20Dragon%20Breath\"&gt;Red Dragon Breath&lt;/a&gt; blasts during the battle. The breath weapons are used no sooner than every three rounds.\nAlmost all of Saladrex's spell attacks are not interruptible by damaging the dragon, and \"ForceSpell\" cast.\nNote that when the dragon's hit points first fall below 50%, a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell will trigger, mending all of his wounds.\nSee the dragon's immunities and special abilities listed on the InfoBox. \nWhen the beast is defeated, take the gold and loot which can be recovered from Saladrex's corpse.\nBugs.\nSaladrex's regeneration ability timing mode is set as permanent, but that setting requires a duration to work, and it has no duration, and therefore it doesn't operate correctly. This is an issue throughout the game in several other creatures as well. This issue is included in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt; and is already identified to Beamdog for possible fixing in the future.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises Saladrex in many ways. Especially if you install the \"Smarter Dragons\" component (which is responsive to the game difficulty selection). His SCS AI improves targeting and recognition of opponent's protections, which means he will fight smarter and not waste attacks on someone he cannot hit or damage. It will also influence his tactical options and attack methods. First, some mention of the dragon's stats and abilities. In most cases, all of the unmodded ones are still applicable:\nImmunities in addition to the unmodded dragon version:\nAs stated in the article above, Saladrex has access to several innate Dragon abilities (which are manifested as \"spells\"). They are uninterruptible. A little bit more on what SCS does with the following:\nSpells: Saladrex is scripted to use the following spells, as determined by the AI's need: Magic Missile , Melf's Acid Arrow , Fire Arrow , Remove Magic , Slow, Greater Malison, Breach , Death Spell, Ruby Ray , and Power Word Blind. \nWith the installation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, some of Saladrex's arcane memorized spells will be the SR version.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod adds the \"Secret Manual of Golem Building (vol. 6)\" to the dragon's hoard."}
{"id": "48667", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48667", "title": "Salahee", "text": "Salahee is a Caravaner in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign, and can be found inside &lt;a href=\"Raafee%27s%20Tent\"&gt;Raafee's Tent&lt;/a&gt; south of the exterior wall, just outside the city gates.\nDialog.\nGenie Trouble.\n\"You are welcome here. We are not so suspicious as the people of the town, although I think they have every right to be fearful.\"\n\"It has been troubling. The genies mesmerized the merchants in the caravans so they sell their goods to them very cheaply, and no one else may buy. No one can do a thing about it.\"\n\"Between the attacks of the animals on our wagons and the genies who hoard our goods, my husband has gone nearly bankrupt. I... I fear for his health.\"\nTrouble No More.\n\"On behalf of my husband and I, I thank you for everything you have done. Our caravans have been restored to prosperity. Wherever we go, we shall tell of your good deed, dear &lt;MAN/WOMAN&gt;!\""}
{"id": "29041", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29041", "title": "Salamander", "text": "Salamanders are a species of extraplanar reptilian humanoids that resemble red-skinned humans with horns from the waist up and giant, red-scaled serpents from the waist down. They hail from the Elemental Plane of Fire.\nEncounters.\nSalamanders are a rare encounter but can be found in a select few areas:\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; makes minor revisions to this creature. It provides an SCS default tactical combat script for smarter decision making, threat recognition and targeting. The Spear proficiency is boosted to 3 pips, and 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style is assigned. This will result in a better THAC0, damage, speed factor and critical hit chance. Immunity to Web and Entangle effects is provided, including their overlay animations. \nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20of%20Deception\"&gt;Tower of Deception&lt;/a&gt; mod populates one dungeon level with various monsters, and you will encounter both Fire and Ice Salamanders within."}
{"id": "29042", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29042", "title": "Salamanders", "text": ""}
{"id": "48395", "revid": "284062", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48395", "title": "Salia", "text": "Salia is a female &lt;a href=\"Vampires\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and a loyal member of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt;.\nEncounters.\nChapters 2 or 3.\nBefore &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, she may appear in any district of the city during a night cycle (midnight to dawn). Salia is the second member of Bodhi's Vampire Coven that the protagonist will encounter this way, \n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; will see her talking to two &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; in an attempt to get them to leave their organization and join with Bodhi's rival guild. Salia appears neutral during this encounter and will transform into her gaseous form before any attempt can be made to attack her.But the two shadow thieves will turn hostile and attack the party.\nThe most noteworthy treasure they drop is a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt;, some gems and gold from the first thief (VVSHAD4), and a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Find%20Familiar\"&gt;Find Familiar&lt;/a&gt;, one more of &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Pearl\"&gt;Pearl&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Garnet%20Gem\"&gt;Garnet Gem&lt;/a&gt; from the second thief (VVSHAD5). The first shadow thief also has a note on him which reads:\n\"\"The Shadow Thieves weaken day by day and cannot even protect their own members from the night they claim to know so well. What do your guild dues pay for, besides the opulence of the Shadow Council? Join with us and receive what you know you are worth. We meet when the night is half past. You know the place.\"\nChapter Six.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; Salia will be in Bodhi's Hideout, along with &lt;a href=\"Hareishan%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Hareishan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Meredath\"&gt;Meredath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tanova\"&gt;Tanova&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt;, five &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;fledgling vampires&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Vampire%29\"&gt;vampire guard&lt;/a&gt;; all of whom are defending Bodhi's inner sanctum from being accessed by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party (and perhaps some helpful allies).\nSalia is akin to a &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;Fledgling Vampire&lt;/a&gt;, and can be struck with normal weapons, however she can drain 3 experience levels on a hit. Her script does allow use of the &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; ability after two rounds of hostilities have elapsed.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod with the \"Improved Vampires\" component revises both appearances of Salia. See the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article and the \"Mod content\" section for a discussion of the mod's revisions to vampires (including Salia) in the game.&lt;br&gt;\nThe first version of this vampire (VVSALIA.CRE) is a moot point, as she cannot be attacked or engaged in combat. \nThe second version of this vampire (C6SALIA.CRE) is a level 12/2 Fighter/Thief with 145 HP, STR 20, DEX 20, CON 19. She has 2.5 attacks per round, THAC0 3 and -3 Armor Class. Her melee strike drains 3 experience levels or 3 CON. She also has a different default script, making her akin to an ancient vampire, that has all the abilities of that vampire version including Vampire Domination, Shape changing to bat or wolf, summoning bats, rats or wolves and the innate &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20Fear\"&gt;Vampire Fear&lt;/a&gt; ability and the \"Mesmerize\" feeblemindedness attack. She will recognize opponents protected from level drain and charm and many other \"buffs\" for intelligent targeting. At least +2 or better enchanted weapons are needed to hit her."}
{"id": "51306", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51306", "title": "Salt Crystals", "text": "Salt Crystals is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Salt%20Mephit\"&gt;Salt Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A bullet projectile is launched at a single target in range. \nIt will strike the target and inflict 1d4 damage. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath Attack is required to negate a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect lasting 12 seconds. The stun will place the target under the &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; state. The stun effect can be blocked by magic resistance and also has a level 2 spell pwer, so it can also be stopped with protection such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe crushing damage will bypass magic resistance, but it also can be blocked by a spell protection because it too has a level 2 spell power. A &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; could also absorb the crushing damage."}
{"id": "51305", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51305", "title": "Salt Mephit", "text": "A Salt Mephit is an extra-planar \"outsider\" (i.e., linked to various Elemental, Quasi-Elemental and Outer planes of existence). These creatures are similar to &lt;a href=\"Imp\"&gt;Imps&lt;/a&gt; and are found in a number of areas during the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;\"Baldur's Gate II\"&lt;/a&gt; games.\nGameplay.\nA Salt Mephit can attack twice per round in melee for 1d3 damage. Any hit will stun the target for 12 seconds unless a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Polymorph is made. It also has the innate &lt;a href=\"Salt%20Crystals\"&gt;Salt Crystals&lt;/a&gt; ability. \nThe mephit will initiate the \"Salt Crystals\" attack, which launches a bullet projectile at a target in range and it deals 1d4 damage. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath Attack is required to negate a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect with a 12 second duration (making the creature under the &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; state during that time). The mephit will launch this ability when a opponent is detected and in range. At least 10 seconds will then pass while the mephit engages in melee combat before the ability use cycle can cycle anew. The mephit has an endless supply of the Salt Crystals.\nThe Salt Mephit has no magic, or physical damage resistance. It does however have immunity to fire damage.\nThe mephit can regenerate 1 hit point every round.\nThe InfoBox summarizes the creature's special abilities and immunities to certain status effects. The game has the creature with a memorized &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt; spell but it isn't scripted to use it, so it is probably just a developer creature file copy-paste remnant."}
{"id": "29856", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29856", "title": "Salvanas", "text": ""}
{"id": "8880", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8880", "title": "Salvanas di Riyos", "text": "Salvanos di Riyos is a philandring Bard watching the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; clientele, with a amused smile and a lecherous eye for the female form.\nGameplay.\nIf spoken to by a party member, Salvanas will react with very individual lines to various &lt;a href=\"female\"&gt;female&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; members \u2013 who also have unique reactions based on the person. If talked to by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, he will leave the Coronet after the conversation.\nThere is a particularly rare and amusing interaction with Salvanas if &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwina&lt;/a&gt; engages in conversation with the bard. Suggest saving your game before doing so.\nDialogue.\n\u2022 Female Gorion's Ward.\nIf a &lt;a href=\"female\"&gt;female&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, he will express his desire for her, in which case she may either insult him or offer to rent a room at the Coronet \u2013 just now. Either way, he will leave.\n\u2022 Aerie.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, she will feel uneasy for a moment before stating that &lt;a href=\"Quayle\"&gt;Quayle&lt;/a&gt; has warned her to stay away from guys like Salvanas, and then brush him aside.\n\u2022 Edwina.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Edwina\"&gt;Edwina&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, she he will both be annoyed and flatted by what Salvanas says. In the end, it will result in Edwin/a casting a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; on him, causing hostilities. It won't cause the whole tavern to go hostile, as Salvanas had it coming for commenting on Edwina's Adams Apple. \n\u2022 Hexxat.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Hexxat\"&gt;Hexxat&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, he will confess his preference for &lt;a href=\"Chult\"&gt;Chult&lt;/a&gt;an beauty over her denials \u2013 until she comments on drinking his blood. This brings about an end to the discussion.\n\u2022 Jaheira.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, Salvanas will fall for her but Jaheira will brush him aside.\n\u2022 Mazzy.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Mazzy\"&gt;Mazzy&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, it becomes obvious that this is not their first encounter. However, she's not pleased to see him again or by the way he's naming her and warns him \"for the last time\" to leave her alone.\n\u2022 Nalia.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Nalia\"&gt;Nalia&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, she will interrupt his flattering by stating that she already knows him \u2013 after all, she hangs up in the Coronet \u2013 and his charms won't work on her.\n\u2022 Neera.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, she seems confused whom he might be speaking about. He admits that he'd be entranced by her eyes, lips \u2026 and hair. Neera finally tells him to keep his hands to himself.\n\u2022 Viconia.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt; talks to him, he will also fall for her due to her dark drow appearance. After even admitting he'd be willing to die to partake of her swarthy lust, she will be tempted for a short time, but finally brush him aside."}
{"id": "2648", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2648", "title": "Samantha", "text": "Samantha is one of the wealthy inhabitants of the &lt;a href=\"Manor%20House\"&gt;Manor House&lt;/a&gt; in the town of &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. She can be found in her bedroom on the second floor.\nKilling her results in a reputation loss. However, when she summons &lt;a href=\"Jamie\"&gt;Jamie&lt;/a&gt; and they both run away, the chest near the bed containing a unique &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing%20%28murky%29\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt; and can be looted safely.\nDialogue.\nTalking to her can go one of three ways:"}
{"id": "27186", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27186", "title": "Samia", "text": "Samia is relic hunter who can be found in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nShe initiates dialogue with the closest party member - to assist in a hunt for some texts about an ancient ruler in his burial chamber. She offers a key to access the maze area beyond that supposedly contains these texts. \nIf the party accepts her offer and agrees to help, then the dialogue will finish with several bits of information, and the key is provided. She'll say:\nIf later the party decides not to pursue the maze or only partially explored, then they can return to Samia and tell her so and return the key. This leads to hostilities. She'll say:\nIf the party rejects Samia's offer of the key, and refuses to help her, this also leads to hostilities. She'll say:\nAnd if the party still refuses, she'll say:\nRegardless of the path chosen, at some point the party will probably be in conflict with Samia and her group of five other relic hunters.\nIn combat she acts as a ordinary melee fighter, attacking with her scimitar. She may quaff a Potion of Extra Healing when her hit points fall to a scripted predetermined percentage.\nAll of the items listed in the InfoBox may be scavenged from her corpse if defeated. The exception will be &lt;a href=\"Samia%27s%20Key\"&gt;Samia's Key&lt;/a&gt; if she has already provided it to the party.\nNote.\nIn the classic game her alignment was Chaotic Neutral.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to Samia. Foremost she has a new default smarter fighter script for better threat recognition, vulnerability assessments and improved tactical behavior. She is provided 5 pips in scimitar weapon proficiency, and 2 pips in sword and shield fighting style. This will improve her &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;, weapon damage and &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;. Her armor class versus missile will be boosted. In addition, more random potions may be quaffed/applied during combat for healing or boosting abilities."}
{"id": "33889", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33889", "title": "Samia's Key", "text": "Samia's Key is a key given to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Samia\"&gt;Samia&lt;/a&gt; in . The key allows the party to progress further in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "51945", "revid": "279172", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51945", "title": "Samia's Proposal", "text": "Samia's Proposal is a side-quest that has no actual in-game official title, although there are Journal entries provided once the proposal is accepted, and another when 'resolved'. This section of the adventure actually falls under the &lt;a href=\"Rescue%20Garren%27s%20child%20from%20Firkraag\"&gt;Rescue Garren's child from Firkraag&lt;/a&gt; questline in the player's journal - even though this part of the quest isn't necessary to complete the child rescue. This might be a developer oversight.\nAquisition.\n&lt;a href=\"Samia\"&gt;Samia&lt;/a&gt; will initiate dialogue with the closest party member in a corridor within Firkraag's Maze area. A proposal is offered from her, and if accepted, will trigger a Journal entry, as follows:\nGameplay and abbreviated walkthrough.\nSamia's proposal accepted.\nAfter Samia speaks to the party, various dialogue will ensue - she appears to be an armed and armored fighter with scimitar and shield. She is alone, and neutral at the moment. If the party listens and doesn't immediately attack her, the party will learn her purpose in this dungeon, and have the opportunity to ask her several questions. Samia is a level-headed and reasonable speaker and quite charismatic in her own way.\nParaphrased here are the final remarks from her:\nMore dialogue occurs, and if the player decides to help her, she'll promise compensation and will provide &lt;a href=\"Samia%27s%20Key\"&gt;Samia's Key&lt;/a&gt;, saying:\nThe maze.\nThe corridor in which you spoke to Samia is fitted with several doors, leading West but mostly North. The key she provided will fit one of them, allowing access to the interior maze and burial chambers she spoke of, somewhere beyond. An Automap Note shows the door and a text display shows: Entrance to the maze. It is likely that the King's tomb may be warded against intrusion, so a party member who can discern traps could be of use while exploring the maze. There are probably further doors that are locked as well, needing lockpicking, or forced with strength, or even opened magically with a &lt;a href=\"Knock\"&gt;Knock&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nAdvance through the unlocked door north. A mostly empty room with some dusty debris on the floor is all that is seen, as well as two closed doors. A door to the north or one to the west.\nMoving through the western door leads into another chamber, littered with debris and various trash. Two closed doors are seen, one leading North and the other west. Moving rapidly toward the party from the shadows is an attacking &lt;a href=\"Fell%20Ghast\"&gt;Fell Ghast&lt;/a&gt;. It seems the maze isn't uninhabited after all. A search of the room in one corner leads to finding the &lt;a href=\"Book%20of%20King%20Strohm%20III\"&gt;Book of King Strohm III&lt;/a&gt; and some other random treasure, possibly a &lt;a href=\"Stone%20to%20Flesh%20Scroll\"&gt;Stone to Flesh Scroll&lt;/a&gt;. The ghast may be carrying a shiny bauble (as they often do) as a keepsake or to occupy its time between meals of manling flesh and bone marrow. Perhaps this Book is the text Samia sought?\nOf course, it couldn't be that easy to solve this task.\nThe room where you found the book has two closed doors. The one to west is a smallish chamber, devoid of furnishings and only some cobwebbed wall shelving. Surprisingly some sort of Genie, maybe an Efreeti stands before you, calmly staring into your gaze. If you draw close to the magical creature it speaks: \nThe creature turns hostile. You must defend yourself!\nThis creature is just one of several &lt;a href=\"Mask%20guardian\"&gt;Mask guardians&lt;/a&gt; within the maze. If the party is able to defeat its physical form, it shrinks into a planar vortex and disappears - leaving behind a single Piece of Burial Mask. What is this for? And what are you supposed to do with it? One thing noticed during the battle with the strange creature is that this guardian was most likely an Efreeti or possibly a Noble Efreeti. That explains the fireball cast upon the party and the eye watering acrid sting of partially combusted sulfur.\nExamination of the Piece of Burial Mask notes the following description:\nHaving heard the cryptic message from a guardian and having examined the found Piece of Burial Mask from the defeated guardian, the party has correctly deduced that exploring this maze and area definitely has something to do with a King Strohm III. The presence of guardians also points to the place being purposefully protected from intrusion, and the mask pieces may be key to solving the whole thing. It now seems that Samia was not lying about the importance of this place and the potential for special texts and perhaps treasures hidden within.\nDelve further and seize the Mask Pieces.\nThe party must penetrate and explore the rest of this maze. More guardians are present ahead. There will be doors to examine, and rooms to search. Methodically scan for traps, and expect some doors to be locked, or maybe even find that there are \"false doors\" that seek to confuse and distract as they lead nowhere.\nFind and destroy the remaining guardians. Each will utter some words of their duty and strange portents of doom for any would-be grave robbers. Ensure all pieces of the mask are collected.\nIn one surprise chamber, a &lt;a href=\"Director\"&gt;Director&lt;/a&gt; beholder will be discovered, which is hostile. It will begin its attack script if any creatures are in its detection range. See the creature page for details.\nAssuming the party is successful in getting all six Mask Pieces, when this occurs a screen text message will display:\nAnd the player's Journal will update as well with:\nEventually the party will come to a chamber (located north of the Director beholder, and nearby one of the Mask guardians). A door leading north is locked, and despite attempts to open it will not budge. Examining the door will reveal an on-screen text message:\n&lt;br&gt;\nDefeat the Final mask guardian and explore King Strohm's tomb.\nWith the clue about the Mask on the door, the party can take the completed &lt;a href=\"Mask%20of%20King%20Strohm%20III\"&gt;Mask of King Strohm III&lt;/a&gt; and equip it on a party members helmet slot. This action acts as the key needed to open the final door to King Strohm's tomb. \nIt also has one other effect, and that is to reveal the invisible &lt;a href=\"Final%20mask%20guardian\"&gt;Final mask guardian&lt;/a&gt;. This guardian will attack the closest detected party member in melee combat. The guardian resembles a sort of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Elemental\"&gt;Fire Elemental&lt;/a&gt;. For details about the being, see the creature article.\nWhen defeated, the party may enter and explore the last room, which is the tomb of King Strohm III. The player will discover two items in a floor niche amidst some debris, including &lt;a href=\"Peridan\"&gt;Peridan&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale%20Shield\"&gt;Dragon Scale Shield&lt;/a&gt;. When these items are picked up, a script trigger will initiate.\nSamia and cohorts make an appearance.\nBlocking the path out of the maze are Samia and a group of allied relic hunters. Paraphrased below, Samia will speak:\nSamia and her five cohorts will then initiate hostile attacks upon the party. The player has been lied to and must defend against this assault. The following creatures are your new enemies:\n&lt;a href=\"Samia\"&gt;Samia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Akae\"&gt;Akae&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chak\"&gt;Chak&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ferric%20Ironblade\"&gt;Ferric Ironblade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kaol\"&gt;Kaol&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Legdoril\"&gt;Legdoril&lt;/a&gt;. See their individual pages for details. Additionally, a short journal entry will pop up as soon as the enemy party begins hostilities that basically summarizes that the PC is now aware that she and her party intended to ambush, kill and loot the party all along.\nIf defeated, a journal entry will update:\nAnd so, this ends Samia's proposal."}
{"id": "7599", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7599", "title": "Samuel", "text": "Samuel is a deserter from the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; who is found in the &lt;a href=\"Gibberling%20Mountains\"&gt;Gibberling Mountains&lt;/a&gt; area east of the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;. He is lying on the ground after being badly wounded. His friend &lt;a href=\"Lena\"&gt;Lena&lt;/a&gt; wants you to take him to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Wisdom\"&gt;Temple of Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; to be healed. A &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Mercenary%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Flaming Fist Mercenary&lt;/a&gt; to the west wants to arrest him for desertion."}
{"id": "8267", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8267", "title": "Samuel Thunderburp", "text": "Samuel Thunderburp is a &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; and owner of the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Flagons%20Inn\"&gt;Five Flagons Inn&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;.He claims to serve a beverage of every flavor available, though there are only five types of drinks you can buy from him. Samuel's wife &lt;a href=\"Thalia%20Thunderburp\"&gt;Thalia Thunderburp&lt;/a&gt;, also a halfling, works in the Inn as a serving wench.\n\"There's a theater downstairs, if you like...but don't forget a mug of spiced wine before you go! At the Five Flagons, tickling your palatte is our pleasure!\"\nVisit him with &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt; in your party, and he will thank you for rescuing his favourite &lt;a href=\"Halfling\"&gt;Halfling&lt;/a&gt; \"Paladin\" by rewarding you with a pair of boots, &lt;a href=\"Worn%20Whispers\"&gt;Worn Whispers&lt;/a&gt;.\nVisit Samuel with &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt; in the party after having freed he and &lt;a href=\"Raelis%20Shai\"&gt;Raelis Shai&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Planar%20Prison\"&gt;Planar Prison&lt;/a&gt;, and he will gift you with a &lt;a href=\"diamond\"&gt;diamond&lt;/a&gt; from a fan of his acting performances.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises Samuel by assigning an SCS default fighter AI script for smarter tactical behavior, and potion use. Weapon proficiency is changed to 4 pips with Flail and 2 pips in Single Weapon fighting style. Random SCS treasures are placed in his inventory."}
{"id": "8718", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8718", "title": "Samuel and Lena", "text": "Samuel and Lena is a side quest that begins in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Gibberling%20Mountains\"&gt;Gibberling Mountains&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0area east of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Lena\"&gt;Lena&lt;/a&gt; will ask the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; to carry her very ill friend\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Samuel\"&gt;Samuel&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0to\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Gellana%20Mirrorshade\"&gt;Gellana Mirrorshade&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0at the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Wisdom\"&gt;Temple of Wisdom&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0area. If you insist on payment she will give you a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Jade%20Ring\"&gt;Jade Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis quest is in direct conflict with the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Samuel%20the%20Deserter\"&gt;Samuel the Deserter&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0quest given by the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Mercenary%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Flaming Fist Mercenary&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in the\u00a0Gibberling Mountains\u00a0area. This one offers far better rewards, but the Friendly Arm Inn is far away, Samuel (who must be carried) weighs 100 lbs (115 lbs in the ), and the quest is on a very short timer. The party has 72 hours to succeed, and travel from Gibberling Mountains to Friendly Arm Inn takes 40 hrs, so it should be easily completed so long as the party doesn't stop to smell the &lt;a href=\"Xvart\"&gt;Xvart&lt;/a&gt;s along the way (in other words, so long as they don't waste much time, but travel to the Inn soon). The only way to complete both quests is to first complete this one, kill Gellana Mirrorshade, loot Samuel's body from her corpse, and then deliver it to the Flaming Fist Mercenary.\nIf Samuel is delivered to the Temple of Wisdom before he dies, the party gets 500 &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt;, two potions (see sidebar)\u00a0and +1 to the party's\u00a0&lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "8719", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8719", "title": "Samuel the Deserter", "text": "Samuel the Deserter is a side quest from a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Mercenary%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Flaming Fist Mercenary&lt;/a&gt; who's encountered on the west side of the &lt;a href=\"Gibberling%20Mountains\"&gt;Gibberling Mountains&lt;/a&gt; area, which is located to the east of the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;. He asks you to watch for the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; deserter &lt;a href=\"Samuel\"&gt;Samuel&lt;/a&gt;, and to turn him in if you find him. The Flaming Fist Mercenary will stay there after initial dialogue and only says, \"So we meet again. I'm sorry, but I don't have any time for talk.\" when spoken to again.\nThe &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will find Samuel laying on the ground near his friend &lt;a href=\"Lena\"&gt;Lena&lt;/a&gt; and you'll have to accept to undertake the &lt;a href=\"Samuel%20and%20Lena\"&gt;Samuel and Lena&lt;/a&gt; side quest in order to place him in your pack. He is heavy ( 100 pounds &amp; 115 pounds), and will need to be carried back to the Flaming Fist Mercenary. You will receive 50 as reward and no other penalties or rewards will be accessible.\nThis is in direct conflict with the more involved (but much more rewarding) Samuel and Lena quest obtained from Samuel's friend Lena. The only way to complete both quests is to first complete the Samuel and Lena quest, kill Gellana Mirrroshade, loot Samuel's body from her corpse, and then deliver it to the Flaming Fist Mercenary."}
{"id": "8115", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8115", "title": "Sanadal Gwist", "text": "Sanadal Gwist is a comely young lass who can be found on the second floor of a generic &lt;a href=\"Generic%20Tavern%20and%20Inn%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1306\"&gt;Inn and Tavern&lt;/a&gt; that's located across from &lt;a href=\"Well-Adjusted%20Al%27s%20General%20Store\"&gt;Well-Adjusted Al's General Store&lt;/a&gt; and sits parallel to the city's outer wall in &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is the sister of &lt;a href=\"Shank\"&gt;Shank&lt;/a&gt; and a cousin of &lt;a href=\"Carbos\"&gt;Carbos&lt;/a&gt;, the two assassins that tried to kill &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;. She is angry at them because they owe her money, and isn't sad to hear of their demise."}
{"id": "11467", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11467", "title": "Sanasha", "text": "Sanasha is an apprentice of the mad &lt;a href=\"Zhentarim\"&gt;Zhentarim&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt;. She can be found paired with &lt;a href=\"Prebek\"&gt;Prebek&lt;/a&gt; in his &lt;a href=\"Prebek%27s%20House\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"Rylock\"&gt;Rylock&lt;/a&gt;, a member of the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, tasks &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party with killing Prebek, his accomplices and his 'creations' (which appear to be nothing more than ordinary &lt;a href=\"goblin%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;goblin&lt;/a&gt;s). With the installation of the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; mod, the original creatures in the home are restored, as well as the scimitar &lt;a href=\"Shazzellim\"&gt;Shazzellim&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nMage Book.\nSanasha has a number of &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; memorized (see also &lt;a href=\"%23Trivia\"&gt;Trivia&lt;/a&gt;), but will use only a couple of them. In addition, when combat starts, a \"&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt;\" applies &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; on her.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Sanasha, especially with the \"Smarter Mages\" component. Sanasha is now an Invoker and has a new array of memorized spells. A default SCS AI script is assigned for smarter tactical behavior. She will deploy a contingency that raises some defensive protections on herself at the outset of hostilities. Sanasha has a loaded &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; ready to fire. Defensive contingency identified as cast previously including &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Armor\"&gt;Ghost Armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;. After that, she'll attempt a Remove Magic and then let loose the offensive Invocation spell cast at a vulnerable party member in sight, including the Minor Sequencer loaded with two invocation spells. "}
{"id": "39376", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39376", "title": "Sanctified Shards", "text": "The Sanctified Shards are both the &lt;a href=\"First%20Stone%20Fragment\"&gt;First&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Second%20Stone%20Fragment\"&gt;Second Stone Fragment&lt;/a&gt;s blessed by &lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt;, priestess of &lt;a href=\"Tempus\"&gt;Tempus&lt;/a&gt;. The Sanctified Shards are needed in the &lt;a href=\"Foehammer%27s%20Blessing\"&gt;Foehammer's Blessing&lt;/a&gt; quest in ."}
{"id": "4883", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4883", "title": "Sanctuary", "text": "Sanctuary is a 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. It prevents enemies from attacking or targeting the caster.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its casting time, duration and description. See below:\nSanctuary\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Charm, Protection\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 6 rounds\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen the priest casts a Sanctuary spell, it causes all of his opponents to ignore his existence, as if he were invisible. While protected by this spell, the subject cannot take direct offensive action without breaking the spell but may use non-attack spells focused on himself or otherwise act in any way that does not violate the prohibition against offensive action. This allows a warded priest to heal his wounds, for example, or to cast a Chant spell. He cannot cast spells on other targets without ending the spell.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises many enemy divine spell casters scripts to utilize the Sanctuary spell when they are severely wounded, and then they'll attempt to administer healing to self while temporarily protected. This works out well when the SCS mod is coupled with the Spell Revisions mod - as the SR version has a 1 casting time."}
{"id": "41235", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41235", "title": "Sand Golem", "text": "The Sand Golem is a Giant Humanoid with a &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt; class identifier. They are found during the , and the \"Throne of Bhaal\" and the Enhanced Edition versions of the game.\nThey are potential enemy spawns during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey may spawn in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; or when selecting the \"I wish to be more experienced\" option of the &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish\"&gt;Limited Wish&lt;/a&gt; choice.\nGameplay.\nThe Sand Golem is a slightly less combat capable and robust version of the Clay Golem, although they share the same AI script and animation.\nThis particular category of Golem is 100% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;resistant to magic&lt;/a&gt;; however, this can be overcome by casting &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt; first or by using spells that ignore magic resistance (&lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Minute%20Meteors\"&gt;Melf's Minute Meteors&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt;...). \nWeapons-wise, they can only be harmed by magical weapons. The only elemental effects that can harm this golem are &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; (although at only 50%) and &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;Acid damage&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, Sand Golems are completely invulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;. They are the same general size as the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem\"&gt;Stone Golem&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Golem\"&gt;Flesh Golem&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Brain%20Golem\"&gt;Brain Golem&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe golem's melee attack dishes out 3d10 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; and it is modified by their superior strength. The fist attack counts as a +4 enchanted item for the purpose of what it can strike. They typically only strike once per round, but under the effects of their innate &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Haste\"&gt;Golem Haste&lt;/a&gt; ability, their &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; increase to 2.\nSand Golems normally empower themselves at the beginning of combat with a \"Golem Haste\" innate ability. This bestows them with a \"normal\" &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;. It should last for 72 seconds, but it can be dispelled. The haste effect can also be applied to the golem's allies (if there are any) in a 15' radius around the creature when the ability is initiated (possibly hasting other nearby golems or allies). The golem's movement rate will also double while hasted. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the installation of the \"AI Enhancement's\" component improves many aspects of creatures encountered in the game. In regard to golems, the mod implements the following:\nImproved Golems (BG2, BG2EE, BGT/EET)&lt;br&gt;\nThis component doesn't really make golems smarter (they're supposed to be stupid) But it streamlines their scripts a bit, gives their weapons a sensible range, makes them immune to \"Lower Resistance\" and to poison, and tries to prevent situations where golems get stuck behind barricades. It also fixes an animation glitch in the Iron Golem animation - this hopefully makes iron golems a bit prettier when they attack and blow clouds. As of SCS version 22, it also gives clay golems a cursed-wound weapon, as in PnP Dungeons &amp; Dragons.\nSCS revises the typical Clay Golem fist melee weapon &lt;a href=\"GOLCLA.ITM\"&gt;GOLCLA.ITM&lt;/a&gt;. When the golem hits a target, it applies an instant \"Cursed Wound\" effect (DW#CURSE.spl).\nThe golem hit inflicts its rolled damage, but that damage is now Cursed. \nUpon a hit, a lighting animation will play over the target, the combat log will show a text display \"\"Cursed\" and another one that says \"Unable to Heal\"\". This means that any damage incurred by this weapon cannot be healed by normal means (such as a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, or a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Cure Light Wounds (spell)&lt;/a&gt;. However, a &lt;a href=\"Regeneration\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; effect can heal this damage.\nWith this component the clay golem is immune to all the status effects in the unmodified version, plus the following spells and additional status effects: &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Plant%20Growth\"&gt;Plant Growth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nSand Golems with SCS do not have any innate spells or the Golem Haste ability.\nThis golem now has a melee attack range reach of 2, instead of the unmodified creature's range of 1."}
