{"id": "3846", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3846", "title": "Sandthief's Ring", "text": "The Sandthief's Ring is a in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;\", ', ', ' (and ') and can be imported into \"\".\nGameplay.\nIt bestows normal &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; to the wearer upon command via the item spell use menu. Therefore, the effect is not constant, but rather is activated when needed, so long as the item is not drained of charges. Its effect is removed by anything that would normally end the Wizard spell Invisibility.\nIn the original \"Baldur's Gate I\" with the \"Tales of the Sword Coast\" expansion, the ring would be destroyed if all of its charges were used up, having neglected to sell and then re-buy it, in order to recharge it back to its maximum number of charges. This could be quite expensive with a base item value of 20,000.\nIn \"Baldur's Gate II\" the ring has one charge per Rest Period and is temporarily \"drained\" not destroyed, so there's no reason to sell and re-buy it anymore in order to recharge it, but instead just rest. Its price has also been lowered significantly.\nIn addition, &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; can use the ring to upgrade &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Hood\"&gt;Thieves' Hood&lt;/a&gt; (also requires an &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0and 10,000).\nVarious game-controlled NPCs will employ an undroppable Sandthief's ring coupled with the \"useitem.bcs\" script in order to attain invisibility. An example is &lt;a href=\"Regis\"&gt;Regis&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Encounter%20-%20Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Encounter - Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; area."}
{"id": "35094", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35094", "title": "Sanik", "text": "Sanik is a free trader on the island of &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\". He is encountered during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, but only if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; took the &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; route to &lt;a href=\"Getting%20inside%20the%20asylum\"&gt;get inside the asylum&lt;/a&gt;. He'll be inside Brynnlaw's Inn known as the Vulgar Monkey.\nGameplay.\nPrior to the arrival of the party, Sanik \u2013 who had made his money by trading supplies and spellcasting components to the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; operating &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 has fallen in love with &lt;a href=\"Claire\"&gt;Claire&lt;/a&gt;, a courtesan employed by &lt;a href=\"Galvena\"&gt;Galvena&lt;/a&gt;. He had plans to smuggle her away from Brynnlaw to marry her, and his dealings with Gorion's Ward were intended to be his last job before doing that.\nSoon after speaking with Sanik, a surprise attack in the Brynnlaw Inn from a halfling assassin ends his life. Based on further statements from the Innkeeper and what the assassin has said, it looks like the \"hit\" was ordered by Galvena as punishment for some sort of slight against the Brothel madame. \nThe information supplied by Sanik, and the Innkeeper should clue the party in that Claire has some information needed to provide a pathway or method to gain access to &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. See the &lt;a href=\"Getting%20inside%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Getting inside the asylum&lt;/a&gt; page for more information. The party now has at least one goal to help move forward to rescue Imoen.\nMod content.\nTwo are available that add an unofficial alternative to save Sanik and let the couple enjoy a happy ending. Both mods are very different in content."}
{"id": "48421", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48421", "title": "Sansuki", "text": "Sansuki is a male &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; who is being hunted by the &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Del\"&gt;Del&lt;/a&gt; and two male vampires. He will appear randomly within the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; between the hours of midnight and dawn and approach the party upon sight.\nSaving the man is a possibility if you can get the vampires to concentrate their attack on the party, but he will become hostile if attacked or caught in friendly fire. If he does become hostile, he'll still be attacked by the vampires. If the party is able to keep him alive, all he'll do is give you his thanks and disappear.\nDialogue.\n\"Help! You've got to help! Please!\"\nAfter he has been saved:\nThen, if you've sided with the vampires in the guild war:\nIf you've sided with the shadow thieves:\nIf you haven't made a choice yet:"}
{"id": "6099", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6099", "title": "Saradush", "text": "Saradush is a city in &lt;a href=\"Tethyr\"&gt;Tethyr&lt;/a&gt; that was led by &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan.&lt;/a&gt; The city was under siege during the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%208\"&gt;first chapter&lt;/a&gt; of \"Throne of Bhaal\" campaign and was later destroyed by the fire giant &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura\"&gt;Yaga-Shura&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackstory.\nOnce a great bureaucratic center for the city's royal dynasty, Saradush became a producer of agricultural products for trade. Despite this, Saradush became an important way station for trade in the area surrounding the Lake of Steam. Given its proximity to several kinds of terrain, along with increased prominence as trade traffic with &lt;a href=\"https%3A//forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Riatavin\"&gt;Riatavin&lt;/a&gt; rises, Saradush also become a haven for travelers and adventurers alike.\nLater in Saradush history, the unpopular ruling Count Santele was overthrown by the even more tyrannic &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; half-orc war lord Gromnir Il-Khan. At the same time, a woman named &lt;a href=\"Amelyssan\"&gt;Melissan&lt;/a&gt; came and brought as many Bhaalspawn as she could to the city for their 'protection'. Unknown to them, she was actually Bhaal's right-hand servant and had really lured them to Saradush to gather them all in one place - allowing them to be killed together and Melissan able to gather more of Bhaal's essence for her cause. This would eventually lead to one of Melissan's cohorts, Yaga-Shura, besieging and sacking the city.\nGameplay and walkthrough (abbreviated).\nTravel to Saradush.\nThe party has already had an opportunuity to experience the &lt;a href=\"Pocket%20Plane%20%28area%29\"&gt;Pocket Plane (area)&lt;/a&gt; and was introduced to the &lt;a href=\"Solar\"&gt;Solar&lt;/a&gt;. The party has encountered &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; and had discussion with the protagonist's \"dead\" brother. Additionally, the party has also completed the first of several challenges - specifically the Challenge: Retribution. \nWhen the party is ready to continue the adventure, exit the pocket plane. A Journal Entry will display soon:\nArriving in Saradush.\nNext a cut scene cinematic will play about the siege of Saradush. Narration and a violent scene of burning buildings and flaming catapult missiles are featured. This transitions into another cutscene focused on the main steps in front of Castle Saradush. A mob of townsfolk are gathered and face a group of human and orc guards. They seek an audience with the town's current ruler, &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt;. The guards refuse, warning all to disperse or face their wrath. Another NPC named &lt;a href=\"Melissan\"&gt;Melissan&lt;/a&gt; talks over the mob and addresses all. She seeks to calm the situation, and says:\nThe soldiers aren't listening and prepare to attack the crowd. Melissan shouts:\nAt this moment the party appears only feet away from the gathering and observes the soldiers' advancing upon the hapless unarmed townsfolk. Melissan says out loud:\nA final soldier shouts that the party are intruders into the city, and to attack. The soldiers are now hostile and change their focus to the party. Defeat the &lt;a href=\"Il-Khan%20Soldier\"&gt;Il-Khan Soldier&lt;/a&gt; forces, and check out their loot drops. The townsfolk flee the local area.\nConverse with Melissan.\nOnce the soldier threat is finished, Melissan will address the protagonist. During her explanations there may be a chance to interject, and further along ask some questions. Some paraphrased dialogue below:\nYou learn more and find out your next goals in the saga:\nShe continues:\nThere are several questions and replies available should the party wish to delve further. Afterwards Melissan teleports away. At that time the player receives two Journal Entries:"}
