{"id": "16583", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16583", "title": "Save Editors", "text": "Save Editors, unlike &lt;a href=\"Console\"&gt;CLUAConsole&lt;/a&gt;, which is activated in-game, are tools to edit the content of saved games. Popular save editors for &lt;a href=\"Infinity%20Engine\"&gt;Infinity Engine&lt;/a&gt; games are \"Keeper\" series.EEKeeper supports Enhanced Editions while ShadowKeeper and GateKeeper are used for original versions. Not only can these keepers edit saved files (change character classes, add powerful items, alter global values etc.), they also have limited support for modifying game files, consider them a mini &lt;a href=\"Near%20Infinity\"&gt;Near Infinity&lt;/a&gt; in this field.\nThere is also DaleKeeper for Icewind Dale series.\n&lt;a href=\"Near%20Infinity\"&gt;Near Infinity&lt;/a&gt; itself as well provides the functionality of a Save Editor for all of the above games in original and Enhanced Edition versions.\nExternal links.\nJSEE Keeper\n\"EE Keeper adaptation for the browser. Allows editing .gam files. Supports BG2, ToB and BG2: Enhanced Edition. Usable, but with less features than the original EE Keeper (desktop version).\""}
{"id": "5959", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5959", "title": "Save Jaheira from Baron Ployer's Curse", "text": "Save Jaheira from Baron Ployer's Curse is one of two &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;Quests&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; during the campaign.\nAcquisition.\nUpon entering the &lt;a href=\"Sea%27s%20Bounty%20Tavern\"&gt;Sea's Bounty Tavern&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; with Jahiera in the party, a former slaver named &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Ployer\"&gt;Baron Ployer&lt;/a&gt; will confront Jaheira. After their dialog, three mages, &lt;a href=\"Terrece\"&gt;Terrece&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gracien\"&gt;Gracien&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Malacazar\"&gt;Malacazar&lt;/a&gt;, will appear and cast a curse on her, which lowers her &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and her &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; by one point immediately. It will continue to make her weaker every day. Furious about what happened to her and eager to kill him, Jaheira suggests that the party should find &lt;a href=\"Bernard\"&gt;Bernard&lt;/a&gt;, who may know the whereabouts of Belgrade, whom Ployer mentioned. She also proposes searching the Slums for Ployer and asking at the government building (&lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Six%20Building\"&gt;Council of Six&lt;/a&gt;) about the mages he had hired."}
{"id": "5955", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5955", "title": "Save Mazzy's Sister, Pala", "text": "Save Mazzy's Sister, Pala is a &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;Quest&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nAcquisition.\nThis quest can begin 7-8 days after having freed Mazzy Fentan from the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord's&lt;/a&gt; grasp in the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; during the quest to &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20Deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Investigate the Deaths in the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;. \nBackground.\n&lt;a href=\"Danno%20Fairfoot\"&gt;Danno Fairfoot&lt;/a&gt; appears and asks Mazzy to return to &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; to help her sister &lt;a href=\"Pala%20Fentan\"&gt;Pala&lt;/a&gt;. He says he bought a \"love potion\" from Wallace the Peddler's shop, &lt;a href=\"Wallace\"&gt;Wallace's Wares&lt;/a&gt;, which turned out to be poisoned. \"I didn't mean to do it... I just wanted her to love me. She only had a sip of it and she collapsed.\"\nMazzy chides him, \"Danno, you fool, you need no potion! She's always loved you...\" She then explains to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, \"Pala is my sister and Danno is her betrothed. She may be dying, we must go to her,\" after which, the player's Journal is updated with this quest.\nWalkthrough.\nMazzy gives Pala the potion, and then says, \"She breathes easier and color returns to her features. It may be working... She is resting, now, and I am most relieved. If all goes well, I shall be ready to leave when Pala awakens again. I shall understand, however, if you cannot wait.\" After this, your Journal is updated once more.\nThe player now has a choice:\nThus concludes this companion quest, securing Mazzy as a present and/or future companion.\nBugs.\nUnder unclear circumstances Danno does not show up to alert Mazzy. In this case the following &lt;a href=\"console\"&gt;console&lt;/a&gt; commands seem to help:\n C:SetGlobal(\"DannoBeginsPalaPlot\",\"GLOBAL\",1)\n C:SetGlobal(\"Pala\",\"GLOBAL\",0)\n C:SetGlobal(\"SpawnDanno\",\"GLOBAL\",0)\n C:SetGlobal(\"SpawnDannoTimer\",\"GLOBAL\",1)\nIf he still begins with the Trademeet dialogue, summon him and then enter this command before he can speak to Mazzy.\n C:SetGlobal(\"DannoBeginsPalaPlot\",\"GLOBAL\",1)\nUsing EEKeeper to insert these variables does not seem to work.\nAfter inputting the previous commands, it may be necessary to manually spawn Danno if he does not appear automatically, using the following command:\n C:CreateCreature(\"Danno\")\nAt which point he should then proceed to automatically path to and subsequently interact with Mazzy as though he had spawned properly."}
