{"id": "5479", "revid": "282288", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5479", "title": "Scar", "text": "Harold \"Scar\" Loggerson is the second-in-command of the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and a good friend of his commander, &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt;. He'll ask the player to perform several investigations for him that not only puts the player in his good graces, they also provide a handsome boost to the players coin purse.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Seven%20Suns\"&gt;The Seven Suns&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen the player first meets Scar on the &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%27s%20Crossing\"&gt;Wyrm's Crossing bridge&lt;/a&gt; at the beginning of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt;, he'll ask the player if they would investigate the strange business activities of the &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Suns\"&gt;Seven Suns&lt;/a&gt; trading coster. If the player fully completes that mission, Scar would be informed that the Seven Suns has been infested with doppelgangers and that his friend &lt;a href=\"Jhasso\"&gt;Jhasso&lt;/a&gt; is alive and well. Scar will pay the party 2000 for the information and he'll double it if the party agrees to go back and eliminate the doopelgangers.\n&lt;a href=\"Missing%20Citizens\"&gt;Missing Citizens&lt;/a&gt;.\nScar then wants the player to investigate the disappearances of random people in &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. If that mission is successful the player will have killed an &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage\"&gt;ogre mage&lt;/a&gt; and retrieved a &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ring\"&gt;ruby ring&lt;/a&gt;. Scar will pay the party 1300 for discovering and eliminating the reason for the missing citizens and he'll toss in an extra 3000 for returing the items (the ruby ring) to their rightful owner.\nAfter the second mission, Scar introduces the player and their party to &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt;, who then gives the party their third and final mission in the fifth chapter. It is important to know, that after introducing you to Duke Eltan, Scar leaves forever, so you might want to complete his two sidequests beforehand. \n(If you are intent on killing him for the 9,000 XP, and various +1 loot, due to his large amount of Hit Points, hitting him with Cloudkill is the easiest route to take to achieve this. Where he is not resistant to poison, and is only Level 6, so only has 6 Hit Dice, he must make a save vs poison at -4 penalty or be slain).\nLater on, whilst the player is back in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;, Scar is attacked and murdered by two &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt;s. One of the doppelgangers then took the shape of Scar and attacked Duke Eltan. Though the Duke overcame the attack, he did receive injuries and to make things worse, his healer, &lt;a href=\"Rashad\"&gt;Rashad&lt;/a&gt; was actually a doppelganger whose 'cures' only made the Duke's health worse."}
{"id": "13722", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13722", "title": "Scar and the Iron Throne", "text": "Scar and the Iron Throne is the third quest given by &lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; officer. Upon completion of the &lt;a href=\"Missing%20Citizens\"&gt;Missing Citizens&lt;/a&gt; quest, he will ask you to meet him outside the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt;. Once you've talked to him, he will take you to talk to &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt; which leads to &lt;a href=\"Investigating%20the%20Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Investigating the Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt;."}
