{"id": "9379", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9379", "title": "Scribe Scrolls", "text": "Scribe Scrolls is a is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieve&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s.\nPrerequisite: &lt;a href=\"Use%20Any%20Item\"&gt;Use Any Item&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\nGameplay.\nThe scroll created is randomly selected from the above list, but works just like any other spell scroll and remains in the party's inventory indefinitely - until used, sold or thrown away. Therefore, the player can have as many of those scrolls as they choose (or as many as their patience allows), especially if using an area such as &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; to be able to rest freely and produce more scrolls.\nDue to the fact spells used via scrolls are cast at level 10 (or higher, if the spell has a higher minimum level), the spells listed above work as following:\nAlthough not necessarily powerful, this ability does have some niche uses, as it, for example:\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a change to the Rogue's HLA's:\nCrippling Strike (replaces Scribe Scrolls)\nAn experienced Thief can use the knowledge of his opponent's weak spots to gain an advantage in combat. During the round when this ability is activated, every attack of the Thief deals maximum damage and may weaken his target. On each successful hit the victim must make a saving throw vs. death (with a -4 penalty) or have its strength score lowered to 10 for the next five rounds. Note: Constructs, Elementals, Slimes and Undead creatures are completely unaffected by this ability.\nRequires: Assassination"}
