{"id": "9561", "revid": "5305940", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9561", "title": "Sel\u00fbne", "text": "Sel\u00fbne, also known as Our Lady of Silver or the Moon Maiden, is a &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20good\"&gt;chaotic good&lt;/a&gt; intermediate &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt; of the moon and the stars.\nShe is worshipped by navigators, seamen, good-aligned lycanthropes and many more. Furthermore she is the twin sister of &lt;a href=\"Shar\"&gt;Shar&lt;/a&gt;, with whom she has been bitter enemies since ancient times. The sisters' battles have brought forth the creation of &lt;a href=\"Jergal\"&gt;Jergal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mystra\"&gt;Mystra&lt;/a&gt;, among others.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon%20heretics\"&gt;Dark Moon heretics&lt;/a&gt; believe that Sel\u00fbne and Shar are two sides of the same goddess.\nTemples.\nUnlike most other temples in the games, the temple of Sel\u00fbne does not offer any services."}
