{"id": "5874", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5874", "title": "Sendai", "text": "Sendai is a &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Mage\"&gt;cleric/mage&lt;/a&gt; member of &lt;a href=\"The%20Five\"&gt;The Five&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nIn , when the player meets her in the deepest area of &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;her enclave&lt;/a&gt;, Sendai will create seven statues around the room. One by one, each statue will turn into a copy of Sendai and attack. When a statue copy is killed, two drow warriors will appear and attack, and another statue will turn into a copy of Sendai and attack. After all the statues have been destroyed, the real Sendai will appear and attack."}
{"id": "19596", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19596", "title": "Sendai's Enclave", "text": "Sendai's Enclave is a plot location in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%209\"&gt;Chapter 9&lt;/a&gt; of \"Throne of Bhaal\" campaign. Players may choose the order of the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; elimination, either into &lt;a href=\"Abazigal%27s%20Lair\"&gt;Abazigal's Lair&lt;/a&gt; first, or proceed into this enclave which is broken up into smaller tunnels through where the party must pass through to reach &lt;a href=\"Sendai\"&gt;Sendai&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes numerous changes to the creatures and dialogue in these areas. It also restores some cut content by Bioware. The &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod adds even more changes to the Ascension Mod, mostly improving the enemy creatures' AI and numbers of opponents found within. The Mods are compatible with each other."}
