{"id": "48310", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48310", "title": "Senior Armagaran Vulova", "text": "Senior Armagaran Vulova is a nobleman who is found in his &lt;a href=\"Vulova%20Estate\"&gt;estate&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt; if you have decided to side with &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; in the guild war. \nGameplay.\nSenior Vulova is the head of a merchant house with ties to the Shadow Thieves. \nAs part of the &lt;a href=\"Perform%20Bodhi%27s%20Tasks%20to%20Receive%20Her%20Aid\"&gt;Perform Bodhi's Tasks to Receive Her Aid&lt;/a&gt; questline, the Ward must select one of two choices offered by Bodhi - killing Senior Vulova and pinning the blame on the Shadow Thieves is one of those choices.\nAssuming the party has decided to go forward with this task, when they enter the estate Senior Vulova is inside, along with a guardian named &lt;a href=\"Laen%20Torg\"&gt;Laen Torg&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen a party member is detected and is close enough (10 feet or so) then he'll initiate dialogue.\nThere are several outcomes to this task, including just stealthily slaying Vulova, speaking with him and having no mercy and killing him, or perhaps letting him live and demanding that he flee Athkatla and disappear for awhile. it is up to Gorion's Ward to decide how to proceed.\nIt is likely that there may be some battle going on here, regardless of what transpires.\nDialogue.\n\"What? Who are you? I demand to know what you are doing in here!\""}
