{"id": "48766", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48766", "title": "Sergeant Natula", "text": "Sergeant Natula is a &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;-assassin, hired by an anti-magic faction in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. He first approaches &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; after two days have passed since the protagonist's apprentices have graduated during the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nNatula will be accompanied by six others, including three other fighter-assassins named &lt;a href=\"Tyrian\"&gt;Tyrian&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vilhelm\"&gt;Vilhelm&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Jalin%20Tix\"&gt;Jalin Tix&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Alnarow\"&gt;Alnarow&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Mahar\"&gt;Mahar&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;), and &lt;a href=\"Sorsha\"&gt;Sorsha&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "6811", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6811", "title": "Serpent Shaft", "text": "Serpent Shaft is a Magical &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B2\"&gt;Quarterstaff +2&lt;/a&gt;. On each hit from this staff, there's a 50% chance to inflict a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison effect&lt;/a&gt; unless the target &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;saves&lt;/a&gt; vs Death. This weapon is required to upgrade the &lt;a href=\"Ravager\"&gt;Ravager&lt;/a&gt; to +6 by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis item appears in and .\nNormally, this weapon's poison does a total of 24 damage over the course of 2 rounds, but if the enemy is hasted they'll receive 46 damage over those same 2 rounds instead, due to how damage-over-time poison interacts with haste. Considering that the poison can also be stacked, this fact makes this one of the most damaging weapons in the game in the hands of a character or party that can haste enemies via Improved Haste or Wish (against enemies that are vulnerable to poison, of course) or against enemies that already make use of haste themselves. Moreover the fast-acting poison (even without haste) is especially devastating against spellcasters who won't be able to cast during the effect.\nThe main drawback of the weapon is the 50% chance, as it can't be improved upon with Greater Malison and similar spells. The +2 enchantment rarely matters as the few enemies that require +3 or +4 weapons to be hit tend to already be immune to poison (like balors, pit fiends, ancient vampires and greater mummies), so one should use another weapon against those even if Enchanted Weapon (EE) is available to allow the Serpent Shaft to hit them.\nLocation.\nIt is dropped by the lich on the fifth floor of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%28dungeon%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "47516", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47516", "title": "Servant", "text": "A Servant can be found in palaces and in some of the houses of wealthy nobles throughout the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;. They don't provide any meaningful help or information, but they do offer some limited dialogue for those who like to converse with all the creatures they come across.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, they will inquire about your presence in the house of nobility where they may be employed or, in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;, lament about the death of &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn , they appear following incidents within the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Palace\"&gt;Ducal Palace&lt;/a&gt;. They also appear in a couple of cut scenes.\nIn , they either are left to lament the murderous deeds by the fallen knight &lt;a href=\"Anomen%20Delryn\"&gt;Anomen Delryn&lt;/a&gt; or they end up being killed by &lt;a href=\"Troll\"&gt;Troll&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "46699", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46699", "title": "Servants' Quarters", "text": "The Servants' Quarters are found on the property of &lt;a href=\"Travenhurst%20Manor\"&gt;Travenhurst Manor&lt;/a&gt; in the town of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;. The building is located on the left side of the manor house and is partially obscured by a large tree. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe house is populated at night by a sleeping man. The chest next to the first bed is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. The chest between the two beds is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers is empty."}
{"id": "47426", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47426", "title": "Serving Wench", "text": "A Serving Wench is found tending to patrons in the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elfsong%20Tavern\"&gt;Elfsong Tavern&lt;/a&gt;. They have very little dialogue and offer noting of any importance when spoken to."}
{"id": "16716", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16716", "title": "Set Exploding Trap", "text": "Set Exploding Trap is a &lt;a href=\"high-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;high-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt;, except the &lt;a href=\"Shadowdancer\"&gt;Shadowdancer&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a change to the Rogue's HLA:\nExploding Trap (revised ability)\nBy mixing unstable alchemical compounds together, a rogue can set a powerful trap which unleashes a violent explosion when triggered. The force of the blast deals 15d6 points of fire damage to all nearby opponents, pushing them back and knocking them off their feet. Enemies may attempt to save vs. breath in order to reduce the damage by half and avoid being pushed away and knocked down. Exceptionally large or heavy creatures (Dragons, Giants, Stone and Iron Golems) may take damage but are unaffected by the secondary effects of the blast.\nNote: the Exploding Trap is alchemical (rather than magical) in nature and is therefore not subject to the target's magic resistance."}
{"id": "46216", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46216", "title": "Set Snare", "text": ""}
{"id": "46212", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46212", "title": "Set Special Snare", "text": "Set Special Snare is the special ability of the &lt;a href=\"Bounty%20Hunter\"&gt;Bounty Hunter&lt;/a&gt;, which they innately know in addition to the standard &lt;a href=\"Traps\"&gt;thief traps&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe Bounty Hunter selects a spot to place the Special Snare, which can be \"thrown\" or placed within the character's visual range (a bit less than 30 feet). This ability is selected from the \"Special Abilities\" menu icon on the character's record, or by using the F12 key on PC keyboard interface.\nOnce the snare is placed, it remains there indefinitely until triggered by an enemy creature's proximity.\nAn enemy creature moving within about 16 feet of the snare will trigger the device and unleash the effects as described above. These effects are applied to any enemies in range when the snare is triggered.\nOnce the snare has activated, it is expended and disappears from the area map.\nA successful \"Set Traps\" skill roll is required to successfully place a Set Special Snare. Failure can result either wasting the trap or being damaged/exposed to one's own trap, as if they were an enemy. This risk can be reduced by improving that skill up to 100%. Skill points higher than 100% are generally unnecessary.\nThere is a limit of 6 traps/snares allowed at one time per area map."}
{"id": "16714", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16714", "title": "Set Spike Trap", "text": "Set Spike Trap is a &lt;a href=\"high-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;high-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt;, except &lt;a href=\"Shadowdancer\"&gt;Shadowdancer&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod as part of the \"Core Components\" changes this Rogue HLA: From the mod's Readme:\n\"Spike Trap (revised ability)\nThis ability allows the rogue to set a powerful spring-loaded spike trap that deals 20D6 points of piercing damage to the unsuspecting creature that sets it off.\nNote: The Spike Trap now deals piercing damage. For reference, in the original game its damage type was flagged as magical (i.e. like Magic Missile) which didn't make much sense for a non-magical ability.\""}
{"id": "16717", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16717", "title": "Set Time Trap", "text": "Set Time Trap is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;bards&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt;, except for those with the &lt;a href=\"Shadowdancer\"&gt;Shadowdancer&lt;/a&gt; kit. As its name suggests, it allows the rogue to set a special trap that can mimic the effects of a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nThe &lt;a href=\"wizard\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt;s' &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; spell lasts longer and with no need for trigger condition. However, the trap may be set while hidden\u00a0on top of enemies or where enemies will come once battle starts. This HLA may also be chosen far more than 5 times (the limit of level 9 spell slots for mages).\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a change to the Rogue's HLA, and removes Time Trap and replaces with:\nAcid Trap (replaces Time Trap)\nThis ability allows the rogue to set a powerful trap that splashes nearby opponents with a highly vitriolic alchemical mixture which deals 10d6 points of acid damage. Once the acid engulfs a target it becomes difficult to remove. Afflicted opponents must make a saving throw vs. breath or take an additional 2d6 points of acid damage during each of the following three rounds. Creatures who are particularly vulnerable to acid damage (such as Trolls) do not get a saving throw.\nNote: the Acid Trap is alchemical (rather than magical) in nature and is therefore not subject to the target's magic resistance."}
