{"id": "15569", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15569", "title": "Sethle", "text": "Sethle is a gruff older man who works as a grave keeper in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in this area outside a large crypt.\nGameplay.\nIf addressed by the party, Sethle isn't particularly friendly, and says little of interest. He may ask \"You got business here, or you just like walkin' on the graves?\"\nHowever, if engaged in conversation after helping the unfortunate victim &lt;a href=\"Tirdir\"&gt;Tirdir&lt;/a&gt; from being buried alive, then there are different dialogue options. The party can interrogate him to find out if he knows anything about poor Tirdir being put in the ground yet still alive.\nThrough dialogue, and verbal threats, you may learn something important. Sethle may give in and say:\n\" \"I don't know nothing! I just lets them bury what they want when I fill in the graves! It's a man in red what's I see! He's the one. He pays gold, and I turn my head! You want him!\"\"\nAfter a tense back and forth, the party will be able to understand that Sethle is paid in order to \"look the other way\" from certain criminals who wish to dispose of various victims in the graveyard. If forced, he reveals some information about his contact's location, saying:\n\"\"I don't know where he is; he comes here. Look, I help you. I think I see him sometimes by Bridge District. There, I help good! You're not going to tell anyone, are you? Are you?\"\nThe party can tell Sethle to leave and never come back, or even resort to violence if they wish. Despite the fact that Sethle has obviously engaged in less than honest behavior, the game has marked him as an innocent, so if slain there will be a party reputation penalty. \nTo avoid this, you could resolve this by threatening Sethle with reporting him to the authorities, or even saying \"Pathetic creature! Run away, far away, and don't you ever come back!\"\" \nNotes.\nSethle's &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; is changed from lawful neutral to neutral evil in the enhanced game .\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, Sethle could have some part to play in the \"Money Lender\" storyline, but only if he hasn't been chased off or threatened yet."}
{"id": "52228", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52228", "title": "Seven-Legged Spider", "text": "Seven-Legged Spider is a that can be encountered in \"\".\nLocation.\nIt can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Cave\"&gt;Spider Cave&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;.\nCombat.\nIt attacks at melee (1 foot) range, doing 2d6\u00a0 at &lt;a href=\"Speed%20Factor\"&gt;Speed Factor&lt;/a&gt; 3 and can damage targets requiring a +1 weapon. It is naturally &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;d, but it can be dispelled.&lt;a href=\"MAGE06.ITM\"&gt;MAGE06.ITM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/ref&gt;.\nIt is immune to &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; and paralyze.\nLoot.\nIt drops a &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider%20Leg\"&gt;Giant Spider Leg&lt;/a&gt;, used for the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Call%20of%20the%20Wild%20Mage\"&gt;The Call of the Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "46830", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46830", "title": "Seven Suns", "text": "The Seven Suns building is the local operations base for the namesake &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Suns%20Trading%20Coster\"&gt;trading coster&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. It is located between the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Shop\"&gt;Potion Shop&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"General%20Store%20%28AR1116%29\"&gt;general store&lt;/a&gt; are located behind the building and it faces the waterfront. The front door is unlocked.\nLayout.\nGround and Second Floors.\nEntering the ground floor, you are immediately spoken to by one of three &lt;a href=\"merchant\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt;s standing near the front door. A brief conversation reveals that &lt;a href=\"Doppelganger\"&gt;shapeshifters&lt;/a&gt; have infiltrated the coster. This information is important for correctly carrying out &lt;a href=\"The%20Seven%20Suns\"&gt;The Seven Suns&lt;/a&gt; side quest for &lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar&lt;/a&gt;. Two more merchants are located on the second floor. There are no lootable containers on either floor.\nBasement.\nA single doppelganger is down here guarding &lt;a href=\"Jhasso\"&gt;Jhasso&lt;/a&gt; who is the leader of the trading coster and is being kept captive in the basement.\nLoot"}
{"id": "5613", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5613", "title": "Seven Suns Trading Coster", "text": "The Seven Suns Trading Coster is a merchant organization that has its base in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and operates within the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt;, the player is sent\u00a0by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"The%20Seven%20Suns\"&gt;investigate&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Suns\"&gt;Seven Suns&lt;/a&gt; building. When you first enter the building a merchant inside will hail you and tell how something strange has been going on inside the organization recently. Now you can go to Scar and he will double your reward if you agree to clean out the Seven Suns. Instead, you can talk to another one of the merchants three times which will cause it and all the other merchants to turn into &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt;s. \nOr it is possible to go directly to the basement where a doppelganger and the head of the guild will be. Kill all the doppelgangers on the main floor, upstairs and in the basement and then go back to Scar and tell him about the Seven Suns doppelganger problem. If you did not talk with Scar about the shapeshifters issue, you will be scolded by Scar's lieutenant for an unauthorized action."}
