{"id": "45480", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45480", "title": "Thayan Circlet", "text": "The Thayan Circlet is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Vicross\"&gt;Vicross&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Neera%20-%20Thayan%20Estate\"&gt;Thayan Estate&lt;/a&gt; as a part of &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Destroying%20the%20Order%20of%20Eight%20Staves\"&gt;Destroying the Order of Eight Staves&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nGameplay.\nThe circlet gives a +15 &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge%23Mechanics\"&gt;wild surge bonus&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt; wearing it, and it stacks with bonuses from other sources. For a level 31 Wild Mage using &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Chaos%20Shield\"&gt;Improved Chaos Shield&lt;/a&gt;, equipping this circlet amounts to cutting by more than one third the remaining surges that do not cast the desired spell \u2014 13 out of 36. The figure is about a quarter at level 25. This item is the only way to remove the risky &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge%2361\"&gt;Held #61&lt;/a&gt; from the realm of possible surges."}
{"id": "50276", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50276", "title": "Thayan Fighter", "text": "Thayan Fighter is a human Fighter class warrior allied with the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt; to conduct Wizard bodyguard protection and enforcement operations in the Athkatla area for the Wild Mage hunting Order of the Eight Staves. These warriors are loyal to &lt;a href=\"Lanneth\"&gt;Lanneth&lt;/a&gt; and are headquartered in the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. They are not mercenaries and are actually Thayan Fighters assigned to the Red Wizards."}
{"id": "50277", "revid": "218448", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50277", "title": "Thayan Knight", "text": "Thayan Knight is a human Fighter class warrior allied with the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt; to conduct Wizard bodyguard protection and enforcement operations in the Athkatla area for the Wild Mage hunting Order of the Eight Staves. These elite warriors are loyal to &lt;a href=\"Lanneth\"&gt;Lanneth&lt;/a&gt; and are headquartered in the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. They are not mercenaries and are actually Thayan Fighters assigned to the Red Wizards. The Knight is protected from fear effects and morale failure."}
{"id": "50273", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50273", "title": "Thayan Mercenary", "text": "Thayan Mercenary is a human Fighter class warrior in the employ of the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt; hired to conduct protection and enforcement operations in the Athkatla area for the Wild Mage hunting Order of the Eight Staves. These mercenary members are led by &lt;a href=\"Fadell%20Ironeye\"&gt;Fadell Ironeye&lt;/a&gt; and are headquartered in the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. There are a total of three types of these mercenary warriors, and the example in the first info box is for the spear wielding variety. The two other types are summarized below in their own info boxes."}
{"id": "21483", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21483", "title": "Thayan Wizard", "text": "Thayan Wizards accompany &lt;a href=\"Ekandor\"&gt;Ekandor&lt;/a&gt; during his attempts to hunt down &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; in the town of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; and in &lt;a href=\"Adoy%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Adoy's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe wizard will only use the following spells in battle:"}
